title: scampi-style shrimp
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, cook and stir green onion and garlic in margarine and oil 1 minute; add shrimp.
Cook and stir until shrimp are pink; add lemon juice and salt and heat good.

title: dutch green bean salad
directions: Cook beans in 2 pints salted water.
Should not be completely well done.
Drain and cool.
Rub the salad bowl in which you want to prepare the dressing with the sliced garlic clove.
Add all ingredients except the vegetable oil to the bowl.
Mix carefully. Stir in vegetable oil slowly until the dressing becomes thick and smooth.
Add beans and toss carefully.
Place covered bowl, for at least 1 hour, in the refrigerator before serving.
Decorate with a few parsley leaves.
Serves 4.

title: grandma's pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix milk and lemonade together. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust and freeze. Serve frozen garnished with Cool Whip. Limeade may be substituted for lemonade if you prefer.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, horseradish, basil and oregano.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Stir in shrimp and cook 10 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marvelous marinated mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms to remove any soil.
Heat vinegar, oil, garlic, salt, parsley, mustard and sugar to boil.
Add mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Allow to cool in liquid.
Then refrigerate several hours, stirring occasionally.
Drain and serve with cocktail picks.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: In casserole dish, crumble corn bread and biscuits.
Add onion salt, celery, eggs, sage, black pepper and cream of chicken soup. Mix well, then tear chicken into pieces and mix with the other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: absolute favorite fish and chips
directions: Thaw frozen fish.
Cut into serving size pieces.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Cut potatoes into uniform strips slightly larger than French fries.
Fry a few at a time in deep hot fat (375°) until golden, 5 to 6 minutes.
Remove.
Drain and keep warm.

title: grandma's ginger cookies("thin and crispy")
directions: In saucepan, bring shortening, sugar, molasses and salt to a slow boil until sugar melts.
Cool.
Add eggs after mixture cools. Add flour, spices and soda/vinegar mix.
Dough will be stiff. Roll out very thin (about 1/8-inch thickness).
If dough sticks, add small amounts of flour to board, pin or hands to keep from sticking.
Bake at 350° about 7 to 8 minutes.
Cookies should be very thin and crispy.
Flavor will improve as they are stored in tins.

title: sliced cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat until light and fluffy.
Mix dry ingredients together and mix well into creamed mixture.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Mix well.
Drop onion into batter and drop into hot grease; fry until brown.
Remove and serve.

title: lynchburg lemonade
directions: Garnish with lemon slices and cherries.
Makes 7 cups.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix corn, flour and sugar until well coated in an 8 to 10-inch casserole dish.
Pour egg and milk mixture over this until well mixed.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring every 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve as side dish.

title: marble cheesecake(easy and delicious)
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter in medium bowl and mix well. Pat into bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: dirt cups
directions: Will also need 8 to 10 clear plastic cups.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Beat butter and sugar to a cream.
Add beaten eggs, vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Roll out thin.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: triple chocolate fudge cake
directions: Crumble cake mix with eggs.
Cook pudding as directed on package.
Pour hot pudding on crumbled cake mix and mix together. Stir in package of chocolate chips.

title: chicken scallop bake
directions: Pour milk, soup, chicken broth and eggs over crumbs.
Add chicken.
Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Cut into squares.
Cover with sauce.

title: ice cream a la mode rosie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and place in an ice cream freezer.

title: cooked play dough
directions: In a pan mix the first 3 ingredients; add the remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Cook on medium heat until dough is the right thickness for use (about 3 to 5 minutes).
Remove from pan as soon as possible.
"Work" or knead it a little by hand until it feels like play dough.
Store in plastic bag at room temperature.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
In another bowl combine pineapple, nuts, bananas and strawberries.
Mix all well and add Cool Whip gently.
Freeze before serving.
Place in refrigerator for 1 or 1 1/2 hours before serving.

title: crock-pot beef
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low approximately 6 to 7 hours.
When done, flake meat apart and stir. Serve on hard rolls with Mozzarella cheese.
Tastes just like the beef sandwiches at Portillo's.
Great and easy for the working mom.

title: baked chinese noodles and oysters(oysters, oriental)
directions: Drain liquid from the water chestnuts and the bean sprouts and add to the salted water in which the egg noodles are being cooked. Cook egg noodles as directed on the package.
Drain.
Place layer of egg noodles in bottom of a buttered 2-quart casserole dish. Cover with 1/3 of the oysters.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a large skillet melt butter.
Cut each onion into 1/2 and add to butter.
Saute until light brown.
Sprinkle in flour and stir.
Add water, vegetable,
bouillon and spices.
Bring to boil. Cover and cook for 20 minutes.
Then add white wine.
Turn down to simmer.
In individual bowls, put in a thick cube of Italian bread, the soup and then sprinkle with Jarlsberg cheese.

title: pawtucket fingers
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together. Add butter and mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Last, add vanilla and nuts. Spread thin in jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool, cut in finger lengths and roll in powdered sugar.
Keeps fresh in a tin container.

title: petite pinwheels
directions: Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Spread with cream cheese; sprinkle with ham and olives, pressing lightly.
Roll up, starting at the short end; seal edges. Cut each roll into 4 or 5 slices.
Place, cut side down, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 16 to 20 appetizers.

title: homemade cracker jacks
directions: Mix popped corn and peanuts in very large ovenproof bowl.
Keep warm in 250° oven.
Melt margarine in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to rolling boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil without stirring 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla.
Quickly pour over popcorn mixture, tossing until kernels and nuts are well coated.
Spread out in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Remove from oven.
Turn out on aluminum foil to cool. Break into pieces.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: banana punch
directions: Make syrup by adding 4 cups sugar to 6 cups boiling water. After sugar is dissolved, remove from heat and add the following: 12 ounce can frozen orange juice mixed with three 12 ounce cans water, the pulp and juice of 2 lemons, 1 (46 ounce) can pineapple juice, 5 bananas, well blended.
Freeze to a frozen slush.
Frozen slush may be kept for long periods.

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place roasting rack in large roasting pan.
Rinse chicken; pat dry with paper towels.
In large bowl, toss stuffing with 1 cup water. In large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion, spinach, prosciutto, garlic, sage and rosemary to skillet; saute until tender, about 5 minutes. Add spinach mixture to stuffing.
Stir in heavy cream and lemon juice; mix well.
Spoon stuffing loosely into chicken cavity, filling about 3/4 full.
Fold skin over openings and close with metal skewers.
Tuck wings under chicken.
Place on roasting rack. Roast chicken until an instant-read meat thermometer, inserted in the thigh, not touching bone, registers 180 degrees and chicken is golden, about 1 hour 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and add beaten eggs.
Add milk and soda; mix well.
Add bananas, salt and nuts.
Blend in flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in greased bread pan.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: refrigerator pizza
directions: Spread unbaked crescent rolls over cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes until golden brown.
Let crust cool until it is no longer warm when you touch it.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In cup and with fork, beat eggs slightly; reserve 1 tablespoon.
Stir milk and remaining egg into flour mixture just until flour is moistened.
Turn dough out onto well-floured surface.
With floured hands, knead about 10 strokes to mix thoroughly.
Shape into ball; place in casserole.
In center of ball with sharp knife, cut a 4-inch cross 1/4-inch deep.
Brush with reserved egg.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in casserole on wire rack 10 minutes.

title: easy chicken dinner
directions: Clean chicken.
Peel, clean and cut up potatoes.
Stuff potatoes in chicken cavity.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Drain your 2 cans of vegetables and cook in your chicken broth to use as side dish.
Delicious!

title: pasta salad
directions: Chop fresh vegetables.
Other vegetables could also be used, i.e. broccoli, cauliflower or carrot.
Mix vegetables and pasta together well.
Pour on salad dressing.
Mix again.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: hush puppies
directions: Make corn bread as usual. Add 1/4 cup fresh cut corn to the mixture before baking.

title: rice salad
directions: Combine the above ingredients.
Press and pack into custard cups.
Unmold on lettuce, garnish with tomato wedges, and sour cream dressed with chopped chives.

title: cheesy beer soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add flour and heat over low flame for 4 minutes.
Add in broth and cream.
Stir until smooth and thick.
Then add Cheez Whiz, beer, chives and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serve piping hot.
Garnish with popped popcorn.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all the ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: creamy scalloped chicken
directions: In 1-quart casserole, combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot; stir top with chips.
Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups, 4 servings.

title: nadine's chocolate chiffon pie
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour, salt and cocoa; beat in egg yolks. Gradually stir in hot milk.
Cook in double boiler until slightly thickened.
Add the dissolved gelatin to hot custard.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Cool.
Beat the egg whites until in peaks, adding the remaining sugar.
Fold into the cooled custard.
Pour into pie crust and chill several hours.

title: easy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Place chicken in large pot with one stalk or piece of celery and one carrot and small amount of onion salt.
Add about 2 pints cold water.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer until chicken is tender.
Take chicken from broth, reserving broth.
Cut chicken from bones in small pieces.
Cook spaghetti in broth until tender; drain well.
Blend soup and milk in saucepan.
Add chicken, pimento and mushrooms.
Heat thoroughly.
Layer spaghetti, chicken mixture and Cheddar cheese in long casserole dish, sprinkling each layer with salt and pepper.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecue smoked sausage links
directions: Mix all together in slow cooker on high about 1 hour, then turn to low (simmer) and hold to serve.

title: vanilla bark candy clusters
directions: Melt bark in microwave, approximately 1 to 2 minutes or until melted.
Stir until smooth.
Add next 4 ingredients as listed, 1 at a time.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.
Will set up in about 1 hour.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Mix
dressing
by
package
directions.
Make
balls of dressing.
Wrap chicken around dressing.
Place in a casserole dish.
Mix	together
1 can of soup and 1 can of water.
Spoon some soup
on chicken and pour rest in dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Cover with foil.
Uncover last 15 minutes.

title: ham and cheese puffs
directions: Grease and flour large cookie sheet. In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat butter and water until melted and boiling. Remove from heat and stir in flour and mustard, all at once, boiling vigorously. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition until smooth. Cut ham in small pieces. Mix ham and cheese into batter. Drop batter into small mounds 2-inches apart. Bake at 375° about 30 minutes or until golden. Turn heat off and leave in oven 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugar, brown sugar, egg, water and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: biscotti savoiardi
directions: Put eggs, baking powder, sugar, lemon and vanilla in a bowl and mix.
Mix flour and melted butter.
Combine the egg mixture with the flour mixture together.
Leave in refrigerator until next day.
Make balls and roll them in sugar.
Place on wax paper. Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes until done.

title: crab imperial
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mr. jiggs' corned beef and cabbage
directions: Fry corned beef and onion, then add water and shoyu sauce with sugar (depending on how sweet you desire it).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 10 minutes, then add head of cabbage, sliced about 1/2 inch thick.
Simmer for about 10 minutes to soften cabbage, then separate in the pan of corned beef and cabbage.
Add eggs (like poached eggs).
Serve with rice.

title: green bean almondine
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and almonds until tender.
Drain beans, pimentos and mushrooms.
Mix together with undiluted soup. Add onion mixture and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Place in treated casserole pan (sprayed with Pam).
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: tahitian delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, measuring syrup.
Add water to make 3/4 cup. Add to gelatin. Chill until very thick.
Fold in fruit and coconut.
Pour into individual molds. Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool and add remaining ingredients.
Stir all ingredients together and chill until firm.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, salt and butter or margarine thoroughly.
Beat egg, lemon rind and extract into creamed mixture until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Gradually stir into creamed ingredients.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick on floured board.
Cut into fancy shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 9 to 10 minutes or until light brown around edges.
Remove to cooling rack.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: parsley spread
directions: Chop parsley well after washing and removing stems.
Mix with enough mayonnaise/sour cream/yogurt to be spreadable and to taste. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion (1 tablespoon per bunch). Serve with Wheat Thins, Melba toast or Triscuits.
Guaranteed to be gone in minutes.

title: limeade
directions: Cut limes in half.
Squeeze juice and pulp out, pour into pitcher.
Add water and honey.
Stir and add ice cubes.

title: no sugar pumpkin pie
directions: *Or 2 1/2 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice.

title: sausage cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 10 inch skillet.
Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Combine eggs, cornmeal, corn, milk and oil.
Pour one half batter into pan; sprinkle with sausage and onion.
Add cheese.
Pour remaining batter over top.
Bake for 30 40 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: low-cholesterol, low-sodium meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, mix all the ingredients thoroughly.
Use 1/2 of the tomato sauce and reserve the other half for spreading on top of the loaf.
Garnish with parsley tops.
Bake until lightly browned or until done in a 350° oven for about 1 1/4 hours.

title: maple walnut scones
directions: Mix flour with brown sugar, baking powder, salt, soda and ginger.
Cut butter into flour mixture in small particles.
Add egg, buttermilk and maple syrup.
Stir just until mixed.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Drop batter by heaping tablespoons onto lightly greased baking sheet 2 inches apart, making 10 mounds. Bake at 425° for 12 to 13 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: gingerbread
directions: Place eggs, syrup, oil, sugar and spices in a large bowl; beat well.
Add dissolved soda.
Sift in flour and beat well.
Add boiling water and beat lightly and quickly.
Place in 9 x 12-inch pan, greased well.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack firmly into an ungreased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: pumpkin upside-down cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan. Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Top with nuts.
Drizzle butter over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut when cool.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream before serving.

title: sizzling cheese appetizers
directions: Mix ingredients except for bread.
Spread mixture on bread and broil until sizzling, about 5 minutes.

title: black eye pea dip
directions: Saute onions in oleo.
Run peas and onions through blender. Mix all ingredients and heat until bubbly.
Serve warm with chips.

title: florida chicken breast
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put chicken in baking pan.
Spoon melted margarine on top of chicken.
Then sprinkle with soup mix.
Spoon thawed orange juice over all.
Cover and bake 1 hour until chicken is tender.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients to mix.
Toss peaches in dry ingredients.
Dump into pie shell.
Pour cream over all.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: 'possum and 'taters
directions: If one is handy, skin and dress opossum.
(Roast beef may be substituted for the opossum.)
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over medium heat until very tender.
Place opossum pieces in center of large baking pan and arrange sweet potatoes around them. Sprinkle sugar and margarine over potatoes.
Pour 2 cups of broth from cooked opossum over all.
Place in preheated 375° oven and bake until potatoes are fork-tender, slightly browned and broth has evaporated.

title: grilled spam on buns
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put on buns with cheese on top. Put under broiler.
Makes 16 buns.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cut squash into 2-inch pieces.
Add onion and cook.
Drain well and mash.
Add brown sugar, butter, eggs, 1 cup of cheese, salt and cornstarch that has been added to the evaporated milk. Pour into flat casserole and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in blender well. Add by hand the rest of the ingredients. Chill for 1 hour. Roll dough in balls the size of a walnut. Roll in sugar.
Place on greased pan 2-inches apart. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Will crack on top.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: ham and chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except
dressing and place mixture in baking dish.
Sprinkle dressing on top.
Bake at 350° until hot through.
May use turkey or chicken and omit the ham.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter in microwave.
Add cheese and butter to sugar, cocoa, nuts and vanilla.
Place in greased dish and chill. Place in refrigerator to store after chilling.

title: easy-as-pie-crust
directions: In a bowl, mix flour and salt.
Cut in shortening with two knives or a pastry blender until it is cut into particles the size of small peas.
Sprinkle ice water over top of mixture and mix with a fork.
Push all the large clumps of flour to one side and continue sprinkling mixture until all flour is moistened and mixed into large clumps.
Knead clumps together into a smooth ball. Wrap and chill until ready to use.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt all ingredients except whipping cream and crust in double boiler and cool thoroughly.
Beat whipping cream until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Put into pie crust.
Place in refrigerator or freezer until serving time.
Can be made ahead and kept in deep freezer.
Can be topped with Cool Whip or dab of whipped cream when served.
Delicious, but rich.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil well.
Sift and add the flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Stir well.
Add sliced apples and chopped nuts.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 375°.
Serve with a scoop of ice cream topped with sauce.

title: busy day chicken
directions: Scatter rice on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay pieces of chicken on top of rice.
Combine soup with water; pour over chicken. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover the last 20 minutes to allow chicken to brown.

title: seven layered mexican appetizer
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch serving dish, layer ingredients in the following order:
Spread bean dip on bottom of dish, mash avocados and add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix sour cream with taco seasoning and layer on top of avocado mixture.
Top with olives, onions, tomatoes and grated cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Melt butter in pan; set aside.
Mix rest of ingredients; pour into pan with butter.
Sprinkle cinnamon, a tablespoon sugar and pecans on top.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: rice dressing
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour in pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cover dressing with foil before baking.

title: granny's teacakes
directions: Mix butter, eggs and sugar. Mix well. Add flour and milk. Mix well. Add baking powder and vanilla. Mix until all lumps are out. Roll out thin. Cut and place about 1-inch apart. Place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° until done.

title: turkey and boiled dressing
directions: While turkey is baking, prepare bread crumbs (6 to 8 cups, depending on how much dressing you want to make).
Chop onion and celery stalks and add to bread crumbs.
Add sage, egg and a little salt.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar,
eggs and oil well, then add flour, salt and soda. Mix
well,	then
by
hand	mix
in fruit cocktail with juice. Pour
into	greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Mix all together except last 3 ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Crush crackers with margarine and spread on top.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Keep starter in refrigerator. Every 2 to 5 days,
take it out. Shake it up and feed it.

title: sticky bun coffee ring
directions: Brush a 10-inch fluted tube pan with 1 tablespoon butter. In a small bowl, combine syrup and remaining butter. Drizzle 2 tablespoons into pan.

title: pot de creme
directions: Place first five ingredients in blender.
Heat milk to boiling; pour over all ingredients.
Cover and blend one minute. Pour into serving dishes.

title: chocolate raspberry torte
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions for 2 layers.
Cook, cut each layer in half.
Melt 6 ounces chocolate in ovenproof bowl (190°), make chocolate curls with remaining 2 ounces chocolate bar.
Cool. Thaw raspberries and drain off all liquid.
Blend melted chocolate and butter in bowl.
Set aside.
Stir raspberries into Cool Whip.
Set aside.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, grapes and almonds. Set aside.

title: antipasto
directions: Combine ingredients, including the juice from the mushrooms and artichoke hearts.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve on a platter alongside or garnished with Prosciutto or Prosciuttini, Genoa salami and sliced Provolone.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: After cutting cabbage, salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle Wesson oil over mixture and then lemon juice.
Stir until well mixed.
Decide if more or less lemon juice is needed.

title: tang pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix and pour into pie crusts.
(Do not use a mixer.)
Top with Cool Whip.
Place mandarin orange slices on top.

title: spaghetti
directions: Chop onions, celery, bell peppers, garlic and mushrooms. Put in pot with olive oil and saute. When finished, pour out all excess oil. Brown all meat; add tomatoes, sauce and paste. Add meat. Add salt, basil, oregano, red peppers, parsley and sugar. Simmer 8 to 10 hours. Stir every half hour, low heat.

title: mexican hots
directions: Mix together and make patties.
Fry, broil or grill them. Also good without the pepper sauce.

title: cherry peek-a-boo
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Add vanilla, flour and nuts; mix all together.
Mixture will be thick and sticky.
Spread 3/4 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with pie filling.
Spoon remaining dough on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hobo supper
directions: Roll hamburger meat into four 1/2-pound balls. Slice onion, bell pepper, carrots and potatoes to medium sizes. Place on top of hamburger balls. Put each one in foil and wrap well. Bake for 1 hour at 450°. Salt and pepper to taste. Makes a whole meal for each person and is very filling and good.

title: raisin nut pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy and add sugar and raisins (after boiling raisins and sugar for 5 minutes and draining).
Add butter, cinnamon and pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: mom's peach ice cream
directions: Peel and mash peaches.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs and slowly add sugar until dissolved.
Stir in cream and peaches. Freeze in ice cream freezer or do it the old fashioned way.
Pour into shallow pan (like old ice cube trays without dividers) and freeze until it is beginning to set up, then stir well and re-freeze, repeating 2 to 3 times.
Serve when it is frozen.

title: 7-inch berry pie deluxe
directions: Crush and drain berries to get juice; may add water if not enough juice from berries.
Boil all ingredients, except berries, until thickened.
Place berries in pie shell and pour sauce over them.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chewy chocolate no-fat cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray baking sheets with nonstick spray. Combine oats, flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons onto baking sheet.
Bake until set, 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash, core and slice tomatoes 1/4 inch thick.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place corn meal in a small bowl.
Dip each tomato slice into corn meal, turning to coat both sides.
In a large skillet, heat 1/4 cup bacon drippings or oil.
Add coated tomato slices.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes per side.
Turning will depend on size and moisture in tomatoes.
Add oil as needed.
When tomatoes are lightly brown on both sides, place on a paper towel lined platter.

title: louisiana chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Drain.
Combine tomatoes and cornstarch in saucepan.
Stir to dissolve cornstarch.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove chicken from baking dish. Pour all but 1 cup sauce into dish.
Arrange chicken over sauce in dish; top with remaining sauce.
Place 1 slice cheese on each piece of chicken.
Bake until cheese melts.
Garnish with parsley. Serve with hot cooked rice, if desired.

title: caramel-chocolate pears
directions: Unwrap caramel sheets.
Using a round or scalloped cutter, cut out a 1 1/2-inch circle from the center of each sheet.
Rinse and dry pears; remove stems.
Center a sheet of caramel over the stem end of each pear.
Wrap caramel around the pear, pressing ends under base of pear.
Insert a wooden stick into stem end of each pear.
Line a baking sheet with wax paper.
Stand pears on baking sheet.
Bake in a 300° oven for 5 minutes.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.

title: mexican breakfast twists
directions: Roll each biscuit into a long rope.
Pinch ends together to form a circle.
Mix together the cinnamon and sugar.
Dip the circles into melted butter, then into sugar mixture.
Bake at 425° on baking sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook zita until tender.
Brown meat in small amount of oil. In a large baking dish, place enough sauce to cover bottom.
Place layers of ziti, sauce, meat and Ricotta until all is used up.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover pan tightly with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese if desired.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in heavy baking dish.
Top with strips of cheese.
Mix other half of tomato soup with 1/4 cup water. Pour over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, soda and vinegar and beat well.
Add oil and flour alternately until all has been added.
Blend in buttermilk. Add vanilla and food coloring.
Pour into three 9-inch cake pans and bake in a 350° oven until done, approximately 20 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Debone chicken and divided into 10 serving pieces. Remove the skin.
Wrap bacon around chicken (1/2 slice).
Mix sour cream with soup.
Pour over chicken.
Top with almonds.
Bake 3 hours at 300°.
Serve over rice.

title: grammy's cheese ball
directions: Cream together cheese and cream cheese.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Shape into ball and wrap in aluminum foil. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs.
Beat well until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven or until golden brown.

title: macaroni pizza style
directions: Brown beef, onion, salt and pepper.
When brown, add tomato soup.
Cook macaroni until tender and drain well.
Beat together milk and egg and add to the macaroni.
Spread macaroni mixture on the bottom of shallow greased baking dish.
Cover with beef and tomato mixture.
Top with slices or grated Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water and stir.
Add cold water.
Add pineapple and cream cheese.
Mix well.
Cover with marshmallows an sprinkle nuts on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanutty chocolates
directions: Break chocolate into pieces.
Add flavored chips.
Melt over low heat.
Remove from heat and spoon into miniature foil cups. Top with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate 30 minutes to set.
Store in airtight container.

title: sliced green tomato pickle
directions: Pile the green tomatoes and onions in an enamel pan in alternating layers.
Sprinkle salt over top and let stand overnight.
The next morning, drain, then add water and vinegar. Let come to a boil; drain and add sugar, vinegar and pickling spices.
Let mixture come to a boil and cook for about 10 minutes before packing in sterilized jars and sealing.

title: almond noodles
directions: Add salt to boiling water, add vegetable oil.
Add noodles and boil on low heat, stirring occasionally, until noodles are tender (about 7 minutes).
Saute almonds in butter in small skillet until lightly browned.
Drain noodles and toss with sauteed almonds and leftover butter from pan.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Layer items in order.
Mix 1 stick melted margarine with crushed vanilla wafers, firmly packed in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Add pineapple.
Mix 1 stick margarine, vanilla and powdered sugar and pour over the other layers.
Slice bananas over this. Add Cool Whip on top.
Add nuts and cherries, if desired.
Keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook onion in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Combine 1 cup cheese, 1 can soup, 1 cup juice from asparagus. Layer the following:
Crushed saltines and 1 cup shredded cheese on bottom of casserole dish.
Cover with part of soup mixture.
Add layer of asparagus and cheese and cover with rest of soup mixture. Sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: ceviche
directions: Put scallops into strainer and pour boiling water over them. Submerge them in lemon and lime juice.
Add onion, tomatoes, olives and chopped chiles; mix well.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic salt and sugar to taste.
Add cilantro.
Marinate for at least 12 hours or overnight.
Serve chilled.
Will keep in refrigerator for 4 days.

title: layered chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Heat oil in small skillet to 350°. Soften each tortilla by dipping in hot oil for 2-3 seconds on each side; drain on paper towels. Place 1 tortilla on lightly greased baking sheet. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese, 1/4 cup chicken, 1 tablespoon green chilies and 1 tablespoon onion. Top with a second tortilla. Pour 1/3 cup enchilada sauce over stack. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cheese. Repeat with remaining tortillas to make 3 additional stacks. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Makes 4 servings. Recipe can be doubled.

title: sugar plums
directions: Beat butter until creamy; add sugar gradually and beat until smooth.
Add vanilla and almond flavoring.
Sift flour and salt together; add to butter mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in oats; mix well.
Dough will be quite stiff.
Shape into balls around cherries.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 30 minutes in 325° preheated oven.
While warm, roll in sifted confectioners sugar. Yields more than 3 dozen.

title: snappy eggs
directions: Butter a large shallow baking dish. Split and seed chilies (I use the mild ones) and spread flat in bottom of dish.
Cover chilies with cheese.
In a large bowl, beat eggs and add Bisquick and milk.
Beat well with mixer.
Pour egg mixture over peppers and cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: vegetable pizza appetizers
directions: Press crescent rolls into two ungreased baking sheets, making sure to seal seams.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Watch closely to avoid overbrowning.
Cool completely.

title: some mores
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter together. Add peanuts, marshmallows, and Rice Krispies. Drop by spoonsful on waxed paper.

title: squash relish
directions: Soak squash in 2/3 cups of salt water for 1 hour.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Mix 2 cups sugar and 2 cups vinegar together and bring to boil.
Put in jars.
If you want it hot, put in hot peppers.

title: almond tarts
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add almonds, paste and lemon juice.
Use tart pans; cut pastry to fit. Fill each 1/2 full of mixture.
Bake at 450° for 7 minutes. Reduce to 350°; bake for 30 minutes.
Dust with sugar.
On each tart, place dab of jam.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Arrange peaches in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar and the lemon juice.
Heat in a low 250° oven while preparing shortcake.
Combine flour, baking powder, 1 tablespoon of the remaining sugar and the salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture is like coarse crumbs.
Add milk and egg at once, stirring until flour is just moistened.
Spread dough over hot peaches and sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Bake in a 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes, until golden.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel sweet potatoes and cut into chunks.
Add about 2 cups of water to a large saucepan with lid and parboil the potatoes until almost done.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the liquid and cool.
Layer half the sweet potatoes in a large deep casserole.
Then add half the apples, spreading evenly.
Layer 1 1/2 cups of small marshmallows over apple.
Repeat again with layer of sweet potatoes and apples. (Add rest of the marshmallows on top towards the last 15 minutes of baking time and leave cover off.)

title: chocolate turtle pie
directions: Bring caramel topping to a boil in saucepan, stirring constantly.
Pour into pie shell.
Arrange pecans on top; chill. Combine pie filling mix and milk in a medium saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into a pie shell; place plastic wrap on surface of filling.
Chill 3 hours.
Remove plastic wrap. Cover with whipped topping.
Drizzle with additional caramel topping.
Garnish with pecans.

title: how to boil water
directions: Mix to form stiff dough.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Make hole with straw to hang as ornaments. Carefully put on rack to dry.
Let air dry for several days, turning occasionally to prevent warping.
Makes 12.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, oleo and Pet milk to a boil; boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and add 1 1/2 cups peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
After mixing, put pan in cold water.
Stir until hard to stir.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: joy's cold noodle salad
directions: *Toast lightly in toaster oven or microwave.

title: raspberry-strawberry bavarian
directions: Place gelatin in large bowl.
Add boiling water and stir to dissolve.
Add sour cream and beat with whisk or electric mixer until smooth.
Cut frozen ice cream into the gelatin mixture, cutting it into about 10 pieces.
Stir until melted and smooth. Add lemon juice and frozen fruit.
Use fork to break up the frozen fruit a bit, then use your bare hands until there are no pieces larger than a single piece of fruit.
It feels cold, but it does the best job.
Adding the fruit while it is frozen helps to set the gelatin mixture so that by the time the fruit is broken up and separated, the Bavarian is firm enough to keep the fruit from sinking.

title: jello pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 375° until top is firm and just begins to crack.

title: fruit nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add beaten eggs. Add 3 cups flour sifted with baking powder and salt. Mix rest of flour with chopped fruit and nuts. Stir into batter and add vanilla. Pour into a tube pan that has been greased and bottom lined with heavy brown paper. Bake at 250° for 3 hours. Let cool in pan.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil fryer until done.
Debone and shred meat. In a large saucepan combine all ingredients except potatoes.
Bring to a boil, then cover and simmer for at least one hour (longer if you have time).
Add cubed potatoes and finish cooking until potatoes are done.

title: barbecue chicken sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Place desired chicken wings or chicken breasts in shallow baking pan, spread with barbecue sauce and bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until chicken is tender.

title: pumpkin freeze
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and melted oleo; mix well.
Reserve 1/2 cup.
Put over top of mixture; press remaining mixture in an 8 x 9-inch square pan.
In a large mixer bowl, combine remaining ingredients; beat until just well combined.
Immediately pour over crumb mixture.
Freeze at least 4 hours.
Remove from freezer a few minutes before cutting.
Cut in squares.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: country style steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Flour meat.
Melt shortening in skillet until hot, then add floured meat.
Brown on each side 5 to 8 minutes.
Remove meat and put in baking dish.
Pour gravy over meat and bake uncovered at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: dad's cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, brown sugar, egg and vanilla. Add the dry ingredients and mix well.
Roll into small balls and flatten with a glass that has a moistened cloth held tightly over the end.
Bake about 10 minutes at 375°.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Slice pickles and rinse well with water.
Bring sugar, vinegar and spice to a boil: pour over rinsed pickles.
Turn jar upside down and rotate for a few hours.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Use 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put potatoes, cream of chicken soup, sour cream, onion and sharp cheese in bowl and mix.
Put in baking dish.
Pour margarine over top and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beet salad(lo-fat)
directions: Drain the pineapple and beets, saving the juice.
Add lemon juice, vinegar and enough water added to the juice to make 3 1/2 cups liquid.
Heat.
Add the sugar and jello, stirring until completely dissolved; cool.
Add cut up beets, pineapple and nuts. Pour into a large (9 x 13-inch or more) pan.
Chill until set. Serve on lettuce with a little mayonnaise, if desired.

title: borsch(beet soup)
directions: Prepare a meat stock.
Wash and shoestring the beets.
Add 1 cupful of hot meat stock, vinegar, tomato puree and boiled butter.
Bring to a boil, turn the heat down, cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours; stir every 15 to 20 minutes.
Shoestring and saute the carrots and parsley; add onion and continue to saute, then add to the beets.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in the sugar.

title: broccoli cornbread no. 1
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: fireside coffee mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
To make coffee, add 1 cup boiling water to 2 tablespoons plus 1 teaspoon of mix.
Stir.
Enjoy!

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar together in a large bowl until light.
Add flour to butter mixture and add nuts.
Roll into balls size of small walnut and flatten slightly on a greased baking sheet.
Refrigerate until firm, then bake in a 375° oven for 10 minutes or until done. Cool on cookie rack.
Sift with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: pansy's chicken enchilada
directions: Boil chicken until done; drain and chop.
Layer tortillas in bottom of large
baking pan.
Combine soup, peppers, salt and pepper in mixing bowl.
Saute garlic, onions and celery, then mix with soup mixture.
Add chicken and spread over tortillas.
Cover top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Sprinkle gelatin on cold water to soften and add water to dissolve.
Add mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion, Tabasco, paprika and salt.
Remove skin and visible bone from salmon.
Flake well. Add salmon to mixture and mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into oiled mold and chill.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Place pan in oven to warm.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese, in a large bowl.
Pour half of batter into warm, prepared pan.
Sprinkle half of cheese on top.
Add other half of batter on top of cheese.
Bake for 35 minutes. Yields 16 servings.
Has 199 calories each.

title: rocky road frosting
directions: Melt shortening with cocoa over boiling water.
Heat milk to simmer and pour over sugar and blend well.
Add cocoa mixture and vanilla.
Beat until slightly thickened.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread on cake.

title: broccoli rice(main dish)
directions: Melt butter; add Cheez Whiz, then celery soup and instant rice. Add frozen broccoli.
Bake in 2-quart 9 x 9-inch baking dish in a 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken salad(hot)
directions: Mix together.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Top with potato chips or seasoned crumbs. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spinach squares
directions: Place crescent rolls in bottom of pan. Mix other ingredients and pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: alabama cookies
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating well. Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by heaping teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool slightly on cookie sheets.
Remove to wire racks to cool completely.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: baked pork chops in gravy
directions: Sprinkle salt and brown chops on both sides in skillet in shortening.
Place in large shallow casserole; drain off all but 2 tablespoons of fat from skillet.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper in skillet.
Cook until brown; stir in water gradually, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Pour over chops.
Cover and bake in oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until tender at 350°.

title: cabbage and ground beef casserole
directions: Grate 1/2 of cabbage and put in bottom of large casserole. In a frying pan, cook ground beef and chopped onion until the redness is out of meat.
Spread this over the grated cabbage.
Do not mix!
Shred rest of cabbage and spread over ground beef and onion.
Do not mix!
Mix can of tomato soup with can of water, 2 tablespoons of sour cream, salt and pepper and pour over top of the cabbage.
Do not mix! Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: wedding punch
directions: Boil water and sugar 3 minutes.
Cool.
Blend bananas with lemon juice.
Mix orange juice with 1 can water, then mix lemonade with 1 can water.
Blend together banana mixture, orange juice, lemonade, daiquiri mix and pineapple juice.
Freeze in 1/2 gallon containers.
Remove from freezer 1/2 hour before serving and add ginger ale.

title: dried beef cracker spread
directions: Rinse dry beef VERY well and set aside to drain.
Chop scallions in small pieces.
Take softened cream cheese and place in large bowl and break apart.
Chop dried beef (pat dry if still wet).
Mix scallions, chives and dried beef into the cream cheese. Mix well.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix the jello with 2 cups boiling water only; allow to cool. Mix the cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Fold in sour cream. Spread on top of jello.

title: alabama candy
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips and paraffin wax together and press in pan.
Put in freezer and chill.
Cut in small squares and then dip in chocolate chips and paraffin wax that has been melted together.

title: country butter
directions: Blend ingredients in a deep bowl.
Whip with mixer.
Pour into containers.
Place in refrigerator to harden.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: pat's cheese and pumpernickel dip
directions: Scoop out pumpernickel bread.
Fill bread with cream cheese filling.
Serve with scooped bread and additional pumpernickel slices.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix together above ingredients including pineapple juice. Pour into "Best Ever Pie Crust" recipe baked shell.

title: hamburger
directions: Get eggs and get pot and put water in pot and put eggs in the water that is in the pot.
Boil for 5 minutes and eat.

title: creamy ham casserole
directions: Melt margarine over low heat in a heavy saucepan. Blend in flour and seasonings. Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly. Remove from heat; stir in milk. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Mix sour cream and mushrooms into sauce.
Line baking dish with cooked cauliflower. Layer diced ham over the cauliflower. Pour the cheese sauce mixture over the ham; cover with toasted bread crumbs. Bake 25 minutes in a 250° oven.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix sugars and flour; add hot water and butter. Cook on top of stove until thick, stirring often. Add nuts and dates, let dissolve slightly. Remove from heat; add vanilla. Stir, pour into dish and cool. Add Cool Whip.

title: cream cheese cut-ups
directions: In a small bowl, mix the cream cheese with a fork until it's creamy.
You may need to add a few drops of milk to make it creamy.
Mix in the cucumbers (or fruit).
Smooth the paste onto two slices of bread and fit them together.
Use your favorite cookie cutters to make fun sandwich shapes.

title: casata
directions: Mix all together
and
cook
on
top of stove, stirring constantly.
Pour in pan or dish.
Sprinkle with colored candy and add cookies on top.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix the apples and sugar and set aside. Mix all ingredients by hand. Put in square pan. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: bologna
directions: Spread pieces of bread on cookie sheet.
Fill with your favorite pizza fillings.
A slice of pork roll, pizza sauce and cheese, or ground beef (fried), pizza sauce and cheese, etc.
Pop in oven and toast until hot.
If you like this bread real toasty, add cheese after bread is toasted, then pop in oven to melt cheese.

title: clams linguini
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil; add lemon juice and pepper.
Stir in clams and juice.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add 3 tablespoons chopped parsley; serve over hot linguini.
One can shrimp and some tiny scallops may be added with clams, if desired.

title: grilled fish with vegetable butter
directions: With mixer, blend soup mix, butter, brandy and ginger.
Turn onto wax paper and shape into an 8 x 2-inch log.
Wrap in plastic wrap on wax paper; chill until firm.

title: italian stuffed shells
directions: Brown chopped onion in 2 tablespoons cooking oil.
Add hamburger and brown until most liquid is evaporated.
While cooling, boil the pasta shells until cooked.
Drain and run cold water over them while in the colander.
Mix the cheeses in with the cooked hamburger, as well as the dried soup.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in water.
Cook sausage and crumble.
Beat eggs and milk and add to grits, cheese and margarine.
Add sausage to top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Delicious hot!

title: white candy
directions: Blend sugar, milk, salt and butter together. Cook until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Add peanut butter and nuts. Spread into 8 x 8 pan and cool.

title: easy condensed lemon pie
directions: Let lemonade thaw slightly.
Mix with Cool Whip and milk. Pour into prepared pie crusts.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Beat sugar, vanilla and margarine with an electric mixer for 10 minutes.
Add eggs and beat until creamy like custard.
Pour into crust.

title: brandy balls
directions: Combine wafer crumbs, confectioners sugar, cocoa powder and nuts.
Stir in brandy and corn syrup.
Add a little water (about 1 1/4 teaspoons) if necessary to form mixture into 3/4-inch balls. Roll in granulated sugar.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: dressing
directions: Blend together well. Pour over combination salad or slaw when ready to serve. Toss.

title: jello popcorn balls
directions: Melt all ingredients together.
Pour over large bowl of popped popcorn.
Form into balls.
Good with candy corn or cinnamon candy added.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients, then add remaining 5 ingredients. Chill for 2 hours. Serve.
This is really good!

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in boiling water until thick.
Mix in other ingredients except paprika.
Put in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 250° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Yields 12 servings.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix soup with water.
Dip chicken in soup mixture; then roll in stuffing mix.
Place in baking dish or pan.
Melt margarine. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: easy wild duck
directions: Put apples and onions in cavity of duck.
Salt and pepper outside.
Cover with breast with 2 slices of bacon and secure with toothpicks.
Line bottom of pan with foil.
Add ducks.
Pour orange juice over ducks.
Cover and bake with vent open at 350° for 3 hours.

title: quick manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti shells as directed. Rinse and drain. Saute beef and garlic; drain. Add cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese, salt and mayo to skillet.
Mix well and stuff manicotti shells with meat mixture.
Arrange in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine spaghetti sauce and oregano and pour over manicotti. Sprinkle over with Parmesan. Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and continue to bake for 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: rolled chicken breasts in wine sauce
directions: Flatten chicken to 1/4-inch thick.
Place ham slice and cheese strip
on
each.
Tuck
in	sides
and roll up.
Skewer securely. Coat in the 1/4 cup flour and brown in butter.
Put chicken in
9 x 13-inch baking pan.
In same skillet, combine 1/2
water, bouillon,
mushrooms
and
wine.
Heat
and
pour mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours. Transfer chicken
to warm platter.
Blend 2 tablespoons flour with 1/2
cup cold
water.
Add to gravy in baking pan.	Cook and
stir	until thickened.	Pour a little gravy over chicken, garnish
with toasted almonds.
Pass remaining gravy.
Serves 6.

title: yorkshire pudding(to be served with roast beef.)
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Ingredients should be mixed very smooth, about the consistency of cream. Bake in two shallow pans which have been greased with drippings from the roast.
Send to the table hot to be served with roast beef.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cream and water.
Pour cherry pie filling in casserole dish.
Pour flour mixture over top of fruit.
Slice butter and place on top.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili
directions: Saute garlic and onions until lightly colored in oil (on high temperature). Add all the vegetables (with exception of corn and beans). Add oregano, bay leaves, chili powder and cumin. Stir to blend well. Add the crushed tomatoes, broth, water if necessary, and salt and pepper to taste. Add the red pepper flakes. Bring to boil and cook, stirring often for about 20 minutes. Add the beans and corn and cook 10 minutes longer. Serve in bowls and garnish with sour cream, cheese or lime wedges, if desired. Makes about 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheddar potato casserole
directions: Boil the potatoes until tender, then peel and grate.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Put in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: elsie's special spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Use as a spread for crackers or sandwiches.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well together and pour into pie crust. Bake at 300° until done.

title: float soap
directions: Arrange the cookie cutters on waxed paper.
Measure the soap flakes into a heavy bowl and add the boiling water.
Stir until the soap dissolves and add the food coloring and scented oil, if you have it.
Beat the mixture with an eggbeater until it is smooth and satiny. Fill the cookie cutters and allow the soap to dry until it is firm to the touch.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine. Next layer is chocolate chips, then layer on that the butterscotch chips.
Add the pecans next.
Pour the Eagle Brand milk over the top.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Allow to cool; cut into bars.

title: pineapple and lime salad
directions: Drain pineapple; put juice in a cup and add enough water to make 1 cup.
Bring water and juice to a boil.
Pour in medium size bowl.
Add Jell-O; stir until dissolved.
Set aside in refrigerator until syrupy.

title: strawberry smoothie
directions: Wash strawberries and remove steams and leaves.
Slice strawberries; put all ingredients in a blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 cups.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Cover and let set 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Combine pork and beans, mustard, catsup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Fry meat until brown; stir meat into bean mixture.
Place in 2-quart baking dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, combine chocolate chips and butter.
Cook and stir over low heat until melted and smooth. Add condensed milk.
Mix well.
Spoon flour, nuts, chocolate mix and vanilla in a medium bowl.
Shape 1 tablespoon full of dough around each kiss, covering completely.
Place 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Do not overbake. Remove and cool.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in bowl.
Add salt, sugar and flour. (If sticky, add flour; if dry, add water.)
Make 8 balls from dough.
Roll into long strips and shape into pretzels.
Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with kosher salt.
Bake at 425° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Blend well with mixer.
Pour immediately into an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 450° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: cherry waldorf jello
directions: In medium bowl, dissolve Jell-O with boiling water.
Add cold water and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in apples, celery and pecans.
Pour into lightly oiled 6-cup mold or 9-inch square baking pan.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: apple torte
directions: Sift dry ingredients together and set aside.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Fold in dry ingredients, apples and nuts.
Turn into well-greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve with ice cream.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Bring water to a boil. Stir in rice and salt. Cover.
Simmer until all water is absorbed.
Add milk and boil gently, stirring occasionally until thickens slightly, about 5 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except Doritos chips and cheese. Cover the bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish with 1 cup Doritos chips.
Layer in order: 1/2 chicken mixture and 1/3 of cheese.
Repeat, ending with Doritos, topped with cheese. Refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: orange pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add orange juice, beat and then add vanilla.
Add baking soda to flour.
Gradually beat in flour and beat well. Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: reese's peanut butter cups(easy, no baking)
directions: Melt margarine.
Add and mix peanut butter, powdered sugar and graham cracker crumbs in a large mixing bowl.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost with melted milk chocolate chips.

title: unnamed recipe
directions: Brown ground meat and onions; when well done, add chopped eggs, raisins and chopped olives, bouillon (1 cup) or hot water and let simmer for approximately 1/2 hour.
Most liquid will be absorbed.
Transfer to greased casserole; cover with mashed potatoes and bake in medium oven (350°) for half hour.
You can brush top of potatoes with beaten egg yolk to get a golden color.

title: light peach shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 9-inch square baking pan.
In medium bowl, combine 2 tablespoons sugar, peaches and lemon juice; set aside.
In another medium bowl, stir together baking mix, remaining 4 tablespoons sugar, milk and margarine until blended. Pour batter into 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Cool cake on wire rack.
To serve, cut cake into squares; top each with 1/4 cup peach mixture.
Makes 8 servings (240 calories and 9 g fat per serving).

title: karen's stove-top punch(version of "perky punch")
directions: Place liquids in pan on the stove.
Tie spices in a bag of cheesecloth; add to liquid.
Simmer for about an hour.
Or do as I do and use a crock-pot.
The punch stays hot as long as needed and the house smells wonderful!

title: spiced beef sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Refrigerate 1 day.
Take out and mix thoroughly with hands for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate another day.
Take out and mix in same fashion. Refrigerate and mix once again.
Form meat mixture into 5 rolls. Place on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 hours at 150°.

title: fig preserves
directions: To increase recipe, just maintain ratio.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Melt Velveeta cheese with tomatoes in the microwave.
Stir in sausage.
Excellent with nachos.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat together first four ingredients.
Add zucchini, walnuts and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes (check on it before then) in Bundt cake pan.
Frost with glaze.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, mix together all the ingredients.
Form the mixture into meatballs.
Place on a cookie sheet with nonstick vegetable spray and bake 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Add to your favorite sauce and spaghetti.

title: mexican lasagna with black beans and corn
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Spray a 13 x 9 pan with cooking oil; set aside. Stack tortillas on cutting board and slice through them lengthwise into 3 strips. Set aside. Pour corn and black beans in a colander; rinse with warm tap water and set aside to drain.

title: chicken-n-dumplings(southern style)
directions: Cook chicken by boiling; cook until meat comes off the bones. Take meat off of bones and put back into the chicken stock.
Mix in
large bowl the flour, salt, pepper and parsley.
Cut in butter, then add water to make dough.
Roll out and cut into squares.
Drop into boiling water with chicken pieces.
Stir well until thick.

title: karo strawberry preserves
directions: Put Karo in bottom of pan to heat.
Boil until it spins a thread.
Add 2 cups of berries.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add 2 cups of berries and sugar.
Boil 20 minutes.
Set aside.
Skim, cool and let stand 24 hours or overnight.
Put in jars.
Cover with paraffin and seal.

title: kentucky corn pudding(serves 6)
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together and add salt, sugar and margarine.
Beat eggs with milk; add to mixture and mix well. Stir in drained whole corn.
Sprinkle paprika over top of casserole.
Bake in greased casserole dish in a preheated oven at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in casserole dish.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and salt slowly.
Add oil and mix in blender or by eggbeater.
Pour over veggies and mix thoroughly. Refrigerate overnight.
Stir several times before serving.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Melt cheese and soup in double boiler; completely cool. Mix in soft gelatin; fold in mayonnaise and other ingredients. Place in oiled mold and refrigerate.

title: mom's meat loaf(even kids love it!)
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spread in ungreased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch. Cook, uncovered, in 350° oven until done, about 1 1/2 hours. This is a great meal to freeze.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Mix water, butter, Crisco, and cocoa together and place in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Take off stove.
Add sugar, buttermilk, flour and eggs.
Mix with a spoon.
Pour into a greased and floured shallow baking pan (10 x 15).
Bake at 350° for about 25 or 30 minutes or until done.

title: easy pastry
directions: Roll out dough in a long rectangle.
Spoon pie filling over long half.
Dot with butter.
Fold over dough; pinch closed.
Dot top with butter.
Cut air slits.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Glaze.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix jello in water until dissolved.
Add drained pineapple, pecans and strawberries.
Pour half of mixture in casserole or mold.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours or until firm.

title: cheese - bacon puffs
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread thickly on crackers. Broil until bubbly and slightly brown.

title: apple salad
directions: Dissolve red hots and jello in hot water.
Add applesauce. Pour 1/2 into mold and chill.
Blend cheese and pineapple into soft paste.
Spread over chilled jello.
Pour rest of liquid jello over and chill.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, soup, onion, celery, water chestnuts and Miracle Whip well.
Pour into baking dish.
Melt margarine and add cracker crumbs.
Spoon over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into tiny balls (bite size).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: deviled dip
directions: With electric beater, thoroughly combine cheese spread, deviled ham, parsley, onion and seasonings. Chill. Makes about 1 1/3 cups. Serve with assorted crackers and potato chips.

title: ornamental frosting
directions: Mix up and beat ingredients until sharp enough to hold a line when cut with a knife.

title: oatmeal raisin muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Stir in oats. Mix in oil, egg and milk (just until ingredients are wet; batter will be lumpy). Add raisins. Fill greased muffin tins about 2/3 full. Bake in preheated 425° oven for about 15 minutes or until muffin tops are lightly browned.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Mix and pour over the other mix.
Turn in pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: In large skillet or wok, heat olive oil.
Add all the vegetables; cook until almost done.
Add sugar; toss.
Add soy sauce; toss.
Vegetables should be done by now.
To serve, place on platter.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: deviled crab cakes(makes 6 to 8 cakes)
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter; saute until tender the celery, onions, garlic and dry spices.
In a large bowl, combine crabmeat (carefully remove all shell particles), bread crumbs, eggs, mustard and Tabasco sauce.
Mix well.
Turn up skillet and add crab mixture; stir until egg starts to cook and remove from heat.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: green bean medley
directions: In a large pot, bring 4 cups of water to boil.
Stir in the oil.
Add still frozen green beans.
Cook on high until water starts boiling again.
While waiting, peel and cut the other vegetables into small chunks.
Add these to the beans.
Turn the heat to low and put the lid on the pot.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until all vegetables are tender-crisp when pierced with a fork.
Do not overcook.
Serves 6 to 8 generously.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook squash and onions in small amount of chicken broth. Combine ingredients and pour into a greased 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add chips immediately before serving.

title: meat and macaroni casserole with italian vegetables
directions: Prepare macaroni as directed and drain.
Spoon into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Keep warm.
Over medium heat in a 12-inch skillet, saute cut up green peppers, onions and mushrooms, stirring until vegetables are tender.
Spoon mixture into baking dish with macaroni, keeping about 1/3 cup for garnish.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Fold in condensed milk, peanut butter and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill until firm.
Spread top with chocolate fudge sauce.
Chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a boil.
Add peanut butter and Special K. Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Blend and cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs; beat after each egg is added.
Add zucchini and mix.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together; add to zucchini mixture and beat well.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Bake in a 9 x 15-inch or 11 x 17-inch pan at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Cool.

title: bar cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt. In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs until light and fluffy. Gradually add brown sugar, oil and vanilla. Dissolve coffee crystals in cold water.
Gradually stir into egg mixture. Add dry ingredients. Beat until well combined.
Pour batter into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Sprinkle chocolate pieces and nuts evenly on top. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool slightly.
Drizzle with Coffee Glaze.

title: orange candy balls
directions: Mix together; refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours.
Roll in balls and then in sugar.

title: horseradish relish
directions: Mix all together.
Used for shrimp or lobster dip.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for one hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck in a deep pan. Drain off any excess water or fat.
Stir in the Chili-O mix. Add the tomato sauce or juice. Add the kidney beans and bring to a boil, stirring frequently. Reduce heat to simmer and cover with lid.
Cook for about 15 minutes. Serve with crackers.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the shortening and eggs together.
Add sugar and milk. Beat for 1 minute, then add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well for 2 more minutes.
Bake in a well-greased Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: watergate salad(pistachio)
directions: Mix pudding mix in pineapple. Stir in marshmallows and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine soup, margarine, onion, cheese, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Break up potatoes with fork.
Add to soup mixture; mix gently.
Spoon into 12 x 12-inch baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
In a small bowl, toss 1/2 cup chocolate chips with flour to coat; stir into cheese mixture. Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup chips evenly over top.
Bake 55 minutes or until center springs back when touched lightly.
Allow cheese cake to cool in oven with door slightly open.
Chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and brown.
Remove from pan.
Add vinegar, water and sugar to bacon drippings.
Heat to a boil. Remove from pan from heat and slowly add egg.
Stir until slightly thickened.
Serve warm.
May be used on any salad greens.

title: jude's fluff
directions: Mix pineapple and Jell-O in saucepan.
Bring to full boil and remove from heat.
Cool in refrigerator.
When cool, fold in cottage cheese, marshmallows, walnuts, apples and Cool Whip. Return to refrigerator and cool completely.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Beat egg and add to milk, vanilla and peanut butter.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Shape dough into balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes on greased cookie sheet. Top with candy kisses as soon as they come out of oven.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: easy chicken noodle casserole
directions: Prepare noodles as directed on package.
Cook chicken breasts in microwave until done.
Cut up chicken into bite-size pieces and add to noodles.
Add frozen vegetables and mix well.
Bake additional 30 minutes until vegetables are done.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-low heat in hot oil, stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover pan, cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, approximately 20 minutes total time.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: angel cake
directions: Fill ice cream cones with any kind of cake mix 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes on cookie sheet.
Cool and frost with thin frosting, letting it dribble over sides.

title: mabu tofu and rice
directions: Cut tofu into 1/2-inch chunks and drain on towels.
In a small bowl, pour 1 cup boiling water over mushrooms; let stand until soft, 15 to 20 minutes.
Lift out mushrooms; discard stems. Thinly slice caps.
Return to water.
Thinly slice the green onions, keeping white and green parts separate.
Crumble meat into a 10 to 12-inch frying pan over medium-high heat.
Add white part of onions. stir often until meat is browned. Add ginger, pepper, sugar, soy, Sake, mushrooms with their liquid and cornstarch mixture.
Stir until boiling. Add tofu. Simmer until hot, about 5 minutes.
Spoon mixture onto rice and top with green part of onions. Serves 4.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion and bell pepper (chopped).
Heat soups in saucepan and add to ground beef.
Place in casserole dish.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until Tater Tots are brown.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and flour.
Add pineapple.
Push bread into mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Or microwave covered about 12 minutes.

title: breakfast strata
directions: In a large skillet, brown sausage and drain.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sausage and rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: never fail donuts
directions: Mix milk, sugar and salt.
Add yeast.
Stir in eggs and shortening.
Add flour and knead to make soft dough.
Let rise, then on lightly floured board, roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut out donuts.
Let rise, fry and then glaze.

title: molasses icebox cookies
directions: Mix molasses, soda and hot water, salt, melted shortening and lemon.
Then add sugar, cream of tartar, ginger and flour to make a firm dough.
Chill in refrigerator, roll and cut.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Rinse rice well in warm water.
Cook in water for 45 to 60 minutes.
Rice should be opened up, soft and fluffy.
Drain.
Set aside to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients in order given.
Add cooled rice.
Chill.
Makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: quickie meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef with ingredients.
Retain 1/2 can of tomato sauce.
Put ground beef mixture into bread pan.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
(Meat should not be pink when cut open.)

title: 10 bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
Place in large kettle; cover with water and add 2 tablespoons salt.
Soak overnight.
In the morning, drain and add quart of water, ham or pork hock and bring to boil.
Simmer slowly 2 1/2 or 3 hours.
May have to add more water.
To this, add onion, tomatoes, red pepper chili powder, lemon juice and salt.
Simmer another 30 minutes.
Good with corn bread.

title: party pizza
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread on party rye bread and sprinkle top with Bac*Os.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks until light; add 1/4 cup sugar and beat thoroughly. Scald milk and stir slowly into yolks; cook slowly over low heat until mixture coats a metal spoon, stirring constantly. Chill.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa and milk in a saucepan for 2 minutes after it starts boiling.
Add oats, butter, vanilla and salt.
Stir and drop onto waxed paper.
Refrigerate.

title: butter crunch
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over low heat, melt butter.
Add sugar and stir until blended.
Return to low heat and cook until it bubbles, stirring rapidly and constantly.
Add the water and syrup and mix well.
Put in thermometer.
Stirring frequently, cook until 290° (brittle stage) 15 or 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup chopped nuts over surface and quickly mix in.
Do not beat. Pour on greased cookie sheet.
Spread thin.
Cool; loosen 2 or 3 times until cold.
Spread softened chocolate (1/2) over surface and top with 1/2 the finely chopped nuts.
Turn over and repeat.
Break into pieces when chocolate is set.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: Simmer berries in 1 quart of water.
Add sugar to taste.
Add butter and dumplings of your choice and simmer until done.

title: toast sticks
directions: Working with about 6
slices at a time, remove the crust from the bread and slice it in 1/2-inch strips.
Melt butter and season it to taste with the other ingredients.
Pour half of this mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 14-inch baking pan.
Arrange bread in rows, close together.
Pour remaining butter mixture on top evenly. Bake at 200° until brown, about 45 minutes.

title: breakfast in a glass
directions: Slice bananas into blender.
Add all remaining ingredients and whir in blender.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: In the large Tupperware bowl, melt margarine 1 to 2 minutes in microwave (on High).
Add marshmallows; stir.
Put back in microwave 1 to 2 minutes on High; stir.
Then put back in microwave 1 to 2 minutes on High; stir.
If everything is melted, stir in Rice Krispies and put onto a greased jelly roll pan.
Let cool; cut and enjoy.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into crusts.
Let set in refrigerator for 4 hours before serving.

title: baked vidalia onion
directions: Peel onion and cut core out.
Put beef bouillon cube in center.
Pat with a tiny bit of butter.
Put in microwave for 15 minutes.

title: hungarian paprikas(drop noodles)
directions: Beat eggs and water together.
Add flour to which baking powder has been added.
Beat well, dough should not be runny. Drop noodles from a spoon (small amount of dough) into 2 1/2 quarts of boiling water with 3 tablespoons salt.
Cook for 10 minutes. Drain.
Rinse in warm water.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: mom's blueberry cake(this is a very old recipe.)
directions: Cream egg, sugar, oleo and milk.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: margaret's spoon bread
directions: Beat
all
ingredients together well, adding sour cream last. Bake
at
450° for about 20 minutes in a buttered, deep casserole, about 2 1/2 quarts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients and set aside.
Combine oil and next five ingredients, whisking until dressing homogenizes.
Pour over vegetables and toss to coat well.
With a slotted spoon, mound on Boston lettuce or curly endive.
Garnish with chopped pimento.
This also looks pretty in a crystal bowl with the pimento mixed into the salad.

title: chicken soup
directions: Place chicken, skin side down, in pressure cooker.
Sprinkle seasoned salt over chicken.
Put vegetables on top.
Pour water over all.
Cook at 10 pounds of pressure for 20 minutes.

title: shepherd's or cottage pie
directions: For pie, gently saute ground meat in heavy skillet, breaking into small pieces.
Cook until lightly browned.
Drain.
Add onion and saute until soft, but not browned.
Add mushrooms and saute until heated through.
Add mixed vegetables, Italian seasoning, parsley and sugar.
Stir gently.
Add broth.
Simmer until vegetables are done.
In small bowl, blend flour and butter. Gradually add to ground meat mixture, stirring gently.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Transfer to baking dish.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef and onions and drain.
Add remaining ingredients except noodles.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Serve beef mixture over noodles or add noodles to beef mixture.

title: chow mein noodle clusters
directions: Melt chips over hot water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop onto wax paper.
Chill until set.
Keep refrigerated.
This can be served as candy.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
