Mix nuts and coconut and spread on bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to box directions, then pour over nut/coconut mixture.
Blend softened margarine, cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
No need for frosting.

title: navy hamburger helper
directions: Chop onion.
Cook hamburger; remove all grease.
Add beans, garlic powder, onion and red and black pepper.
Simmer about an hour or until onion is tender.
Serve over steamed rice (optional).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain.
Mix rest of ingredients in large casserole dish.
Add beef.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all together.
Chill until serving time.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Add all ingredients, except paprika and cheese.
Pour into greased, shallow, glass casserole. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° until bubbly. This may be made the night before, refrigerated and baked in the morning.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of large casserole.
Mix together sugar, egg, flour, vanilla and milk.
Pour over butter in dish. Add peaches.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: raisin scones(sugar-free)
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Mix in raisins, then mix in buttermilk with fork.
Gather dough into ball and knead on lightly floured board about 2 minutes.
Roll or pat dough out 3/4-inch thick.
With sharp knife, cut into 3-inch triangles.
Space apart on greased baking sheets. Bake in a preheated 425° oven about 15 minutes or until nicely browned.
Serve warm with butter or jam.
Makes about 1 dozen scones.

title: canadian bacon sandwiches
directions: Mix butter, onion, poppy seed and mustard well and spread on buns.
Top each
bun with Canadian bacon and slice of cheese. Wrap or cover with foil and bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: holy smoke
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup pecans and softened butter.
Flour your hand; then spread mixture out in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven until crust is light brown.
Cool.

title: chicken tender's soup
directions: Put all ingredients in large pot and bring to rolling boil. Turn heat down to medium; cover and cook until meat is done and vegetables are tender.

title: hello dolly cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 2 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle into pan a layer each of graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips and pecans.
Pour condensed milk over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: parmesan pepper dressing
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients together and whip in mayonnaise.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs for about 1/2 hour to 45 minutes. (Hint: They are done when you stick fork in easily and potato is somewhat firm.)
Let cool entirely.
Dice potatoes and eggs in a large bowl.
Add mayo, relish, mustard, parsley flakes, salt, pepper and celery.
Mix well.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: Mix together with dill pickle juice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine wafers and melted margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Slice bananas; spread over wafer mix.
Mix milk and lemon juice.
Pour over bananas, then spread.
Drain pineapple; spread over bananas.
Top with whipped topping. Sprinkle with coconut, cherries and walnuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat sweet potatoes, margarine, eggs, cinnamon, cornstarch, milk and sugar with mixer.
Pour into 8 x 10-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Add flour, coconut, oatmeal, soda and salt. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Grease tube or Bundt pan and line with wax paper, also greased.
Bake in slow oven (300°) for 1 1/2 hours.
Wrap cake in wax paper when cool and enjoy.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix
the
yeast
with
the 2 cups of water and allow to soften and
work.
Melt
the margarine and sugar together and when sufficiently
cool,
add
the
beaten
egg and the yeast mixture to
it.
Gradually stir in the flour.
Mix thoroughly and refrigerate at least 3 to 4 hours.
Spoon the batter into greased muffin
tins.
Bake
at
for
20 to 25 minutes. Makes
18 to 24 rolls.
Batter will keep up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat sugar, molasses, vegetable oil, eggs and salt together. Add remaining ingredients and mix just until all ingredients are moist.
Bake in lightly oiled loaf pan for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Let cool 1/2 hour before removing from pan or bake in 2 pans and cook for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and oleo and bring to boil.
Boil 7 minutes; remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter; mix well.
Add nuts and pour on greased cookie sheet or square pan. Cool.

title: buttery garlic squares
directions: Stir together biscuit mix and milk just until moistened. Spread the mixture in a greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
With the end of a spoon, make indentations in the dough about 1-inch apart. Melt butter or margarine.
Stir in garlic and onions.
Drizzle butter mixture over dough.
Bake until top is browned at 350°, about 35 minutes.
Cool slightly, then cut into squares and serve warm.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix the cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in strawberries.
Add nuts and bananas.
Drain pineapple well and add.
Fold in whipped topping.
Freeze in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let sit out 1 hour before serving.

title: original girl scout cookie recipe(1928)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder in another bowl.
Add flour mixture to butter and sugar mixture.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Mix well. Chill dough for 1 hour.
Take out of the refrigerator and roll out very thin on a floured surface using a rolling pin.
Cut with a cookie cutter and put on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle sugar on baked cookies.
Yields 6 to 7 dozen cookies.

title: macaroni and cheese for 25
directions: Cook macaroni in large pot of salted water until tender. Drain.
Meanwhile in heavy pot, melt butter.
Add flour and stir for 2 minutes.
Stir in mustard.
Slowly add milk.
Cook, stirring frequently, until thickened.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add optional ham or frankfurters, cut into bite-sized pieces.
Pour into baking pan sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all together and put in a greased casserole.
Cover.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking in a 350° oven.
Bake 1 hour.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Do not cover.

title: cool and easy pie
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl at least 2 minutes until completely dissolved. Mix cold water and ice to measure 1 cup. Add to gelatin, stirring until ice is melted. Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth. Refrigerate 15 to 20 minutes or until mixture is thick and will mound. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: peanut butter cookie cups
directions: Prepare cookie mix according to package directions.
Roll the dough into 1 inch balls.
Place in greased miniature muffin cups. Press dough evenly onto bottom and up sides of each cup.
Bake at 350° for 11 - 13 minutes or till set.
Immediately place a peanut butter cup in each cup; press down gently.
Cool for 10 minutes. Carefully remove from pans.
Yield 3 dozen.

title: pumpkin dump cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and put in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry yellow cake mix on top. Pour melted butter over cake mix.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix and bake at 350°.

title: chicken shish kabobs
directions: Cut chicken and veggies into chunks.
Put in dish and marinate with dressing for 2 hours.
Put on skewers, alternating veggies and chicken.
Barbecue approximately 10 minutes on each side.

title: banana cake
directions: Beat sugar and shortening together until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add banana and vanilla to first mixture, then alternate the sour milk with the flour.
Beat well and put into two 8-inch floured and greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice with Caramel Icing.

title: italian oven-fried potatoes
directions: In a 10 x 15-inch pan, mix potatoes with oil.
Bake in a 475° oven until they are a rich brown, 35 to 45 minutes.
Do not disturb until potatoes begin to brown, then use a wide spatula to turn pieces over several times.

title: spice cake
directions: In a pan, add raisins, all the spices, Crisco and 2 cups boiling water.
Mix everything together; boil for 5 minutes.
Let stand overnight.
Add the baking soda to the 1 cup boiling water; stir well.
Let cool.

title: crock-pot sauerbraten(cook while you work)
directions: Combine beef, water, vinegar, onion, lemon, cloves, bay leaves, pepper, salt and sugar and refrigerate meat with marinade for 24 to 36 hours.
Remove meat, put in crock-pot with one cup marinade. Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Remove meat; strain juices and return to crock-pot.
Put on high, stir in gingersnaps and cook covered 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour over meat.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies no. 2
directions: In large bowl, combine sugars, margarine, peanut butter, egg and vanilla;
mix
well.
In medium bowl, mix flour, baking powder,
soda and salt; stir into peanut butter mixture, mixing until blended.
Cover dough; refrigerate 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly
grease
several
large baking sheets.
With hands, roll
level	tablespoons
of
dough in 1 1/4 inch balls. Place
balls
inches
apart
on prepared baking sheets.	Dip tines
of
fork
into
flour or sugar; flatten dough crisscross style.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, or until slightly brown.
Yield: 3 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli and drain.
Melt the butter.
Mix broccoli and Velveeta cheese together. Crumble the Ritz crackers and sprinkle over top of the broccoli and cheese.
Cover the casserole with the melted butter. Cook at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned coffee cake
directions: Mix all together, adding raisins last.
Bake in moderate oven in loaf pan.

title: burgundy beef
directions: Place onion wedges in bottom of crock-pot.
Cut steak into 2-inch pieces.
Place on top of onion.
Mix golden cream of mushroom soup with 1/4 soup can of Burgundy.
Pour over meat. Sprinkle in 1/4 teaspoon of tarragon.
Cook on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Slice mushrooms and add to pot.
Cook 30 minutes longer. Serve over egg noodles.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: In blender, put in boiling water, margarine, sugar and powdered milk; blend.
Keep scraping sides as needed until blended.
Set in refrigerator to thicken (1 1/3 cups equals 1 can).

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Add flour, nuts and extract.
Roll in cocoon shape and place on greased cookie sheet.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven until light brown.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Cook meat and onions in skillet with seasonings until done. Add tomato sauce and simmer about 5 minutes longer.
Then, add to spaghetti (which has been cooked according to the package directions).

title: yummie candy balls
directions: Melt and make into balls; the graham cracker crumbs, coconut, powdered sugar, peanut butter and butter.
Make a dip of the paraffin and chocolate chips using a double boiler.
Dip balls into the mixture and place on waxed paper.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Place shrimp in boiling water to cover; cook 5 minutes.
Cool shrimp.
Peel and devein shrimp; chop.
Combine remaining ingredients except celery to make salad dressing; mix well.
Add shrimp and celery to salad dressing.
Refrigerate until served. Yield:
4 servings.
Each Serving:
1/3 cup.

title: pancake in oven
directions: Beat flour, milk and egg together.
Melt butter in 6-inch cast-iron skillet.
Pour in batter.
Do not mix.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Serves 1.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake mix according to directions, adding 1/2 cup pecans. Bake in 2 pans. Let cool. Slice cakes and make 4 layers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Add flour and baking soda.
Then add bananas.
Mix together and put in 2 loaf pans. Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Crumble 1/4 of cake in bowl. Spread 1/2 blueberry pie filling over cake.
Cover with 1/2 container of Cool Whip.
Crumble 1/4 of cake in bowl.
Spread 1/2 can cherry pie filling over cake, 1/2 container of Cool Whip. Crumble 1/4 cake.
Spread rest of blueberry pie filling, 1/2 container of Cool Whip.
Slice bananas over Cool Whip.
Spread drained pineapple over bananas.
Crumble 1/4 of cake.
Spread rest of cherry pie filling, rest of Cool Whip, coconut, top with pecans.

title: congo bars
directions: Beat eggs, butter and brown sugar; mix well.
Add vanilla and all dry ingredients.
Then mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Grease pan, then put dough into pan and cook on high for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: low cholesterol, low-fat impossible pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Mix well.
Pour batter into deep dish pie plate or quiche dish.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes or until custard sets.
(Because this pie is reluctant to brown on the bottom, place on lowest rack in oven.) Yields 1 pie.
One-tenth of pie contains 154 calories with 30% from fat.

title: fruit delight
directions: Bring to boil the vanilla pudding mix, tapioca mix, gelatin and water; cool in refrigerator.
Add strawberries and Cool Whip.

title: hawaiian yams
directions: Slice yams and place into buttered 2-quart dish.
Slice banana on top of yams.
Pour juice on top.
Sprinkle top with salt, nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 with 202 calories per serving.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In small bowl, blend milk, peanut butter, honey or Karo and cracker crumbs.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in coating. Chill.
Makes 24.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls and then with a rolling pin, roll into thin rounds.
Bake on lightly greased cast-iron griddle.
Bake both sides.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Start with first ingredient and layer in serving dish.
Spread layer of refried beans to cover bottom of dish as first layer. Then repeat process with each additional layer.
Garnish with green chiles and black olives, and refrigerate for several hours prior to serving.
Serve with tortilla chips and salsa.

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla until creamy. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture and blend well.
Stir in oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Can add nuts, raisins or chocolate chips.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Brown beef slowly, breaking with fork until very fine.
Add water, onion, garlic, tomato sauce, chili powder, cumin and salt and simmer over low heat about 10 minutes or until mixture is well blended.
Serve over hot dogs.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Combine sugar, salt, and syrup.
Add milk; bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and butter (to taste).
Let cool to lukewarm. Add vanilla; beat until thick.
Pour in pan and cut.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream the eggs and sugar.
Add the oil, carrots, raisins and nuts.
Sift together the dry ingredients and combine everything. Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: curried rice salad
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni and
let cool. Add remaining ingredients. Mix all and chill.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients except salad dressing and Fritos, toss and chill.
Just before serving, add salad dressing and Fritos and toss.
Quantity of ingredients depends upon taste and number of people being served.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: banana split pie # 1
directions: Make first layer of graham cracker crumbs and second layer of banana slices.
Then mix ReaLemon with condensed milk and pour over bananas.
Spread crushed pineapple over preceding mixture. Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Mix pecans and coconut and sprinkle over Cool Whip.
Top with cherries.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours before serving.

title: water chestnuts and bacon
directions: Cut bacon strips in 1/3 pieces.
Wrap around each water chestnut and secure with toothpick.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Drain grease.

title: easy cheese fondue
directions: Mix together all but egg whites.
Beat whites until stiff and fold gently into mixture.
Pour into heated and buttered casserole.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli. Combine celery, soups, milk and sauce. Salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1/2 of the cheese and mix.
Add broccoli and stir together.
Place in dish and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
The last 15 minutes, sprinkle with remaining cheese. It's great!

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Make dressing by mixing following ingredients:
oleo, onions, pecans, celery and water.
Put large spoonful on each breast, then roll and put in greased shallow pan.
Put mushroom soup, right from can, over each rolled chicken breast.
Bake at 300° uncovered for 1 hour or more.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: pasta vegetable medley
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and rinse with cold water until completely cool.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl; set aside.
In another bowl, sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to liquid ingredients and stir until just moistened.
Gently fold in carrots, raisins, coconut and apple.

title: wild rice chicken soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saut onion, carrot and celery in butter until tender. Spoon in flour and stir until blended, then add broth gradually. Stir in rice, chicken, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil over medium heat; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Stir in milk. Cook for 3 to 5 minutes more until heated through. Ladle into individual bowls. Garnish with chives and serve. Yields about 1 1/4 cups per serving.

title: good housekeeping brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
In a 3-quart saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate and oleo, stirring frequently.
With wooden spoon beat in sugar and eggs.
Stir in flour, vanilla, salt and nuts.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool, then cut into 16 brownies.

title: strawberry lemon punch
directions: Dissolve lemonade with 4 cans of cold water.
Puree strawberries, one bag at a time, in a blender or food processor. Strain to remove seeds.
Blend with sugar and stir into lemonade. Refrigerate until ready to serve, then stir in club soda and ice. Garnish with fresh strawberries and mint.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant; boil until tender.
Soak bread crumbs in milk. Melt margarine and saute onion and eggplant.
Cut in cheese while mixture is hot.
Add rest of ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Add additional grated cheese over top.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: no knead oatmeal bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes, pushing down batter as it climbs beaters.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Cover and let rise in warm, draft free place for 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake for 40 minutes or until golden brown in 350° oven.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: miniature strawberry cheesecakes
directions: Combine the cream cheese, sugar, lemon, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl and beat at high speed for 5 minutes.
In miniature baking tins or cupcake tins, put 2-inch paper baking cups or cupcake baking cups.
Put a vanilla wafer in the bottom of each. Fill each cup with cream cheese mixture to about half full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cracks appear on each cake.
Cool. Top with strawberry preserves.
Makes 36 miniature cakes or 24 regular cupcakes and can be frozen.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Have everything at room temperature.
Cream the butter.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Cream well after each addition.
If it gets too thick or heavy, thin with a bit of cream. Add flavoring. Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well on high speed after each. Add flour and cream alternately.
Beat on No. 3 speed. Bake in tube pan. Start in cold oven. Bake at 275° to 300° for 1 hour. Don't open oven. At the end of this time, turn cake around and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar with milk.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Quickly add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Combine until mixed well.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan and cool.

title: dad's favorite date bars
directions: Mix flour, oats, sugar and soda.
Add melted butter.
Spread 1/2 mixture in greased pan.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cut artichokes in small pieces.
Mix all ingredients. Microwave 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate raspberry yogurt pie
directions: Stir boiling water with jello in large bowl for 2 minutes then stir in frozen yogurt until melted. Fold in cool whip and fruit. Refrigerate until mixture mounds. Then spoon into crust. Chill 2 hours or until firm. Garnish with shaved chocolate. Store in refrigerate.

title: fruit congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Fold in remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 mixture into dish and let set. Spread sour cream over congealed gelatin and top with remaining mixture.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Add shortening. Mix well. Add dissolved yeast and buttermilk. Work all this together until it makes a soft dough. Cover bowl and place in the refrigerator until ready to use. Take out as dough is needed. Roll into 1/2 inch thickness on floured board and cut. Bake at 400 degrees on a greased shallow pan for 10 to 12 minutes. This dough will keep several weeks in the refrigerator. Yield: about 2 dozen biscuits.

title: best yet banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions on box.
Add sour cream and Eagle Brand condensed milk; stir well.

title: impossible vegetable quiche
directions: Grease pie plate.
Cook frozen broccoli and cauliflower according to directions on box.
Add onion, pepper and cheese. Mix milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Add to vegetable mixture.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: eggless jam cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add jam and mix well.
Add the sifted dry ingredients with the buttermilk.
Stir in the nuts. Bake in greased pan at 350° until cake is done (30 to 40 minutes).

title: banana cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, bananas and milk (add 1 teaspoon baking soda to milk).
Add baking soda, flour and other ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: 24-hour fruit salad
directions: Beat egg well and put in a saucepan.
Stir in lemon juice, sugar and salt, and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat and cool.
Fold in remaining ingredients, except nuts.
Cover and chill overnight.
Just before serving, add nuts.

title: slow cooker dressing
directions: Microwave onion,
celery and parsley in margarine.
Mix white bread, cornbread,
baking
powder
and seasonings.	Pour onion mixture over
bread
mixture.
Pour
broth	over
bread mixture. Add eggs and mix together well.
Pack lightly into a 3 1/2 to 4 1/2
quart slow cooker.
Cover and cook on High for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to
low
and
cook 5 to 6 hours.
(To cook in oven, bake 1 hour at 350°.)

title: cream cheese and tuna dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate and serve as a spread, dip or to stuff cherry tomatoes.

title: wassail(the best)
directions: In large saucepan, heat cider and cinnamon stick to boiling; reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve in punch bowl.
Float orange slices and whole cloves inserted in skin.
Can be served in percolator, hot.

title: easy cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour, milk and vanilla.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
After cake has cooled, top with strawberries and whipped topping.

title: corn casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix rice, corn, soups and 1/2 cup cheese.
Pour in dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup cheese on top and allow to melt.

title: "red eye" gravy
directions: After frying country ham slices, remove ham from skillet.
Pour one cup fresh perked coffee into the ham drippings.
Let simmer for 1 minute, then pour off into a bowl.
The dark liquid that settles to the bottom is "red eye" gravy.
A great topping for fresh hot biscuits or ham.
When serving, dip from the bottom of the bowl.

title: coconut snowballs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine oats, flour and almonds.
In large bowl, beat together butter and 1/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract; mix well.
Stir in oats mixture, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in coconut.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Lightly sift remaining 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar over cookies.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: campfire potatoes
directions: Place the potatoes and onion on a large piece of heavy-duty foil (about 20 x 20 inches).
Dot with butter.
Combine the cheese, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle over potatoes.

title: make a handprint
directions: Put the water and salt in a bowl.
Let salt dissolve.
Add the flour and oil; mix together.
Knead the dough very well.
Put the dough into a pie tin.
Flatten the dough until it reaches the edges.
Press your hand into the dough and make a handprint.
Use a pencil to poke a hole in the top and write your name at the bottom.
Put in the oven and bake at 300° for about 1 hour. Decorate your handprint with paint crayons, glitters or markers. Tie a ribbon through the hole and hang up your handprint.

title: fudge
directions: Bring to boil first five ingredients, then stir for five minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, nuts, and chocolate chips.
Put in refrigerator (or freezer) until set.

title: diabetic brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir all ingredients until blended. Bake in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla and rum extract.

title: banana peanut butter salad
directions: Cut bananas in half crosswise, then lengthwise.
Spread peanut butter between matching halves.
Stick together.
Dip each "sandwiched" half in orange juice (or use lemon juice).
Serve with a small spoonful of mayonnaise over each.

title: mexican black bean tortilla soup
directions: For spice and flavor, add salsa to taste.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble cookies; divide into 3 equal portions.
Using a mixer, blend cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar; set aside.
Mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
In a large bowl, layer 1/3 cookies, 1/2 mixture, 1/3 cookies, 1/2 mixture and 1/3 cookies.
Refrigerate.

title: praline party mix
directions: Stir together chex cereal and pecan halves in 13 x 9 inch pan.
In saucepan, melt butter, brown sugar and praline mix.
Heat until boiling.
Gently cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda.
Stir until foamy.
Pour over cereal and nuts.
Stir to coat well.
Bake at 250 degrees for one hour.
Stir once during baking.
Spread on cookie sheet to cool.

title: quilter's brownies
directions: Mix butter, cocoa, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and nuts; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 24 minutes.

title: orange pineapple ice cream
directions: Mix well.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Add Minute Maid to full line.
Freeze as directed.

title: pork-rice tamale pie(good meat stretcher)
directions: Wash rice through several waters until water is clear, drain. Add gradually to a large quantity of rapidly boiling salted water, never allowing water to stop boiling during the addition.
Boil rapidly, uncovered, until rice is tender, 15 to 20 minutes, then drain.
Combine rice, tomatoes, green olives, seasonings, cooked pork and meat broth.
Pour into well-greased casserole or baking dish and bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes.
Cut small biscuits from biscuit dough, place on top of pork-rice casserole dish, return to oven and bake at 400° until biscuits are done. Serve while hot.

title: granola
directions: Stir together oatmeal, wheat germ and coconut.
Heat oil and honey, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and peanut butter.
Blend well.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Spread on cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 225° for one hour.
Cool.
Break apart and stir in raisins with hands.
Store tightly covered.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash with salt; drain and wash.
Combine all ingredients together; add squash and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and Eagle Brand.
Add evaporated milk. Add vanilla.
Fill with milk to the top of the container.
Makes 4 servings.

title: v. k.'s chicken and cornbread dressing
directions: Wash chicken and season well.
Put in large skillet and bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes.
Wash gizzards and put in 2 quarts of water with green onions, vegetable blend can of chicken soup, salt and pepper.
Boil until tender.
Wash liver and season and fry with a little flour.
Make cornbread and broth from gizzards.
Cut gizzards up fine and add to mixture.
Stir well, pour into roaster pan, add baked chicken parts over top of dressing.
Cover and bake for 15 minutes.
Remove cover and bake until desired color is reached.
Cook in 350° oven.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger; mix in the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, corn flakes, parsley, eggs, soy sauce, black pepper, ketchup and onions.
Form balls.
Arrange in one layer.

title: "old fashion" cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrots and pickle cubes; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon over cabbage mixture; toss gently.
Chill until serving time.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together and chill at least 2 hours before using. Serve with crackers.

title: buttermilk brownie squares
directions: Sift flour and sugar; set aside.
Combine butter, water, shortening and cocoa.
Heat to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients; mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla; stir until blended.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Frost cake while hot.
I use jelly roll pan; makes a very large batch.

title: baked chicken gravy
directions: Dip chicken in milk (1/2 cup).
Roll in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan in oven.
Put chicken in pan, skin side down.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, turn chicken.
Mix soup, 3/4 cup evaporated milk and water.
Pour around chicken.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until tender.
Stir gravy.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans; combine and add green pepper.
Combine sugar, vinegar and salad oil.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour over beans; toss gently.
Chill overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: country salad with herb and walnut dressing
directions: Cook snow peas in large quantity of boiling salted water until crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Drain and rinse under cold water. Drain. Toss lettuce with celery. Arrange in an even layer over the bottom of a straight-sided clear glass salad bowl. Arrange the carrots, zucchini and tomatoes in separate layers over the lettuce-celery mixture. Arrange the snow peas in a fan pattern over the tomatoes. Garnish with mushroom and basil. Cover and refrigerate. Prepare Herb-Walnut Dressing. Just before serving, add the dressing; toss well.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place chicken in Dutch oven or large kettle with enough water to cover.
Add the parsley, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Remove meat from bones and return it to chicken stock.
Add carrots and peas.
Blend in flour to stock and stir constantly over low heat until thickened. In a mixing bowl, combine Bisquick and milk.
Drop by tablespoon onto boiling stew.
Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes and covered 10 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy brunch
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and let stand in the refrigerator overnight.
Pour into lightly oiled 9-inch round cake pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350° (the consistency will be similar to bread pudding when it's done).
Meanwhile fry bacon, drain, crumble and sprinkle on top of mixture for the last 10 minutes that it is in the oven.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Bake chicken at 350° until done. Remove meat from bones and cut into small chunks.
Put into large casserole dish.
Add broccoli spears and cream of chicken soup mixed with 1 soup can of milk.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Cover with foil and bake for about 1 1/2 hours at 350° until broccoli is tender.

title: popovers
directions: You will need 6 (6 ounce) custard cups with nonstick cooking spray.

title: fricasseed squirrel
directions: Sprinkle meat liberally with tenderizer and set aside.
In a medium or large skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain. Salt and pepper pieces of squirrel to taste.
Dredge in flour. Brown quickly in hot bacon fat. Reduce heat and add onion.

Cook until tender, but not brown. Stir in crumbled bacon and chicken broth. Cover and simmer over low heat until the meat is tender (about 1 hour). Serve over a bed of steaming rice. This will serve 3 or 4 persons with normal appetites or 2 young hunters.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a 6 x 10-inch baking dish at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: festive florentine crescents
directions: Combine spinach, Velveeta cubes, bread crumbs and bacon in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until Velveeta cubes melt.

title: spaghetti cheese bake
directions: Brown beef with onion; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, tomato paste and seasonings; simmer.

title: light rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in a large bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt, butter and egg.
Add milk, stirring well.
Add flour; stir well. Cover with a towel and let rise in a warm place until double in bulk.
Punch dough down and turn out on a lightly floured board. Roll and cut rolls.
Place in pan.
Brush lightly with melted margarine.
Let rise until double in bulk (about 45 minutes). Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes about 20 rolls.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Crust:
Mix chocolate cookie crumbs with butter.
Press on bottom and sides to top of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Chill in freezer for 15 minutes.

title: easy strawberry pie
directions: Slice strawberries into baked pie shell.
Boil water, cornstarch and sugar, while stirring, until thick.
Add jello. Pour the mixture over strawberries while hot.
Cool in refrigerator.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with strawberries, if desired.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Beat last three ingredients together and set aside.
This will be the filling. Melt butter on low heat.
Add butterscotch morsels and stir until melted. Remove from heat and add graham crumbs. Mix well.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook rice in boiling water, covered, for 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate (the longer the better).

title: cheese and wiener crescents
directions: Slit wieners to within 1/2 inch of ends.
Insert 3 strips cheese in each slit.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Wrap dough around wieners, being sure to keep it all together.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: green beans
directions: Layer beans in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine other ingredients. Melt and pour over beans; refrigerate overnight.
Cover with bacon and bake 30 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: sour cream blueberry bundt cake
directions: Cream margarine, gradually adding 1 cup sugar.
Beat well. Add eggs 1 at a time, beating after each.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda; gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing until blended.
Stir in vanilla and sour cream.
Spoon half of batter into greased and floured 10 inch bundt pan.
Sprinkle with blueberries.
Combine the 1/2 cup sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Top blueberries with half of sugar mixture.
Add rest of batter, top with remainder of sugar mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45-50 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and let cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O with other ingredients.
Chill well before serving.

title: chicken, mushrooms, artichokes
directions: Cook chicken and break into bite size pieces.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Layer chicken, artichokes and mushrooms.
Heat gravy according to package directions.
Add butter, sherry and cheese. Stir until smooth.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: layered dip
directions: Layer in that order, bottom up.

title: german black forest cherry cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round layer pans.
In chilled bowl, beat cream until stiff. Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Fold eggs and vanilla into whipped cream. Stir together remaining ingredients. Fold gently into cream eggs mixture until blended.
Pour into pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: blender pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend on high till mixed. Pour into buttered and floured pie pan. Bake at 350° for 35-40 min. Will form it's own crust and topping.

title: jello cake
directions: Let set while cake is baking.
Then poke holes in cake and pour jello over.

title: heath coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and flour to make a crumb mixture.
Take out 1/2 cup and set aside for topping.
Beat and mix together egg, soda, vanilla and buttermilk.
Fold into crumb mixture.
Do not beat.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Crush Heath bars.
Sprinkle crushed Heath bars and crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Test for doneness with toothpick.

title: ham and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in a little oil.
Combine rice, can of soup, plus can of water.
Crumble ham and add all ingredients together and put in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover top with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: hot cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: black beans
directions: Place beans, salt, studded onion and garlic in Dutch oven. Simmer 1 hour.
Add thyme and oregano and cook 30 minutes.
Saute onion, pepper and garlic in oil until tender, but not brown.
Add beans with liquid and meat which has been browned.
Add tomatoes. Cook; stir occasionally.
Mash 1 cup bean mixture and return to pan.
Cook until sauce thickens.
Prepare rice.
Place in bowl and top with bean and tomato salsa.
Serve with sour cream and cornbread.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: beef in red wine sauce
directions: Marinate the beef for 2 to 4 hours in red wine.
Remove beef and reserve marinade.

In a large heavy pan, brown beef on all sides, a few pieces at a time, in 2 to 3 tablespoons of oil; set aside. Cut up the onion and carrots. Brown them in the same pan, adding more oil, if necessary. Return the beef to the pan with red wine marinade.
Add bay lef, tomato paste, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and 1/2 teaspoon thyme.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, for about 2 hours or until meat is tender. Remove meat from pan and skim off as much fat as possible from the liquid.

Puree the vegetables with the liquid in a blender, then strain. Reheat the meat with the sauce and cook further, if necessary, to thicken. Serve garnished with lightly sauteed onions or green peppers.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook and cool frozen vegetables.
When cool, add celery, green peppers, onions and kidney beans.
Cook the following:
vinegar, sugar, prepared mustard, salt and cornstarch.
Cook until thick. Let cool and add vegetables.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: snicker salad
directions: Cut Snickers into small pieces and apples into small chunks. Mix into Cool Whip and chill well before serving.
Very easy and delicious!

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, tomato sauce, spaghetti mix, oregano and bay leaf.
Stir well.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook noodles as label directs.
Drain and rinse.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Add soups, taco and enchilada sauces.
Grease large casserole dish.
Place small amount of meat sauce in bottom, then layer tortillas, meat sauce and cheese (3 times).
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry jubilee
directions: Mix all ingredients together; store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Better when chilled overnight.

title: chocolate satin frosting
directions: Melt chocolate in mixing bowl over hot water.
Remove from heat.
With electric mixer, blend in sugar and water.
Beat in egg, butter and vanilla.
Frosting will be thin, so continue beating until proper consistency.

title: deep south sausage and pintos
directions: Fry sausage until brown on all sides.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons of the fat.
Add onion and green pepper; saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to blend.
Simmer 10 minutes and serve hot with cornbread.
Serves 6.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix all together.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 225°.
Stir every 15 minutes and salt with the garlic salt on each stir.

title: david's favorite turkey patties
directions: Combine turkey, yogurt, sage and 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Form into patties.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Coat patties with remaining crumbs and cook, uncovered, until browned on both sides and juices run clear.

title: pineapple cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: olive cherries
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour hot over cherries that have been packed in jars.

title: creole black-eyed peas
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in bacon drippings until tender.
Stir in Ro-Tel, black-eyed peas, salt, bay leaf and 1/2 of crumbled bacon.
Cook over low heat for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add water, if necessary.
Remove bay leaf and sprinkle with remaining crumbled bacon just before serving.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Melt margarine in 3 quart pan.
Add remainder of ingredients in order.
Stir.
Put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares before cooled.
Makes 24 bars.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Add together pineapple and soda.
Let stand while you mix flour, sugar, salt, eggs and walnuts.
Mix with pineapple mixture; blend.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Check with toothpick.

title: pam's party cheese dip - chili con queso
directions: Cook onion and chilies in butter in double boiler. Add milk and cheese gradually. Add spices. Keep warm in chafing dish. Use Doritos, etc. as dippers. Stir well occasionally.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on box.
Mix all ingredients, except broccoli, together; heat until melted and blended.
Mix with broccoli; pour into greased casserole dish.
Cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: marinade
directions: Mix together.
Marinate meat several hours or overnight.

title: lemon angel bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix with lemon filling. Pour into greased jelly roll pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Fill in low casserole with apples, water and cinnamon (can use juice from canned apples instead of water; add with juices to make 1 cup).
Blend rest of ingredients until crumbly with fork. Spread this mixture on top of apples and bake, uncovered, for 1 hour in a 400° oven.

title: date bread
directions: Boil the water in large kettle. Pour boiling water over dates, salt and butter. Stir well and let cool. Mix in flour. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: mexican round steak
directions: Work all the flour you can into steaks.
Melt the Crisco. Cook the steak well on each side.
Add water, tomatoes, onion and green pepper.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook 1 hour.

title: seven-layer bars
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle next five ingredients in order.
Pour milk over all.
Baked at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until top is light brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix milk, poultry season, salt and pepper together.
Roll chicken in mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: 24 hour cabbage slaw
directions: Cut vegetables for slaw and put in large jar.
Mix remaining ingredients in pot; bring to a boil, 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour over slaw.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Beat until smooth and pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: egg custard pie
directions: In blender, beat eggs real good.
Heat milk to boiling point. Add to egg mixture, blending continuously.
Add sugar, flavoring and margarine.
Pour into 9-inch deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife when inserted into pie comes out clean.

title: fruit punch
directions: Chill fruit juices.
Add chilled ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 1 1/2 gallons. Cut 2 oranges in slices and let float in punch.
Serves 50.

title: oriental noodle soup with salmon
directions: Put frozen vegetables and water in a 2-quart saucepan over medium-high heat.
Bring to a boil.

title: church windows
directions: Melt and cool butter and chocolate.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Divide into 2 rolls and wrap in wax paper.
Cool for 24 hours.
Roll in coconut and slice.

title: green chili rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased 7 1/2 x 11-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika to add color.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sift first 4 ingredients together in bowl.
Add 3/4 cup milk; mix well.
Pour on top of butter.
Don't stir!
Add 3 cups fruit layer (if canned use syrup).
Sprinkle 1 cup sugar on top of fruit.
Add sprinkles of cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350°, until brown and crusty, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pear honey
directions: Cook all ingredients together until golden color.
Put in jars and seal.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Stir in nuts, etc.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: hot german potato salad with kielbasa
directions: Boil thinly sliced potatoes until tender.
In skillet, brown onions in margarine until golden.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper, cooking over low heat until bubbly. Remove from heat, stirring in water and vinegar.
Return to heat until boiling and stir for one minute.
Mix in drained potatoes, coating well.
Pour into a large, shallow casserole, topping with diagonal, 2-inch chunks of kielbasa.
Heat in oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: icebox cake
directions: Crush crackers fine.
Work in butter and sugar.
Melt marshmallows in the 1/2 cup milk over boiling water in double boiler until thin.
Grease pan or glass dish with butter.
Line with the cracker crumbs.
Save 1/2 for topping.
Chill overnight in icebox (now days refrigerator).

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: french silk pie
directions: Melt chocolate.
Blend sugar, butter and chocolate.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each, until all eggs are used.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate overnight, then cover with Cool Whip and serve.

title: italian pepper cookies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients; cream shortening and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Put whiskey in milk.
Make small balls and place on greased sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over medium heat.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Stir in sifted flour and dry ingredients. Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in greased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet with sides.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: light wild rice soup
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat until tender.
Stir in rice, gravy and milk.
Reduce heat to low.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in sherry.
Makes 4 cups.

title: beefed-up biscuit casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Simmer while preparing dough by pulling apart each biscuit to make 2 layers.
Press 10 biscuit layers over bottom of ungreased 8-inch baking dish.
Combine 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream and egg; mix well.
Remove meat mixture.
Stir in sour cream mixture; spoon over dough.
Arrange remaining biscuits on top.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over meat mixture and biscuits. Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and bone it.
Mix both soups together with tomatoes and 1/2 of the cheese and onions.
Pour 1/2 of this in casserole dish, then layer 1/2 of the chicken, 1/2 the Doritos and 1/2 the cheese.
Repeat first step again.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: whole wheat sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Rub in margarine; mix in enough water to form a stiff dough.
Roll out mixture, one-third at a time, between sheets of waxed paper to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into sticks, 1 x 3-inches.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° until browned, approximately
8 to 12 minutes.
Watch carefully as outside sticks brown faster than inside ones.
Change position.
When cool, store in airtight container.

title: low-fat hamburger casserole(for crock-pot)
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Place layers of vegetables, then large pieces of celery, green pepper, onion, etc., layer of browned ground beef.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Mix tomato soup with a little water, pour over vegetables and meat.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Stir only a few times during cooking.

title: easy crock-pot chili
directions: Brown ground beef in frying pan or crock-pot.
Drain.
Put browned ground beef in crock-pot and add all other ingredients, stirring to mix.
Cover.
Cook on medium heat (simmer) for 7 to 10 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: orange bread
directions: Sift flour and measure; add baking powder, salt and sugar. Sift again.
Combine egg, orange rind, juice and oil or melted shortening (slightly cooled).
Pour into flour mixture and stir just enough to moisten; do not beat.
Turn into greased loaf pan 9 1/2 x 5 1/2 x 3-inch.
Bake in moderate 350° oven about 1 hour. Remove from pan.
Cool.
Best to wait a day to slice and serve.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Pour in crust and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: black walnut apple bread
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Stir in cereal flakes, walnuts and apple.
Combine egg, brown sugar, buttermilk and oil.
Add flour mixture.
Mix just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Do not beat.
Turn into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes. Remove to rack to cool completely.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: christmas cut-out cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring thoroughly.
Stir flour, baking powder and salt together; blend in.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll cookies 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured board.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 6 to 8 minutes or until cookies are delicate golden color.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: hamburger loaf
directions: Brown hamburger, green pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add 2 cans cheese soup.
Cut French bread down middle and take the insides out of the loaf.
Add bread from middle of loaf to hamburger mixture and heat.
Spoon mixture back into French bread.
Wrap loaf in tinfoil and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until hot.
Heat 1 can cheese soup and pour over individual pieces of loaf as it is served.

title: stew beef
directions: Brown beef in small amount of oil in a large skillet.
Transfer it to a 6-quart Dutch oven.
Cover with water.
Add salt, pepper, onions, potatoes, carrots and soup.
Cover and cook slowly about 1 hour.
Add peas and cook about 15 more minutes.
Serve with hot baked cornbread.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spray a cookie sheet with baking spray.
Press crescent rolls together to form a "crust".
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes; let cool.

title: olive salad
directions: Chop black olives and onion and cut celery into bite size pieces.
I put it all through the 2mm slicer on the food processor.
Mix everything together and leave out for several hours at room temperature, stirring occasionally.
Refrigerate. Keeps a long time.

title: crispy corn bread
directions: Grease 8-inch iron skillet.
Mix all ingredients together. Pour into skillet.
Place in oven and bake at 500° for 20 minutes.
Serves about 6 people.

title: chili eggs(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Beat eggs until lemon yellow.
Add butter and mix well.
Add flour, baking powder, salt, cottage cheese and Jack cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Stir in chilies.
Pour into well-buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish.
Bake in 300° preheated oven 35 minutes or until lightly browned and center is firm.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serve with salsa.

title: company chicken
directions: Make Stove Top stuffing as per directions on package but add shredded carrots to the boiling water.
Place chicken in a greased baking dish.
Top with stuffing.
Mix sour cream and cheese. Spoon on top of stuffing.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar and flour.
Mix well and let rise 30 minutes.
Add second set of ingredients.
Mix. Refrigerate in greased bowl.
Cover.
Shape into rolls.
Put in greased pan.
Let rise in warm place about 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy caramel pecan rolls
directions: Put the sugar, butter, and pudding in a sauce pan.
Cook until well blended. Place 10 frozen rolls in greased bundt pan. Pour half of the sugar mixture and half of the pecans over the rolls.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg and enough milk to make a soft dough, mixing with fork.
Knead lightly, about 20 turns on floured board. Divide in thirds.
Pat out thirds in 3 greased 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 450° about 15 minutes.
Divide berries in half and sweeten to taste.
Put shortcake layers together with berries between and on top.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: upper michigan pasties(miner's lunch pies)
directions: Sift flour into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening and suet until coarse crumbs.
Add just enough water to make soft dough; mix well.
Divide into 4 parts; roll out each part in large circle. Combine meat and vegetables; divide into 4 parts.
Place filling on one side of each pastry circle; salt and pepper to taste.
Fold over filling and seal edges well.
Prick with fork on top to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Lower heat to 350°; bake 15 minutes more, or until browned.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a greased baking pan, 9 x 13 x 2-inch.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "out of this world pie"
directions: In large saucepan, combine cherry pie filling, sugar, undrained pineapple, cornstarch and food coloring.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Cool and add bananas and nuts.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells.
You can use either a regular pie crust or graham cracker crust.
I always like to top off with Cool Whip also.
This is optional.

title: chicken caruso
directions: Ingredients can be varied depending upon number of people to be served.

title: giant chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 2 large cookie sheets.
In large bowl cream butter, shortening and sugars until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix just until combined.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Using a #20 ice cream scoop or 1/4 cup measure, drop scoops of batter 3 inches apart onto cookie sheets.
With floured hand flatten each scoop into 4-inch rounds.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove while centers are slightly soft.
Cool cookies on baking sheet 5 minutes, transfer to wire racks to cool.
Makes about 16 cookies, 300 calories each.

title: bean patties
directions: Mash beans.
Beat egg and add to mashed beans.
Shape into patties and roll in crumbs.
Fry in shortening until brown on both sides.

title: 3-bean baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion; drain off grease.
Mix together the vinegar, brown sugar, ketchup and mustard; pour over meat mixture.
Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Combine beans; do not drain.
Combine with meat mixture.
Bake in uncovered casserole at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or it can be simmered in crock-pot.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Combine soup, milk and pepper.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole arrange alternate layers of potatoes, meat, onion and soup mixture.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: easy barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving size pieces.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon over ribs.
Reduce heat to 350°, cover and bake another hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more or until tender.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Flatten softened cookie dough in pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown, 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese with 1/3 cup sugar.
Spread over cooled cookie dough.
Arrange fruit in circles on cream cheese.
Cook orange juice, 1/3 cup sugar and cornstarch over medium heat until thick.
Spread over fruit.
Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and pour in buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and the cornstarch in a 2-quart saucepan; stir in fruit and water.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Stir remaining ingredients until soft dough forms.
Drop dough by 6 tablespoons onto hot fruit mixture.
Bake until golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Serve with cream, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: buttermilk pies (2)
directions: Mix ingredients until light.
Pour into 2 deep-dish unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325°. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes and butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh orange layer cake
directions: Beat vigorously 2 minutes. Add remaining 1/3 cup liquid and 2 medium size eggs. Beat 2 minutes more.
Pour into two 8-inch round greased pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread
directions: Follow the Bosch basic mixing directions.
Makes 6 loaves.

title: chewy bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix graham cracker crumbs with margarine and press in cake dish.
Spread Eagle Brand milk on top, then cover with coconut.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Press firmly in dish.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; cover and refrigerate until chilled.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crust. Place the other pie crust on top (cut a few slits in top) and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: beef marinade
directions: Mix all and bring to a boil.
Marinate at least 8 hours in refrigerator.
Should be longer.
Use to baste while cooking.

title: butter cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1 egg and 1 stick butter.
Spread over a cookie sheet.
Blend together cream cheese, 1 stick butter, powdered sugar and 2 eggs.
Spread over the first layer.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Combine ham, onion, cheese and dried parsley in bowl. In separate bowl, beat together egg, milk and oil.
Add 2 cups buttermilk baking mix, blending well.
Add ham mixture, stirring until mixed.
Then add remaining 1 cup baking mix, stirring until blended.
Turn dough out onto floured surface.
Knead about 10 times or until dough holds together.
Roll out dough, about 3/4-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Repeat until all dough is used.
Place biscuits on greased baking sheet and brush tops with melted butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake in 425° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Brown steak strips in oil (do not flour).
Add onion soup mix; mix well.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add strips of pepper; cook until tender.
Mix cornstarch with 1/2 cup water; add to mixture.
Stir until thick.
Serve over cooked rice or you can add frozen Chinese vegetables.

title: gooseberry meringue pie
directions: Drain the gooseberries. Add the water to the syrup. Mix the 3/4 cup sugar, flour and salt. Add to the liquid.

Add the egg yolks and melted butter or margarine. Cook until thick. Add the vanilla. Gently fold in gooseberries. Cover pan and cool. When cool, pour into a baked 9-inch pie shell or tart shells. Beat together the 2 egg whites, cream of tartar and 4 tablespoons of sugar until all sugar is dissolved.
(When meringue weeps, you haven't dissolved the sugar.)
Pile meringue lightly on pie (seal to crust to stop shrinking).
Bake at 400° until delicately browned (about 8 minutes).
Cool slowly out of draft.

title: chicken yum-yum
directions: Clean and trim chicken.
Place in baking dish and pour French dressing over chicken.
Use about 1/2 to 3/4 of the bottle.
Plot dollops of apricot preserves by tablespoons on chicken pieces. Sprinkle package of onion soup mix over chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Prepare egg noodles while chicken cooks and pour chicken and sauce over noodles. Preparation time:
10 minutes.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour mixture into pie shell. Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Pie is done whenever knife inserted 1 inch from pie's edge comes out clean.

title: chewies
directions: Melt oleo in oblong pan. Put brown sugar into a bowl and add the melted oleo. Cream the oleo and brown sugar. Blend in other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: blueberry-lemon bread(makes one 8-inch loaf)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Combine first 3 ingredients in small bowl.
Using electric mixer, cream butter with 1 cup sugar in large bowl, until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add lemon peel.
Mix in dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Fold in blueberries (Note:
if using frozen blueberries, thaw and drain). Spoon batter into prepared loaf pan.
Bake until golden brown and toothpick inserted into center comes out clean, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Bring remaining 1/2 cup sugar and lemon juice to boil in small saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Pierce top of hot loaf several times with a toothpick.
Pour hot lemon mixture over loaf in pan.
Cool 30 minutes in pan on rack.
Turn bread out of pan and cool completely on rack.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Sift flour before measuring, then resift with soda and salt. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until light and fluffy.
Add milk and flour, stirring well.
Then add fruits and nuts and blend in mixture.
Chill several hours, then drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven about 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen cookies.
These cookies are very good after they have been frozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and bake in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Preheat oven to 400° and bake 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° or 350° for 10 to 15 minutes,
then reduce to 200° and bake until done by testing.

title: play dough
directions: Mix in a medium pot:
flour, salt and cream of tartar.
Mix water, oil and food coloring and heat.
Add other ingredients after they have been mixed together.
Stir.
Store in airtight can or plastic bag.

title: chocolate nut cake
directions: Cream butter,
Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Beat egg yolks, and
add
to
creamed
mixture.
Sift
dry	ingredients together. Add
to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Mix in vanilla and
nuts.	Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into cake batter. Pour
into a greased and floured tube pan.	Bake at 300° for
30 minutes, then turn up oven to 325° and bake 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Wash and drain berries.
Toss berries with 1/3 cup flour and set aside.
Sift 2 cups flour with the sugar, cream of tartar, soda and salt into a bowl.
Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until the mixture looks like coarse meal.

title: zucchini bar cookie
directions: Mix and bake 40 minutes at 350° in a large cookie sheet with sides.

title: beef jerky
directions: The amount of seasoning depends on how hot you want your jerky. Mix all of the spices and pour over meat.
Marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Set oven temperature at 150°.
Place meat on oven racks.
Cook with oven door propped open about 1-inch. Meat should dehydrate, not cook.

title: sweet and sour dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Serve over tossed salad.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add cheese, onions, salt and butter.
Mix well. Add Jiffy mix and broccoli; stir until well mixed.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until light brown.

title: date nut bread
directions: Cut up dates.
Add soda.
Pour boiling water over dates and let cool.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and date mixture.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder. Add to date mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour or until center is done in 350° oven.
Serve with cream cheese and pineapple or with butter.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, oats or crackers, milk, salt and onion.
Roll into balls and set aside.

title: tammy's sweet potato pie
directions: Beat well with electric mixer.
Pour into two 9-inch pie plates.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour until done.

title: martha washington nutmeg custard pie
directions: Line pan with pastry; flute edge and prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 7 minutes.
Remove pie shell from oven and lower heat to 325°.
Scald milk and cinnamon. Mix eggs with egg yolks, sugar, vanilla, nutmeg and salt.
Strain milk and add to egg mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° until a knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 55 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Serve at room temperature with whipped cream and sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-aid by package directions.
Add pineapple juice and pour into punch bowl.
Cut sherbet into slices, top each slice with a pineapple slice and a cherry.
Add to punch bowl.
Pour ginger ale on top of sherbet when ready to serve.
May use any flavor of Kool-Aid.

title: banana-pineapple cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil; stir until moistened.
Do not beat!
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and chopped bananas.

title: yeast based fasnachts
directions: Scald milk, then add shortening and salt.
Cool milk until it is lukewarm, then add crumbled yeast cake and stir.
Gradually add 2 2/3 cups of the flour, beating batter thoroughly.
Put in warm place and allow to stand until full of bubbles.
Mix sugar and nutmeg; combine with beaten eggs.
Stir into first mixture and add remaining flour.
Knead well.
Cover and let rise in a warm place for about an hour.

title: milky way cake
directions: Mix flour, eggs, sugar, buttermilk, vanilla and nuts.
Set mixer on medium-high for 2 minutes.
Add melted Milky Way bars and margarine to mixture.
Blend together.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: baked soybeans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute green pepper and onion in oil until tender.
Combine soybeans, cooking water, sauteed vegetables, catsup, salt, kelp powder, honey and molasses in casserole.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni noodles to desired tenderness.
Drain.
Add eggs, butter, Accent and 1/2 can evaporated milk.
Mix up thoroughly.
Then layer greased 13 x 9-inch pan with macaroni mixture.
Then sprinkle with Colby cheese and pour a little evaporated milk, then more macaroni noodle mixture, cheese and then milk.
Keep doing this until mixture is gone.
Top should be cheese.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cook dates, sugar and oleo, stirring constantly until oleo is absorbed.
Add nuts.
Pour over cereal in large bowl.
Mix well. Form in small balls and dust with powdered sugar.
Put several small balls in bag of powdered sugar and shake until well coated. Makes 4 dozen.

title: christmas salad
directions: Drain corn, beans and peas and put them in a bowl.
Boil sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Bring them to a good boil. Pour the boiled mixture over the beans; add chopped onions, pepper and pimentos.
Stir and refrigerate.

title: cheezy corn bake
directions: Mix butter with cream cheese.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: nut roll dough
directions: Heat milk; add to shortening and salt.
Mix all other ingredients together; mix well.
Let rise 2 hours.
Use your favorite nut recipe.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Before baking, beat 1 egg yolk and brush on bread.
Prick with fork to let steam out.
Instead of rolling like a jellyroll, fold the dough for a different effect.

title: oranges with orange sorbet
directions: Cut the oranges in half.
Remove a thin slice from the base of each half so the halves will stand up without tipping.
Scoop out orange insides and fill shell with sorbet.
Freeze each half in its own freezer bag until sorbet is very firm.
Serve frozen. Just before serving, dust the top of each surface with powdered cinnamon.

title: granola
directions: Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Add 1 cup raisins.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; save broth.
Cut chicken into pieces.
Melt butter. Pour butter over stuffing and mix.
Put half of stuffing in casserole dish.
Place chicken on top.
Mix the soup and broth together and pour over chickens.
Place remainder of stuffing on the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: chocolate-filled shortbread
directions: Combine flour, powdered sugar, baking powder, butter and 1 egg with a pastry blender.
Form into a ball and divide in half. Shape each half into a 12-inch rope and place on a baking sheet. Flatten to 1/8-inch and flute edges as for pie crust.
If handling causes dough to soften, chill 15 minutes before baking.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake shortbread 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: cracker candy
directions: Combine sugar and Pet milk.
Bring to a boil; boil 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, pecans, vanilla and crackers.
Stir well and pour in a greased platter.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: pam's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, soda, Crisco, salt and flour.
Add oatmeal, nuts and flavoring.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add taco mix. Stir well.
Add tomatoes and corn. Heat to boiling. Pour into casserole dish. Cover with corn chips.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Place in oven at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes until cheese melts.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt 1/4 cup of butter over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in until blended the light brown sugar (packed).
Cool.
Stir in 1 egg.
Sift together and stir in the flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in vanilla and coarsely chopped walnuts (optional).
Spread in a well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake until, when touched lightly with finger, only a slight imprint remains at 350° (25 minutes). Do not overbake!
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Cut into bars while still warm.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: italian chicken fingers
directions: Cut breasts in half to make fingers.
Marinate chicken breasts in Italian salad dressing, 1 or 2 hours or overnight in fridge. Remove from marinade.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet.
Drizzle melted margarine over chicken.
Season to taste. Bake in 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes or done.

title: feather pancakes
directions: *For thinner pancakes add more milk.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Melt chocolate squares in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in oil and brown sugar until blended.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and baking powder until well blended.
Chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: pumpkin bread or cake
directions: Bake at 350° about 35 minutes in tube pan.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400° and lower temperature to 350° and bake for 30 minutes longer or until filling is set.

title: creamy crab dip
directions: Let cream cheese out of refrigerator for 1/2 hour or until soft.
Add cream cheese and sour cream. Blend until smooth.
Add in cheese, mustard and Old Bay.
In separate bowl, clean crab meat and add to ingredients. Blend together well. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon, ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: frozen fruit cup(low calorie)
directions: Combine fruit in a large bowl.
Combine 7-Up, juice and sugar. Pour over fruit.
Place in paper muffin cups and freeze.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Cool cake.
Poke holes all over top with wooden spoon handle. Pour milk into holes.
Heat fudge topping and pour into holes. Spread Cool Whip on top.
Crush candy bars and sprinkle on top. Store covered in refrigerator.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix corn, egg, sugar and butter. Bake at 425° for about 35 or 40 minutes, until set and brown.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Mix all in a blender and blend until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.
It must be chilled 24 hours before using.

title: dijon chicken
directions: Lightly sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Combine sour cream and mustard in shallow dish.
Mix well.
Dip each chicken breast into mixture and dredge in bread crumbs. Arrange in single layer in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until tender.

title: bouillon chicken
directions: Place cut-up chicken in baking dish.
Dissolve cubes in margarine and add chopped onion.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Put mixture in pie crusts.
You can save some Cool Whip to put on top.

title: crispy crunch bars
directions: Butter a 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan.
Heat corn syrup to boiling in a 3-quart square pan; remove from heat.
Stir in butterscotch chips until melted.
Gradually fold in cereal until completely coated; fold in marshmallows.
Press mixture in pan with buttered back of spoon.
Let stand at least 1 hour.
Cut into bars about 2 1/4 x 1 1/2 inches.
Makes 18 bars.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mash shrimp with a fork or put in blender.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with Triscuits or sesame seed crackers.

title: crock pot soup
directions: Mix and put in crock pot.
Cook several hours.

title: chicken salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion and celery.
Mix with eggs and chicken.
Season to taste. Serve chilled in lettuce cups. Use about 2/3 cup salad for each serving.
Makes 25 (4 ounce) servings.

title: green goodness dip
directions: Combine the avocados, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Fold in parsley and onions.
Refrigerate until serving.
Serve with shrimp, crackers or vegetables.
Makes 3 cups.

title: forty niners
directions: Combine all the ingredients and blend well.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool completely!
Slice into 48 square cookie bars. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: pastitsio
directions: Cook first 7 ingredients.
Add 1 pound cooked macaroni.
Add butter and mix lightly.
Mix 8 eggs with 2 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over mix.
Add on top 3/4 cup cheese.
Cook in 450° oven for 20 minutes.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Mix cherry and lime Jell-O with crushed pineapple.
Cook on stove until boiling.
Add Coke and nuts. Stir well.
Pour in bowl and refrigerate.

title: biscuit topped ham
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add flour, soup, milk and ham; cook until all thick.
Add lemon and pour into a baking dish.
Add eggs and top with biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes; then bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together. Put in hot skillet of grease. Open and drain corn and tomatoes. Pour on top of meat. Mix corn bread batter and pour on top of other ingredients. Bake at 450° to 500° until corn bread is done.

title: cranberry orange mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add spices and cranberry sauce.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in oranges.
Pour into six-cup mold or bowl.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Serve as salad or relish.
