Makes about 5 cups, 10 side salads or 14 relish servings.

title: lemon pie
directions: In medium bowl, mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together. Pour in thawed can of lemonade, mixing together well.
Pour into pie shells and chill for 1 hour before serving.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain hamburger and add Ragu sauce; simmer until hot.
Brown pie crust in oven.
Pour mixture in pie crust, cover with Mozzarella cheese and brown in oven.

title: fu fu coffee
directions: Top with whipped cream, dash of creme de menthe and nutmeg.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix green beans, celery, peas, pimento and onion in salad bowl.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Add boiling water to sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Cook over low heat.
Add butter and vanilla.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add eggs and beat well. Add salt, vanilla, flour and soda; mix well. Add oatmeal, coconut and cereal; beat slowly. Mixture will be thick.
Drop from spoon on greased cookie sheet. Press down with fork. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: minnie's applesauce cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Put into greased and floured pan. Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: easy deep dish pizza
directions: *Can use tomato sauce in place of pizza sauce.
Use ground turkey in place of beef.

title: creole okra
directions: Saute okra, onion and pepper 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in other ingredients.
Cook over low heat 10 to 15 minutes. Stir occasionally.

title: mustard green beans
directions: Steam beans until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Melt butter in a heavy medium pan over medium heat.
Stir in mustard.
Toss beans in mixture to coat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: buttermilk biscuits with variation
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in a mixing bowl.
Cut in butter with a fork or 2 knives until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in 3/4 cup buttermilk all at once.
Add more buttermilk if needed to make a soft dough.
Knead dough gently about 10 minutes on a lightly floured board.
Pat or roll dough about 1/2 inch thick.
Cut dough with a knife into squares. Place biscuits on a baking sheet.
Brush tops with a little buttermilk.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: In bowl, mix jello with boiling water until dissolved.
Mix in sherbet, then add oranges and juice.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Pour mixture in a 1 1/2-quart dish and chill until set or overnight. Serves 8.

title: sweet dough
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the 1/2 cup warm water.
Using a mixer, make a batter of the sugar, shortening, salt, eggs, 1 3/4 cups warm water, 3 cups flour and yeast mixture.
Using a spoon, add 3 cups more flour.
Turn dough out on lightly floured table.
Grease bowl and turn upside down over dough.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Knead until a soft dough, using around 1/2 to 1 cup flour.
Let rise until double or a little more than double.
Pinch off a piece, roll in a ball and place on greased cookie sheet to make buns.
You can make any kind of rolls or cinnamon rolls with this dough.

title: coconut balls
directions: Melt butter and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix rest of ingredients except chocolate and shape into balls.
Dip in chocolate.

title: mom's "iowa pork chops"
directions: Brown pork chops quickly and place in a baking dish.
Make mixture of remaining ingredients and spread over chops.
Add enough water to cover bottom of pan and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool spaghetti.
Add oil, vinegar and pimientos.

title: fuzzy navel cream
directions: In food processor bowl with metal blade, process peaches until smooth.
Add sherbet and Schnapps.
Process with on-off pulses just to mix.
Add milk; process just until combined.
Pour into chilled glasses.
Serve immediately.
Makes 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese with sugar and mayonnaise.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in freezer for one hour, then transfer to refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil hen.
Add salt to taste when cooking hen.
Remove hen from bone after it's cooked.
Add to deboned hen and broth the cream of chicken soup, bouillon cubes and black pepper.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Add dumplings.
Bake in a 350° oven for a brown top. Pour a little milk on top when you remove from oven.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all the ingredients except the butter.
Add that to the middle and bake for 1 hour or until injected knife in center comes out clean at 350°.

title: no-bake oat cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa (can omit for peanut butter oat cookies) in large heavy saucepan.
Stir in milk.
Bring to full rolling boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, butter or peanut butter and oats.
Stir vigorously until well combined.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool to set.

title: applesauce pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, then pie filling. Add well beaten eggs. Mix in applesauce.
Add vanilla.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: I make a recipe and a half per chicken.

title: russian tea balls
directions: Mix butter and vanilla.
Sift and stir in flour, salt and nuts. Make 1-inch balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
While still warm roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 35.

title: quick delicious fudge
directions: Place chocolate bars, chocolate morsels and Marshmallow Creme in a large bowl of an electric mixer.
Combine the sugar, milk, butter and salt in a heavy 3 or 4-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
When the mixture comes to a boil, lower the heat to medium and set a timer for 6 minutes.
Keep the mixture boiling steadily and stir constantly to prevent scorching.
At the end of 6 minutes, pour the boiling syrup over the chocolate and Marshmallow Creme.
Beat until the chocolate is melted and the ingredients are well blended.
Beat in the vanilla and walnuts.
Pour into a lightly buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Let the fudge cool at room temperature for 24 hours before cutting. Cut into 1-inch square pieces and pack in airtight containers.
The fudge may be stored in airtight containers at room temperature for up to 2 weeks.
It may be frozen for up to 6 months.
Makes 5 pounds of fudge.

title: ice cream
directions: Cook pudding and milk
until it is thickened.
Then add remaining ingredients and put
in freezer and freeze.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: boneless chicken breast in sour cream
directions: Roll boneless breast in sour cream until coated.
Crush potato chips and roll chicken in chips.
Place chicken in greased flat baking dish.
Melt butter, 1 tablespoon per breast.
Crush medium clove of garlic and mix with butter.
Drizzle over chicken.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil all, except soda, until it makes a soft ball when dropped into a cup of cold water.
Remove.
Add the soda; it will foam. Add to popcorn you have already popped!

title: pickled okra
directions: Boil vinegar, water and salt for 10 minutes.
Pack okra in jars.
Place dill seed, garlic and peppers in each jar.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over okra.
Seal.
Allow to pickle for about two weeks.

title: catsup
directions: Cut the tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Cook with salt and strain.
Pour mixture into a bag; let drain 3 hours.
Save 1 cup of juice.
In large boiler, add the vinegar, 1 cup strained juice, sugar and horseradish.
Add spice bag made up of the red pepper and pickle spice.
Cook everything 30 to 40 minutes.
Put into hot, sterilized jars (open kettle).

title: mud pie
directions: Heat the oven to 325°. Grease a round pan, 8 x 1 1/2-inches, with shortening.

title: minestrone(soup)
directions: You will need to use large pot.
Simmer bone, bay leaf and celery in water.
After 20 minutes, add tomatoes, sauce, onion, garlic, salt, pepper and basil.
Simmer for 1.5 hours.
Add celery slices, carrots and potatoes; continue to simmer for 30 minutes. Remove bone and add all remaining ingredients.
Cook for approximately 20 minutes until macaroni is done.
Serve with a sprinkle grated Parmesan cheese.
Recipe makes 6 quarts.
Viva Italiano!!

title: rainbow muck
directions: Mix ingredients and cook until thick.
Play with it on a table or in a Ziploc bag.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Stir ingredients well.
Spread in pan; add topping, if desired.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes until light brown.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Set aside 2/3 cup of cake mix.
Combine rest of cake mix with butter and beaten egg.
Stir by hand until crumbly.
Press evenly into bottom and 1-inch up sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan, ungreased. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Cut kraut into small pieces with scissors.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover tightly and chill.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Mix well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add butter to dressing.
Mix well.
Place 1/2 of dressing mixture in 10 inch casserole dish.
Press down.
Combine soup & milk.
Heat thoroughly in a sauce pan.

title: carrot meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together, shape meat and place in baking dish. Pour glaze over top and bake at 350° until done.

title: oreo cookie delight
directions: Crush Oreos.
Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Mix remainder with 1 stick melted butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch dish.
In a bowl, beat softened cream cheese with 1/2 cup milk until smooth.
In another bowl, mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
Beat until smooth. Pour slowly into cream cheese mix.
Beat until well mixed.
Pour over Oreos.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs. Refrigerate overnight.

title: salt ceramic
directions: Cook over low heat until mixture forms a ball.
Knead the dough.
This is good for making Christmas decorations because it becomes very hard when dry.

title: orange freeze
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender.
Blend for 30 to 40 seconds.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion and rice; brown.
Place in casserole, then lay chicken on top.
Spread soup over this, then pour water over entire casserole.
Salt and pepper, as desired. Cover with foil; cook 1 hour at 375°.
Remove foil and brown 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook onions until tender; add ground beef.
Brown lightly; stir in beans and soup.
Pour into casserole and put drop biscuits on top.
Bake at 400° until biscuits are done.
Can use Bisquick to make biscuits.
(You can top with mashed potatoes and brown instead of biscuits.)

title: grilled herbed potatoes
directions: Clean potatoes, leave skins on. Cut into quarters lengthwise. Place potatoes on a large doubled piece of foil.
Size of foil depends on the amount of potatoes you have.
Drizzle melted margarine over potatoes.
Sprinkle on garlic powder to taste, add chopped chives (fresh or dried), sprinkle Italian seasoning over. Seal foil.
Place over hot grill for about 45 minutes.
Or until done (again depends on amount of potatoes).

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Cook pudding with milk; cover while cooking.
Break angel food in pieces in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When pudding is cool, stir in Cool Whip.
Pour over cake.
Sprinkle with Butterfinger candy bar crumbs.
Or, you may top with more Cool Whip and then sprinkle with candy bar crumbs.

title: one egg cake
directions: Mix
flour;
add baking powder and salt.
Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add egg and beat thoroughly.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a greased pan, 8 x 8-inches, at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mystery meat
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding enough mayo to bind the ingredients together.
Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter icing
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Ice cake when cool.

title: casserole barbecued chicken
directions: Early in the day, dip chicken pieces into flour mixed with salt.
Fry in hot fat until golden brown.
Remove to 3-quart casserole.
If necessary, pour all but 2 tablespoons fat from skillet.
Add onion to fat; saute until golden and tender.
Add celery and next 6 ingredients; pour over chicken.
Chill.

title: grandma bertie's corned beef soup
directions: Save all leftovers in refrigerator, and once a week clean out and mix together, then add 1 can tomato juice.
Cook 25 minutes on low.
Serve while hot.
You may want to cook stew meat or 1 pound of hamburger and add to soup.

title: blueberry torte
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine.
Pat the crumb mixture into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: pumpkin pudding cake
directions: Mix eggs, milk, sugar, pumpkin, vanilla, cinnamon and salt. Pour into lightly oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1 yellow or white cake mix over the pumpkin mixture.
Drizzle 1 cube melted margarine over cake mix.
Top with 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marinade for fish
directions: Combine all ingredients.
This can be used to perk up swordfish or any fish.
Serves 5-6.

title: southern dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: best brownies
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla in large bowl.
Add eggs; using a wooden spoon, beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Gradually blend into egg mixture.
Stir in nuts. Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edges of pan. Cool; frost with Creamy Brownie Frosting.
Cut into squares. Makes about 16 brownies.

title: pecan cream cheese pie
directions: In bowl, combine pecans, coconut and oleo.
Pour onto an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown, stirring occasionally.
Cool.

title: peanut butter-oatmeal cookies
directions: Dried fruits, nuts or seeds may be added.

title: clam chowder
directions: In a large pot, put clams, vegetables and clam juice.
Barely cover with water. Simmer 20 minutes. While that is cooking, take the butter and melt. Add the flour and blend.
Add the milk, salt, pepper and sugar. Cook like a white sauce and add to clam mixture.
Cook slowly until thick.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Important Note:
Boil green beans 20 minutes with 2 cloves garlic.
Remove garlic and drain.

title: carrot-raisin salad with orange yogurt dressing
directions: Mix yogurt and juice concentrate.
Toss with carrots and raisins.
Chill.
Serves 6.

title: six week muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, flour, soda and salt in a very large mixing bowl. Add beaten eggs, shortening or oil and buttermilk. Mix well. Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Use as directed.

title: date nut balls
directions: Mix the butter, nuts, sugar, egg, dates and salt over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes. Mix and mash well.
Cool.
Add the Rice Krispies and vanilla. Roll into 1-inch balls and roll in coconut.

title: chicken sesame stir-fry
directions: Marinate chicken in soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Remove chicken after 15 minutes and set aside.
Whisk 1 teaspoon cornstarch into marinade.
In a separate bowl, combine egg white and remaining 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Dip chicken strips into egg mixture and coat with sesame seeds.
Over very high heat, brown chicken in hot oil; remove.
Add carrots, onions, asparagus tips and water chestnuts; stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Stir in marinade and cook until thick.
Stir in chicken, stirring to blend flavors. Serve with boiled rice.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine butter, flour and nuts.
Mix well and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (also sides).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and 1 1/2 cups of Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Chill until set.
Combine 2 puddings together in bowl and add milk.
(Mix 2 minutes on medium).
Spread over set mixture.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over top.
Let set. Garnish with shaved Hershey bar and chopped nuts.

title: german skillet dinner
directions: Brown kielbasa in butter in heavy large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly and simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, for 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes test done with a fork.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Place egg white in large bowl.
Add 1 tablespoon water and beat slightly.
Add nuts and stir until moistened.
Mix dry ingredients together in small bowl.
Pour over nuts.
Mix well. Spread on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring 2 or 3 times while baking.

title: my grammy's soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar, Crisco and eggs.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Alternate flour mixture to cream mixture, adding milk and vanilla in between.
Grease and flour cookie sheets.
Drop by teaspoons; sprinkle with cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mud cake
directions: Cream the butter and gradually add granulated sugar.
Add 1 whole egg and 1 egg yolk.
Mix well.
Sift in dry ingredients and mix.
Add vanilla; mix.
Spread 1/2-inch thick layer in jelly roll pan or 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Cover with topping made by combining stiffly beaten egg white and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until brown.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: cranberry pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs with fork just until blended.
Stir in corn syrup, sugar, butter and salt. Sprinkle cranberries in pastry shell.
Arrange pecan halves on top of cranberries.
Pour syrup mixture carefully over pecans.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes, or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge of pie comes out clean.
Cool on rack before serving.
If edge of pie seems to be browning too quickly, cover it with a strip of foil.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers thin; sprinkle with salt.
Bury in ice.
Let stand three hours.
Drain well.

title: apple bread pudding
directions: Combine apples and bread cubes in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine butter, sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Pour over apples in casserole.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with brown sugar and reheat a few moments, if desired.
Top with Oakfarms cream.

title: italian macaroni salad
directions: Cook the macaroni. Rinse, drain and chill. Mix together the salt, black pepper, oregano, vinegar and salad oil. Set aside for dressing. Mix macaroni with remaining ingredients and pour dressing over. Mix well. Chill in refrigerator overnight and then let stand 3 hours at room temperature before serving.

title: brown sugar chess pie
directions: Put sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and eggs in a bowl.
Beat well. Add milk and beat again.
Add melted butter and beat again. Bake in unbaked pie shells at 375° for 45 minutes.
This will make three medium-size pies.

title: 1 2 3 coconut cake
directions: Prepare white cake mix as directed on package.
After cake cools, poke holes all over cake with the handle of a wooden spoon (need to be large holes).
Pour cream of coconut over cake.
Frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Keep in the refrigerator.

title: sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Turn oven to 140° (lowest your oven gets).
Line 2 baking sheets with foil.
Place rack on top of foil (cookie rack). Slice tomatoes lengthwise and cut off bottoms.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in oven and let dry to golden (4 to 8 hours). If they are red-brown, they dried too long.
Remove, let cool and place in jar.
Add garlic, basil and olive oil.
Use with pasta, salads or alone.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cook beef until well browned on all sides. Remove from pan. Add onions to drippings. Saute until golden. Return meat.
Add paprika, salt and pepper. Stir until well blended. Stir in 3/4 cup beef broth; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours. Combine flour and remaining broth. Gradually add to beef mixture, stirring constantly. Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Just before serving, add sour cream.
Do not boil. Serve with noodles.

title: spinach squares
directions: In a large bowl, combine and mix well eggs, butter, flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Stir in cheeses, onion and spinach. Spoon mixture in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan and level off.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Let cool 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: great pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, oats, soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Cream butter; gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Alternate additions of dry ingredients and pumpkin, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in morsels.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until done.
Can be glazed.

title: happy home recipe
directions: Take love and loyalty, mix thoroughly with faith.
Blend with tenderness, kindness and understanding.
Add friendship and hope. Sprinkle with laughter.
Bake with sunshine.
Serve daily with communication.

title: banana bread squares
directions: Set oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter and brown sugar.
Add egg and yogurt.
Combine white flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon and sift into creamed mixture.
Add whole wheat flour, rolled oats, mashed bananas and nuts or seeds. Mix just to blend.
Turn into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until center springs back to the touch and sides shrink away from pan.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar well in a bowl.
Add beaten egg yolks, flour and sour cream, mixing thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice eggplant about 1/2 inch.
Slice cheese.
Make a batter of eggs and milk.
Dip eggplant in batter and bread crumbs.
Brown in oil; set aside.
Line bottom of casserole with eggplant; add a layer of cheese.
Sprinkle on oregano and salt.
Pour on 2 cans sauce, then Parmesan cheese.
Add another layer of everything. Bake 55 minutes at 350°.
Let set 5 or 10 minutes.

title: overnight buns
directions: Mix around 4 to 5 p.m.
Warm water; cool to lukewarm.
Combine sugar and yeast.
Add melted margarine, salt and eggs.
Add flour as needed.
Knead down every hour for four times.
Make into buns. Let stand until morning.
Bake at 350°.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix together yellow cake mix, Crisco oil, 1/2 cup sugar, eggs and sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 13 cake pan.
Mix together brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans; pour 1/2 on top of cake batter.
Swirl with knife.
Pour rest of cake batter into the pan. Top with remaining mixture of brown sugar, cinnamon and pecans. Swirl again.
Bake in moderate oven, 325° for 45 minutes.
Mix together powdered sugar, milk, vanilla and butter.
While cake is still hot, punch holes in top with a knife and rum knife around the edges of the cake.
Pour mixture on top of cake while it is still hot.
Let mixture run into holes.

title: lebanese cookies
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and beaten egg yolks.
Beat until light.
Add milk, salt and enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Break off small pieces of dough, roll between floured hands until about 1/2 inch thick.
Shape cookies like a circle and place on cookie sheet.
Brush with egg white and 1 tablespoon rosewater mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts and sugar.
Bake in 325° oven for 15 minutes.
You may add anise seed or sesame seeds to dough mixture.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine the powdered sugar, milk and oleo. Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Add the marshmallow cream and the peanut butter.
Add nuts if desired.
Spread in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add turkey, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Mix well.
Form into 12 to 16 balls.
Spray a nonstick pan with Pam.
Fry the balls until browned.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, pepper salt, monosodium glutamate and oregano. Dredge steak with seasoned flour and brown in skillet.
Place in flat baking pan.
Saute onions, garlic and mushrooms in cooking oil for 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and beef stock.
Cook a minute longer.
Pour sauce over steak and cover pan but not completely.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: cherry delight
directions: Press crumb mixture in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Beat cheese and powdered sugar together.
Mix whipping cream with cheese mixture.
Pour over crumbs and cover with pie filling and chill.

title: new orleans barbecued shrimp
directions: Wash
shrimp
and
place in deep casserole
dish.
Melt butter in microwave.
Add lemon juice,
Worcestershire
sauce and seasonings to butter.
Stir well.
You may want
to adjust garlic or salt to taste.
Pour butter mixture over raw shrimp. Cook in microwave for approximately 15 minutes on High setting until shrimp
is
pink.
Serve with thick slices
of
French bread.

title: ice cream
directions: Add
all
ingredients and beat well; add fruit.
Put in ice cream freezer and finish filling with milk to fill line on container.	Make in ice cream freezer.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Mix eggs, pineapple, sugar and flour in 2-quart casserole. Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
In the meantime, brown the bread cubes in margarine in skillet.
Cover top of casserole with browned bread cubes and bake 45 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Put on dough board and roll out thin.
Cut in long strips and tear in pieces.
Drop in chicken broth pot.
Let dough stand before rolling out and cutting.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add beaten eggs and beat well.
Add flour and
milk
alternately
to	oil and sugar mixture.	Add flavoring and
coconut
and mix.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour in 350° oven. Use well-greased Bundt pan or tube pan.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat (seasoned), onion and garlic on low heat, then add other ingredients except macaroni,
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add cooked macaroni (1/4 cup uncooked).
Simmer an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo and 2 cups of white sugar together.
Beat in eggs. Fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; beat until smooth.
Pour 1/2 of batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cook and mash sweet potatoes.
Mix in eggs until blended.
Add 1/4 cup brown sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Mix until blended.
Add orange juice and blend until fluffy.
Put mixture in oiled baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped pecans on top.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar over pecans.
Pour 1/2 cup melted butter over brown sugar.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: michele's carrot cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add oil & eggs; mix well. Add carrots, drained pineapple, & nuts. Bake in 9x13 greased pan at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix and put in baked pie shell.
Whip egg whites with sugar for meringue.
Bake until peaks are brown.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix margarine, peanut butter and both sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Blend in dry ingredients and mix until thoroughly combined.
Form dough into walnut-sized balls and roll each ball in a bowl of sugar.
Place balls 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Quickly press chocolate Kisses into center of each cookie and return to oven for 3 minutes longer.

title: picnic salad
directions: Mix all the above ingredients.
Chill and serve.
Serves 8.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake 1 hour in 9 x 9-inch pan at 350°.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, vanilla and 1 tablespoon of water together. Add in flour, chopped pecans and dash of salt. Blend together with wooden spoon or by kneading (add flour OR water as necessary to get a good play dough-like consistency). Roll into 1-inch balls (or egg shapes for Easter). Freeze (once shaped) and pull out to bake at a later date OR bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Allow to cool, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: joe's famous taco dip
directions: Layer, beginning with the beans, then mashed avocados, then mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix and pour over the top.
Next, the grated cheese.
Chop or slice the green onions.
Spread the green onions and black olives and diced tomato on top.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serve with taco chips.

title: italian tomato soup
directions: Empty cans of tomato soup and beef consomme into a pan, adding the 1 can of water.
Stir until smooth.
Add thyme and marjoram and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon; reserve a few strips for the top and chop the rest. Combine all the ingredients and add chopped bacon pieces.
Place in casserole or baking dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dirt
directions: In blender, crush 4 cookies at a time.
If no blender, roll them out.
Cream together the margarine or butter with the cream cheese and confectioners sugar.

title: mediterranean chickpea salad
directions: Drain tuna fish, beans and artichoke hearts and combine the three ingredients with celery.
Add ripe olives which have been drained and sliced.
Mix ingredients in bowl and sprinkle with salt.
Add creamy dressing.
Toss lightly and chill. Serves 4 to 6.

title: fluffy orange salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: pistachio supreme
directions: Mix flour, butter, sugar, the 1/2 cup of chopped pecans and water.
Pat this mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the tablespoon of sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool. Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and the one cup Cool Whip. Dab onto the crust and spread lightly evenly.
Beat together the milk and pudding mixes.
Spread over filling in pie pan.
Chill in refrigerator until set.
Spread a thin layer of Cool Whip over this.
Sprinkle (garnish) with pecan pieces.

title: fried crab cakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, toss crabmeat with all ingredients, except oil and lemon, mixing thoroughly.
Shape into 6 or 7 cakes.

title: voyaging potato casserole
directions: Beat warm potatoes and cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in eggs, flour, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and dot with butter or margarine.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken or turkey dressing casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing according to directions.
Add dry bread crumbs to make larger portions.
Add chicken or turkey and cream of chicken soup (undiluted).
Bake at 325° or 350° until heated through.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Save broth.
While chicken is cooling, cut celery and onion into small pieces.
Put into food processor and chop, being careful not to overchop.
Squeeze the liquid out of celery and onion.
Mix all the ingredients, except for the broth.
Put broth in a jar and save for another recipe. Mix and let stand for half an hour, then serve.

title: guacamole
directions: Cut avocado in half; peel, pit and mash well in a medium bowl. Stir in mayonnaise, onion, lemon juice, salt, red pepper seasoning and tomato.
Cover tightly; chill about an hour.
When ready to serve, spoon into a small bowl; sprinkle bacon bites on top.
Place bowl on a large serving plate; surround with corn chips.

title: rocky road chocolate squares
directions: In top of double boiler, over boiling water, melt morsels with sweetened condensed milk and butter.
Remove from heat.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a bowl, toss well.
Cover and chill 3 hours.

title: coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan. Combine all ingredients and stir until well blended.
Sprinkle with streusel topping.
Make indentations in the batter so topping will bake into cake.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vegetarian soup
directions: Bring all vegetables to boil.
Cook until done on lower heat. Sprinkle salt to taste.
Add a little Accent, George Washington seasoning or McKay's chicken seasoning.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and slice about 1/4-inch thick.
Dip in egg and bread crumbs.
Fry in hot oil on both sides until brown.
Put a little spaghetti sauce in bottom of baking dish:
one layer of eggplant, one layer of Mozzarella cheese, a little more spaghetti sauce on top of cheese and add a little Parmesan cheese on top of sauce.
Start with another layer.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Thirty minutes before serving, heat about 3/4 cup of oil in a 12-inch skillet over medium heat to 370° on deep-fat thermometer. Or heat oil in electric skillet to 370°.
In a medium bowl, mix flour, milk, baking powder, salt and egg with a fork or wire whisk.
When oil is ready, hold funnel with finger over spout while pouring 1/2 cup batter into top of funnel.
Carefully remove finger to let batter run out into oil in a steam, spiraling it to form small circle.
Fry 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown, turning once with tongs.
Drain well on paper towel.
Sprinkle cakes lightly with powdered sugar.
Serve warm or cold.

title: doughboys
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; heat milk and shortening in saucepan until milk is scalded and shortening melted.
Blend together sugar and salt; add to hot milk mixture in large bowl.
Cool to lukewarm; blend in egg and yeast.
Gradually add flour.
Mix thoroughly. Grease top and cover.
Let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Divide dough in half; roll out to 12 x 9-inch rectangle. Cut into 4 x 2-inch strips.
Cut each strip twice about halfway across on 4-inch side.
Spread apart so sides do not touch.
Place on floured board and cover.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown, 1 to 2 minutes each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Dip in thin syrup made with powdered sugar, milk and a little vanilla.

title: cherry winks
directions: Crush corn flakes cereal to measure 1 1/3 cups; set aside. Stir together flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture. Mix until well combined.
Stir in nuts, dates and chopped cherries.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Mix all together and stuff turkey or place around turkey 2 hours before turkey is done.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and Crisco; stir until Crisco is melted.
Cool mixture to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water; mix with first water.
Add egg; stir in flour to make soft dough.
Grease a bowl with cooking oil.
Place dough in bowl; turn to grease on all sides.
Cover tightly; store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Will keep about 1 week.
When ready to use, punch down.
Make into rolls.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Brush with melted butter.
Let rise in a warm place until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake in a hot oven at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 rolls.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the sugar and oil.
Add eggs, flour, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Mash bananas and add.

title: hommous-humas
directions: Drain the juice from 1 can of chickpeas.
Place the drained beans in a blender.
Add the second can of chickpeas, water and all.
Add the tahini, lemon juice and garlic; blend until smooth. Pour onto a large plate and drizzle olive oil over top.
Garnish with parsley.
Serve with sliced vegetables for dip, along with pita bread cut into wedges.

title: delicious pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add alternately with milk, starting with flour and ending with flour.
Add flavorings and mix well.
Bake in a 10-inch greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Mash avocados, then mix all ingredients except lettuce and tomatoes thoroughly.
Arrange chopped lettuce and tomatoes in nests on 4 to 6 salad plates.
Mound avocado mixture in each nest. Sprinkle paprika on top of each salad.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pasta with broccoli
directions: In a large pan, heat the oil and butter.
Lightly brown the garlic cloves.
Add tomatoes, chicken broth, wine, basil and pepper.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Add broccoli. Cover pan and cook over medium heat another 10 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes with marshmallows
directions: Mash yams.
Add all ingredients except marshmallows.
Place in baking dish. Bake 30 minutes. Remove from oven and add marshmallows. Return to oven long enough to melt and brown marshmallows.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Layer tuna, rice, almonds and oranges in a 13 x 11-inch pan. Sprinkle with pepper and salt.
Spread soup over the top.
Add 1 can of water.
Put the chow mein noodles over the top.
Cook in oven (325°) for 30 minutes or
microwave 5 to 8 minutes.
Let stand.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: Sprinkle cinnamon on bread.
Cover cinnamon with sugar.
Cover sugar with margarine.
Put into oven to toast!
Serve warm!

title: easy spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onions and peppers, cook a few minutes more.
Drain grease.
Add tomatoes and simmer 30 minutes.

title: pineapple-carrot salad
directions: Mix all together in large bowl. Cover and refrigerate.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Bring to a boil and boil for 3 to 5 minutes the sugar, butter, cocoa and milk, then add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix together, then drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper to cool. (Instead of peanut butter you may use coconut.)

title: play dough
directions: To keep cracked eggs from cooking out so much and to make removal of the shell of a hard-boiled egg easier, add salt to the cooking water.

title: bubble bread
directions: Quarter rolls and dip into melted butter.
Alternate layers of rolls, pepperoni and cheese.
End with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 375° until golden (8 to 10 minutes).

title: meatless spaghetti(altered a bit from recipes for a small planet)
directions: Heat oil in saucepan.
Saute onions, celery, carrots, green pepper, garlic and mushrooms until onions are very soft.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spread in a large Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 45-50 minutes or until bubbling.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine brown sugar substitute, flour, milk, egg yolks, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Pour pudding into baked pie crust.
Whip egg whites until soft peaks form; add sugar substitute and whip until thick and stiff.
Spread on top of pudding, sealing edges.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
8 serving, calories per serving 62. Please add calories for pie crust.

title: gautier gumbo
directions: Roux Recipe:
Instead of the time consuming old recipes for roux of past, Brother Bobby has found a modern microwave way of conjuring up a roux.
In a microwave-safe bowl, combine 1/2 cup of flour and 1/2 cup of vegetable oil.
Cover with paper towel.
Put in microwave on High about 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir roux.
Microwave at 30 second intervals as you stir well, heat, then stir well until the roux has a purple hue.
Don't let roux get black (burnt).
When purple, remove from microwave and set aside.

title: paradise pie
directions: Mix directly in pie plate.
Mixes easy with a fork; then when all is well moistened, pat out to cover bottom and sides evenly. Add fresh fruit or a can of pie filling of your choice.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook meat, onion and green pepper in skillet until meat is lightly browned and vegies are tender.
Stir in tomato sauce, corn, olives, garlic, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, chili powder and pepper. Simmer 20 to 25 minutes, until thick.
Add cheese, stir until melted.
Turn into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Stir cornmeal and 1/2 teaspoon salt into cold water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add butter or margarine, mix well.
Spoon over hot meat mixture.
Bake in 375° oven about 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Cook eggs.
Use cooked meat (small amount).
Add small amount of remaining ingredients.
Use soy sauce to taste.
Mix well.
Refrigerate to keep.

title: rolls
directions: Beat sugar, lard and salt together.
Add yolks and beat.
Add yeast, dissolved in 1/4 cup warm water.
Beat again.
Add 4 cups warm water.
Add enough flour to handle (about 10 cups for firmer dough).
Keep in refrigerator.
Let rise once or twice before storing.
Use as needed.
Shape into rolls; let rise and bake.

title: gramm betty's broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayo, vinegar and sugar for dressing.
Add onions, pour over broccoli and mix as you add raisins; let sit in refrigerator for 4 hours.
Just before serving, sprinkle on bacon bits and sunflower seeds and mix.

title: elaine's salsa
directions: Peel and chunk raw tomatoes.
Place in colander to drain (approximately 10 to 15 minutes).
Chop green peppers, onions and hot peppers.
Mix everything and bring to a boil.
Simmer for one hour plus to reduce liquid.
Place in pint jars.
Seal and use water bath for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 pints.

title: rhubarb dream bars
directions: Mix
crust
of	flour,	powdered
sugar
and margarine. Press into
a
15 x 10-inch pan.	Bake at 350° for 15 minutes (crust will
be light).
Combine eggs, sugar, flour and salt; beat together.
Fold
in
rhubarb.
Spread filling mixture on hot crust.
Return to oven; bake 40 to 45 minutes longer.

title: snow white salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for several hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves. Garnish with fresh apple slices.
Serves 4.

title: margaret's congo squares
directions: In a large saucepan, melt the margarine; add sugar, water and vanilla.
Let cool.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients, which have been sifted together.
Add chocolate bits and chopped nuts.
Mix well and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out and cut into small biscuits.
Dip in melted butter.
Stack one on top of the other. Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400°.

title: grilled chicken with sweet onion relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large self closing bag, mixing well. Seal and marinate in refrigerator at least 2 hours, turning bag occasionally. Spray the grill with no stick spray before heating. Remove chicken from bag, reserving marinade. Place chicken on the rack over coals. Grill uncovered for 15 to 20 minutes or until the chicken is no longer pink. Brush frequently with reserved marinade while grilling. Serve with relish.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: In a frying pan, brown chicken on both sides, in shortening for about 10 minutes.

Grease a Pyrex casserole or other baking pan, then place rice on bottom, add dots of butter and onion soup mix. Mix the mushroom soup with a half can of water and add to rice. Mix rice mixture thoroughly.
Place chicken pieces on top and bake in a 350° to 375° oven for one hour or until tender.

title: yogurt shake
directions: Mix yogurt and fruit in blender on low.
Add in juice and turn blender to medium.
Blend until smooth.
Enjoy!

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange pork chops in lightly greased or sprayed casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with layer of potatoes and onions.
Blend soup, milk and water.
Pour mixture over chops.
Bake approximately 1 hour.
May be browned 2 to 3 minutes under broiler before serving.

title: poulet sauce paradis
directions: Rub chicken inside and out with salt, pepper and butter. Roast chicken, uncovered, in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Make dressing as directed on box.
Layer broccoli and carrots over chicken.
Layer dressing over vegetables.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over top of dressing.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spanish rice
directions: Put a little oil in frying pan, fry rice until brown.
In separate pan, fry bacon, tomato, pepper, onion and garlic until bacon is done.
Add 2 cups of water to rice, when boiling add other ingredients including tomato sauce.
Lower heat and simmer until juice is gone and rice is tender.
Fluff with fork and serve.

title: ham 'n egg casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to directions and drain.
Combine 3/4 cup of cubed cheese and ham.
Alternate layers of noodles with ham and cheese in greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix soup, milk and curry powder.
Pour over noodle mixture. Press halved eggs on top (yolk side up).
Dot with butter and sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix together the flour and sugar, then add beaten egg yolks, milk and butter.
Heat in top of double boiler over hot water. Cook and stir until thickened.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Cool. Pour into baked pie shells.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, flour, coconut, vanilla and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 2 pie pans sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar, oleo and eggs together.
Add peanut butter and flour.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Stir into the creamed mixture.
Form into balls about the size of a walnut.
Flatten with fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars; beat in eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, oats, baking soda and cinnamon; stir into cream mixture alternately with pumpkin. Fold in chocolate chips. Drop by tablespoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 13 minutes or until lightly brown. Makes 4 dozen.

title: ruth's mystery pie
directions: Mix egg whites gradually with sugar.
Add to that the broken Ritz crackers, pecans and vanilla together.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Chill 1/2 pint whipped cream and add 3 tablespoons cocoa.
Spread on top of pie.

title: apple pie crust
directions: Mix well.
Press into pie dish.
Pour apple pie filling over crust.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes.
Good on top, too.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco and add sugar.
Beat and add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt and add alternately with milk.
Bake in a tube pan for one hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Grease tube pan with Crisco and dust with flour.
Don't preheat oven and don't peek!

title: holiday macaroni salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients except lettuce and tomatoes.
Mix well. Pour mayonnaise over salad.
Toss and mix well.
Arrange lettuce leaves on serving platter.
Arrange tomato slices around outer edges of leaves.
Pour salad into middle of platter and arrange.

title: ripe olive sandwich
directions: Mash eggs
with
a
fork.
Drain olives.
Combine eggs, olives, pecans and sweet pickle with enough mayonnaise to make a spreading consistency.
Add grated onion to taste.	Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: fig preserve cake
directions: *Black walnuts and/or hickory nuts can be mixed as part of the nuts.

title: pecan roll candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and milk. Cook to a soft ball.
Put in chopped dates and cook 5 minutes longer. Remove from heat and mix in butter and nuts. Stir until cool.
Pour out on a clean, damp cloth.
When cool enough to handle, roll into a roll.
After candy is completely cool, roll up in foil and refrigerate. Slice and enjoy.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and press down half in bottom of pan.
Mix the sugar and cornstarch. Add the water and vanilla. Cook mixture until thick and clear.
Pour over the rhubarb that has been put on pressed down mixture in pan. Add remaining crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: keene new hampshire applesauce cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Soak raisins in hot water.
Pour hot applesauce over the shortening and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Drain and add raisins.
Pour into greased 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts on top.
Bake for 45 minutes.
This is good with a dollop of whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: peas and radishes
directions: Microwave peas, radishes and water on High for 5 to 7 minutes. Microwave milk, flour, salt and pepper for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes; stir every 30 seconds.
Pour mixture over peas and radishes.

title: irene shelmidine's vegetable soup
directions: Grind potatoes, onions, celery, carrots and peppers.
Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes, which have been ground, and cook a few minutes longer.
Place in jars and seal.

title: salmon ball
directions: Drain, flake and remove bones and skin from salmon.
Add lemon juice and other seasonings, mix well.
Stir in salmon and mix well. Place in refrigerator for at least 4 hours or until thoroughly chilled.
Shape into ball.
Can be used immediately or wrap and keep in the freezer for later.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Boil sugar and syrup until clear.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Add Rice Krispies, 2 cups at a time. Butter 13 x 9-inch pan and press in Rice Krispies mixture.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together in double boiler and spread on top of Rice Krispies mixture.
Let cool at room temperature and serve.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cut into pieces.
Set aside 1/2 cup noodles for top.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, put combined ingredients.
Add nuts.
Sprinkle the 1/2 cup noodles on top. Heat in oven 40 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli delight
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
Drain sauce from bags after it is cooked.
Mix other ingredients and heat, do not boil.
Spoon over broccoli and serve.

title: sesame noodles
directions: *Hot oil is very spicy.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together
and put in dish.
Crush potato chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In
a
large microwavable bowl place cocoa, sugar, milk and margarine.	Do not stir.
Microwave 4 1/2 to 6 minutes on High until
margarine is melted.
Add nuts and vanilla.	Stir until smooth.
Spread
onto
well-greased baking dish.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken tortellini salad
directions: Boil water than add tortellini. Cook until semi-soft. Do not overcook. Mix the cooled tortellini with the chicken and dressing. Chill. You may need to add more dressing if desired.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix wafers, pecans, raisins, cherries and milk; mix well. If it will not hold together with milk, add a little cherry juice. Shape into a long loaf; roll up in wax paper. Then wrap with foil. Refrigerate 24 hours before cutting. Will keep for 3 to 4 weeks in refrigerator if it is kept tightly covered.

title: chocolate caramel brownies
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix and nuts.
Stir in 2/3 cup evaporated milk.
Spread half of batter into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes. In saucepan, combine caramels and remaining 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Stir over low heat until caramels are melted.
Sprinkle chocolate morsels over baked layer; drizzle caramel mixture over top.
Drop remaining batter by heaping teaspoonful over caramel mixture.
Return to 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes (top layer will be soft).
Cool completely before cutting into bars.

title: easy peach jam
directions: Wash, peel, pit and crush peaches; measure 4 cups.
Place in large kettle with water.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add sugar and over medium heat, boil until thick, about 20 minutes.
Pour while hot into sterilized jars; seal.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk to the egg mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and prunes.
Mix well and pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish which has been lightly greased with butter.
Bake at 300° in preheated oven for one hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash. Mix all ingredients except 1/4 of stuffing mix. Put extra mix on top and bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes. May top with grated cheese.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Melt butter; mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Done when a toothpick comes out clean.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan; cook and stir with whisk.
Put in baked pie shell.
Add meringue and bake until brown.

title: apple streusel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 or 10-inch tube pan.
To prepare streusel, in a medium bowl, combine brown sugar, apples, nuts, flour, and cinnamon.
Stir in melted butter.
Prepare cake.

title: gazpacho(low-fat)
directions: Add all the ingredients to a blender or food processor and blend until smooth.
Refrigerate, covered, for 12 to 24 hours before serving.
Serve in chilled soup bowls.

title: tangy party punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients. Stir in ginger ale. Add scoops of sherbet. Serve immediately.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Dissolve cocoa in coffee and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla to milk.
Mix soda, salt and flour together.
Alternate, adding milk and flour mixtures to creamed mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Cook chopped onion and green pepper in bacon grease until soft.
Stir in sugar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Cook an additional 10 minutes.

title: graham bread
directions: Mix well.
(It is a stiff batter.)
Pour into bread pan.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage until done; crumble and drain.
Spread each slice of bread with butter.
Cut into cubes and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sausage, then top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour over the top of sausage.
Chill for 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: mexican rice
directions: Cook and stir pepper and onion until tender.
Add corn and broth; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add cheese.
Fluff with fork.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: Melt shortening in the warm water.
Dissolve yeast in same water in large mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Add sugar, salt, eggs, milk and baking powder.
Slowly add 1 cup flour while scraping sides. Add flour until stiff enough to knead.
Add flour to soft dough, about 5 minutes.
Let rise.
Mix down once.
Shape into rolls, coffee cake, tea ring, cinnamon rolls or pecan rolls.
Bake at 375°.

title: hot mexican dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish (except sour cream).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and scoop sour cream on top.
Serve warm with plain nacho chips.

title: corn meal biscuits
directions: In large saucepan warm, but do not boil, milk and slowly pour in corn meal.
Cook until like mush.
Dissolve active dry yeast in warm water; add sugar, shortening, eggs, salt and flour to corn meal mush mixture.
Blend until smooth.
Turn out on floured board. Knead 8 minutes; place in greased bowl.
Let rise in warm place to double in size.
Roll out to desired thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on sheet; let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dale's savory frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat cheese and sugar together.
Fold in whipped topping first.
Then fold in drained pineapple and strawberries with juice; then add nuts and sliced bananas.
Spray with nonstick vegetable spray a 9 x 13-inch pan or large mold and freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 20 to 30 minutes before serving to make it easier to slice into squares.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Stir together first 4 ingredients with a fork until crumble. Press into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Cool in pan on a wire rack.

title: burger bean cups
directions: Thoroughly mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, breadcrumbs, onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Divide into 4 mounds; flatten each into 5-inch circle.
Turn up edge to make a 1/2-inch rim.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining soup, beans and dill.
Spoon into burger cups.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grilled hash browns
directions: Place potatoes on heavy-duty foil (20 x 18-inch) coated with nonstick cooking spray. Sprinkle with onion, bouillon, seasoned salt and pepper. Drizzle with butter. Fold foil around potatoes and seal tightly. Grill, covered, over indirect medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender, turning once.

title: baked roast beef hash
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased baking dish at 350° until mixture is hot and the top browned, for about 30 minutes.

title: quick 'n crunchy cornbread twists
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough.
Brush with margarine. Sprinkle with sesame seed; press lightly into dough.
Separate at perforations into 16 strips.
Twist each strip and place on 1 large or 2 small ungreased cookie sheets, pressing ends down firmly.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.
Makes 16.

title: baby food plum cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: fruit coffee cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and sour cream. Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Stir flour mixture into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.

title: chocolate dipped strawberries
directions: Wash
strawberries.
Gently
pat
dry.	Place
on paper towels until
room
temperature.
In
top	of double boiler or saucepan over
hot water, combine chips, margarine, corn syrup and rum. Heat
until chips are melted, stirring occasionally. Turn off heat.
Hold chocolate mixture over lukewarm water for dipping. Dip
each strawberry into mixture until 2/3 of berry is coated. Allow
excess chocolate to drip off.
Place berry, stem side down,
on waxed paper-lined cookie sheet to harden. Chill until chocolate
is
set,
about	15 minutes.
Serve as confection or garnish
for fruit trays or desserts.
Makes 36 to 48 strawberries.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In large pot, put in 1-quart broth; add celery, green pepper, onion, garlic and mushroom soup.
Bring to boil; add spaghetti. Cook spaghetti until done.
Do not drain.
Add remaining ingredients and heat until cheese melts.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt in a saucepan.
Pour in 1 cup of milk.
Cook on low heat; as it starts to thicken, gradually add other cup of milk to keep mixture from lumping.
When thickens, remove from heat.
Take out some of hot mixture and mix well in small bowl with egg yolks.
Return to stove; cook about 2 minutes. When desired thickness, remove and add margarine and vanilla. Top with egg white meringue or whipped cream.

title: skillet potatoes
directions: Brown bacon; set aside.
Put all ingredients in pan and heat slowly.
Break bacon into small pieces and sprinkle on top.

title: marshmallow truffles
directions: Arrange marshmallows on tray; freeze 15 minutes.
Microwave chips in microwavable bowl on High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred, stirring every minute.
Dip marshmallows into melted chocolate; turn until coated.
Roll in pecans or sprinkles. Place on wax paper-lined tray.
Refrigerate or keep in cool dry place.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix brown sugar into melted butter.
Sprinkle nuts into butter and sugar mixture.
Arrange pineapple slices in mixture to cover bottom of dish.
Place cherries in center of pineapple rings.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Turn cake onto long cake plate or pan immediately past removing from oven.

title: jalapeno fudge
directions: Spread thin layer of chopped jalapenos in 9 x 13-inch pan. (Needs to be a glass pan.)
Grate cheese and spread over peppers. In separate dish, beat eggs and milk, then pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until edges are slightly brown. Cut and serve.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar and flour.
Melt butter and add. Mix well.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: shrimp and pasta salad(servings:  6)
directions: In jar, shake together oil, lemon juice, soy sauce, sugar, mustard and sesame seed.
Combine remaining ingredients, except shrimp, with this dressing.
Chill.
Before serving, stir in shrimp.

title: lemon luscious dessert
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 8 minutes.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Saute onion in shortening; add seasonings and chicken and saute about 12 minutes.
Cover and simmer slowly until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
Add sour cream to pan drippings and mix well.
Put chicken on platter and pour the gravy mixture over noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Thoroughly cream softened butter with sugar. Blend in chocolate and vanilla. Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each. Pour into a baked and cooled pie shell. Chill! Top with whipped cream and nuts.

title: easy cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip until smooth. Pour into pie crust and top with cherry pie filling.
May half mixture to make 2 pies, if desired.
This is a very rich dessert.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: In a food processor, mince garlic.
Add chutney, curry and cream cheese and whirl until blended.
Open tomatoes by slicing a cap at the top, leaving partially attached.
Hollow out tomatoes. Using a pastry bag, fill each tomato with stuffing and replace cap.
Stuffing also makes a great dip for other vegetables.

title: upside down pineapple and carrot cake
directions: Drain pineapple reserving syrup; set aside.
Melt oleo in 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan.
Stir in tidbits, nuts, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon pineapple juice; spread evenly in pan.

title: spinach balls(to make 10 dozen)
directions: Mix well; shape into marble size balls from teaspoon.
If you want to freeze, do so before baking.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or a little longer.
Best to bake on cookie sheets.
Let cool about 2 or 3 minutes before you serve.

title: curried stuffed eggs
directions: Halve eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks; press them through a strainer into a bowl.
Add margarine, mayonnaise, curry, salt and peppers.
Mix well.
Fit a pastry bag with a star pastry tube and fill with yolk mixture.
Pipe rosettes of yolk mixture into egg white halves.
Put filled eggs in a single layer in a large plastic container.
Cover tightly and refrigerate up to 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before serving.

title: mexican macaroni
directions: Brown sausage, onion and mango.
Add precooked and drained macaroni, tomatoes, milk, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Put into a casserole dish and place enough American cheese slices to cover the casserole.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix until crumbly (don't use hands).
Knead and bake at 450° for 7 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage leaves in salted water a few minutes to soften; drain.
Combine 2 tablespoons soup with remaining ingredients.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Simmer the squash and drain.
Add the onion, soup, carrots and sour cream.
Mix the stuffing with the melted margarine.
Place most of the stuffing mix in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread with rest of ingredients mixed together.
Spread rest of stuffing mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: oven pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 400° to 425°.
In a 9-inch iron skillet, melt butter.
Mix flour, eggs, milk and nutmeg; add to melted butter. Bake for 15 minutes until golden brown.
Sprinkle generously with powdered sugar and return to oven for 3 more minutes.
Remove and pour the juice of 1 lemon over the top.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs lengthwise into half.
Take out yolks and mash with a fork.
Mix in salt and pepper, mustard and salad dressing. Fill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping it lightly.
Can sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Cover and refrigerate no longer than 24 hours.

title: heartburn remedy
directions: Place sugar, vinegar and lemon juice in an 8 ounce glass; mix. Add baking soda.
Fill glass with water and drink immediately. Try this, it helps!

title: spatzle(german egg noodles)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat until it comes easily away from sides of the bowl.
Push through spatzle maker or colander with the back of a wooden spoon into a big pot of boiling water.
Cook gently for 3 to 5 minutes and then drain.
Spatzle may also be browned lightly in butter before serving.

title: shrimp with asparagus
directions: In large pan, saute asparagus in olive oil and butter until tender. Add pesto, onion and garlic. Saute until tender. Add shrimp and saute until cooked. Salt and pepper to taste. Garnish with red pepper and/or lemon. Serves 2.

title: chocolate bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring half and half and whipping cream to just simmering basis in a heavy medium saucepan.
Remove immediately from heat.
Place chocolate chips in a large bowl. Pour cream mixture over, stirring until all chocolate melts.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, egg, liqueur and vanilla. Whisk until blended.
Add bread cubes. Toss to mix well. Transfer to an 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Let stand for 15 minutes. Bake until bread pudding is set and top puffs, about 30 minutes. Transfer to rack and cool slightly.
Pudding will appear to fall.
Sift powdered sugar over bread pudding. Serve warm with a dollop of whipped cream or a scoop of ice cream.
This can also be served with a custard sauce or fruit mixture, even a splash of Triple Sec.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked pretzels
directions: Place pretzels in bottom of broiler pan.
Mix other ingredients and pour over pretzels. Stir.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes, stirring when halfway done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and lightly grease a 9 x 9-inch baking dish. In a medium bowl, combine butter, eggs, corn bread mix, whole and creamed corn and sour cream. Spoon mixture into prepared dish. Bake for 45 minutes or until the top is golden brown. Makes 8 servings.

title: sticky buns
directions: Spread dough and cover with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and brown sugar.
Add raisins and nuts.
Roll up jelly roll style. Slice to desired thickness.
Melt syrup, sugar and butter; mix well.

title: chicken with chipped beef
directions: Mix soup and sour cream in bowl; set aside.
Place alternate layers of chicken and chipped beef in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish (beginning with chicken).
Pour soup-sour cream mixture over chicken and beef.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 300°.
Can be served over rice or noodles or eaten as is!

title: egg custard
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Set aside.
Scald milk in saucepan with butter.
Add to egg mixture slowly and beat well.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Combine Bisquick mix, 1/2 cup sugar, shortening and milk; spread in 8-inch baking dish.
Put chopped fruit over dough and sprinkle sugar on top.
Pour hot water over all. Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: lasagna
directions: Remove casing from sausage.
In skillet, crumble and brown meat slowly; drain.
Add garlic, basil, tomatoes and tomato paste. Simmer uncovered 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles in boiling water; drain and rinse.
In medium bowl, beat eggs with a fork.
Add cottage cheese, parmesan cheese, parsley and pepper to eggs.
Layer 1/2 of the lasagna noodles in a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Spread with 1/2 the cottage cheese mixture.
Add 1/2 the mozzarella cheese and 1/2 the meat sauce. Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain grease.
Mix sausage, sour cream, soup and onion together.
Best when served warm.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Cook eggs, flour, sugar and juice from pineapple together until thick.
Cool and add pineapple, marshmallows and Cool Whip.

title: chicken denise
directions: Pound out each chicken breast, then season them with salt and pepper.
Mix together chopped broccoli, cheese and eggs in large bowl.
Add the bread crumbs a little at a time until mixture binds together.
Place a spoonful of broccoli-cheese mixture in the center of each chicken breast.
Fold the sides of the chicken breast into the center to seal in broccoli-cheese mixture.
Fasten with toothpick.
Place in baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
If there is broccoli-cheese mixture left over, spoon it around the chicken breasts in the dish.
Brush tops of chicken breasts with melted butter and season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with chicken gravy, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp tetrazzini
directions: In a skillet, saute onion in margarine.
Add shrimp and mushrooms and cook until shrimp are pink.
Remove from heat.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in crock pot.
Brown hamburger and add to the melted cheese in the crock pot.
Add chili seasoning mix, mushroom soup, and green chilies.
Stir well.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: quick broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water according to package directions. Drain well; mash with back of spoon.
Stir in oleo and shredded cheese.
Add soup and milk.
Blend well, heating on medium-high until warm through.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except coconut in blender.
Blend on low speed 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Let stand 5 minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal spice cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats in a large bowl; add butter and allow to melt, stirring occasionally.
When cooled to lukewarm, add sugars, eggs and vanilla; stir briskly to combine.
Sift flour and remaining ingredients in another bowl and add to oat mixture. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool for a few minutes.
Spread with frosting and broil.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: To make sauce, mix mayonnaise, soup, curry powder and lemon juice.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer in order:
cut up chicken, broccoli and cheese.
Cover with sauce mixture.
Top with either bread crumbs or grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and top is lightly browned.

title: black forest pie
directions: Spread 1 cup of whipped topping on bottom of pie crust. Combine milk and pudding mix in medium bowl.
Blend with wire whisk or electric mixer (low speed) for 1 minute.
Fold in 1 1/2 cups whipped topping.
Spread over whipped topping in crust.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Add milk; mix.
Mix flour, soda and spices together.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk mixture and beat 2 minutes.
Add raisins and nuts and mix well. Bake at 350° and bake about one hour or until done.

title: butter pecan cookies
directions: Mix and roll into walnut size balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: red cabbage
directions: Quarter and core cabbage.
Slice thinly to make 12 cups. Combine with onion and apple in large kettle.
Add bacon drippings, salt, sugar, vinegar, water and allspice.
Tie bay leaf, cloves and peppercorns in small pieces of cheesecloth.
Add to cabbage.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Uncover, simmer 1 hour longer.
Remove spice bag.
Serve hot.

title: apple nut pudding
directions: Gradually add sugar to egg.
Beating until sugar is dissolved.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in vanilla and nuts. Pour into 8 inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Combine jello and water; cool.
Mash corned beef in bowl.
Add celery and onions.
Mix with salad dressing.
Last, add cooled jello.
Stir good.
Put in serving dish.
Refrigerate.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix and press into greased 10 x 13-inch pan.

title: sharon l's creole gumbo
directions: Steam or saute vegetables in large soup or stock pot until soft.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and about 4 to 6 cups chicken stock and water.
When liquid starts to boil, add raw chicken and shrimp.
Add enough water to almost cover meat.
Add spices.
Cut up links.
Simmer until chicken and shrimp are done.
Add all other ingredients and simmer.
If gumbo gets to thick, add more chicken, stock or water.
Serve over long grain white rice in a bowl. Sprinkle with file powder and add hot sauce to taste.
French bread and salad make the meal.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar, Karo and salt.
Cook on High 7 to 9 minutes. Take out and stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook on High 2 or 3 minutes.
Take out and add soda.
Mix until foamy.
Butter pan sides and bottom.
Pour in pan and level.
Cool in refrigerator and break into pieces.

title: moon cake
directions: Bring water and butter or margarine to a boil; add cup of flour.
Stir rapidly until it forms a ball.
Remove from heat and add the eggs, one at a time, beating after adding each egg. Spread the mixture onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool crust for 20 minutes before adding filling.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In a bowl, combine mushrooms, soup, sour cream, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Let flavors combine for a few minutes.
Cut round steak into 1/4 x 2-inch pieces and chop onion.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Use 1/4 pound sausage to 1 loaf bread.
Cook the sausage for 3 to 4 minutes.
Boil onion, celery, chicken base and water for a few minutes.
Mix everything together and stuff bird.
Good luck!

title: grandma's broken glass jello cake
directions: Prepare each Jell-O separately, using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each.
Pour each into separate 8 x 8-inch pans and chill.
Mix pineapple juice and sugar.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and dissolve lemon Jell-O in hot juice.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and chill.
Mix crumbs and margarine.
Press into bottom of a 9-inch cheese cake spring pan. Cut orange, cherry and lime Jell-O into 1/2-inch cubes.
Whip cream; blend with lemon Jell-O that is partially set.
Fold in Jell-O cubes.
Pour into crumb lined pan.
Chill about 5 hours. Run knife along sides of pan before serving.

title: overnight coffeecake
directions: Place pieces of frozen dough into well of buttered Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Combine dry pudding mix with sugar and nuts. Pour melted margarine over frozen dough and sprinkle with dry pudding mixture.
Leave pan out overnight.
Dough will rise by morning.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Invert on large plate.

title: tuna, egg and macaroni casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in order given.
Blend 3/4 of cheese with milk with tuna mixture.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: coconut orange cake
directions: Beat shortening at medium speed with an electric mixer until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into greased and floured 2 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Split cake layers in half to make 4 layers.
Spread Custard Filling between layers.
Spread top and sides with Snow Peak Frosting and with coconut.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oleo and two sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, salt, flour and soda.
Fold in oatmeal and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: hearts of celery parmesan
directions: Rinse and cut hearts of celery into lengths to fit in a casserole
dish.
Add water, Accent and margarine; steam until tender.
Season
to taste with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and serve hot.

title: roast pork tenderloin
directions: Rinse meat, pat dry and rub with garlic cloves.
Mix in bowl the sage, marjoram and salt.
Sprinkle mixture onto all sides of meat.
Place fat side up on top of racks sprayed with Pam in a shallow baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Slice into thin pieces.
Serves 4.

title: apple crisp(very easy and fast)
directions: Layer apples (1 layer) around buttered pie pan; sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and cake mix and drizzle butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until brown.
Serve warm or cold.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Line baking dish with chipped dried beef.
Remove bone from chicken breasts.
Roll each half and wrap with bacon slice.
Place on top of dried beef.
Mix undiluted soup with sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 3 hours at 300°.
Do not add salt.
This is good warmed over.

title: slow-cooker scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine water and cream of tartar in large bowl; mix well. Add potatoes and stir well. (This will help keep the potatoes from darkening.) Drain. Turn potatoes into slow cooker.

title: bran muffins
directions: Add baking soda in boiling water and let sit until cool. Cream in food processor butter and sugar.
Add 2 eggs and blend. Add buttermilk and flour (alternate buttermilk and flour, a little at a time).
Add the cooled water with baking soda.
Pour mixture into large mixing bowl.
Add Bran Flakes and mix.
Add All-Bran and mix.
Mix in raisins if desired.
Cover bowl and let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Fill muffin tins 3/4 full and bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.
This makes a large batch.
It can sit in refrigerator for 1 week and you can make muffins as needed.

title: peanut butter thumbprints
directions: Make dough as directed.
Shape into 1-inch balls and place 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Make a dent in the middle of each ball with your thumb.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Fill dents with jelly or kisses.
Cool 1 minute, then remove from cookie sheet.

title: chicken noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Put soup and water in glass dish. Put chicken on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn chicken. Bake another 30 minutes. Melt margarine in skillet. Moisten bread crumbs with butter. Sprinkle on top. Bake 10 minutes longer.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Top with potato chips.
