Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mama's rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in water and salt until done, about 25 minutes. Add additional water, if necessary to avoid rice getting too thick and dry.
Add butter to rice.
Beat eggs and sugar and fold into rice.
Add milk, flavoring and a drop or two of food coloring, if desired.
Cook over low heat, stirring until almost boiling.
Add additional milk if necessary.
Could use lemon flavoring instead of vanilla.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and 3 tablespoons butter.
Blend remaining butter with cheese until softened.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar; beat well.
Blend in one egg, 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Set aside.
Beat 2 eggs until thick and light in color. Gradually add 3/4 cup sugar; beat until thick.
Add baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup flour.
Blend in cooled chocolate mixture, nuts and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add cheese mixture, spreading evenly.
Top with tablespoons of chocolate batter.
Zigzag spatula through batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel and cut tomatoes.
Put in large pot; add other ingredients.
Cook for about 45 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal or freeze.

title: coleslaw
directions: Make dressing by beating egg in saucepan or double boiler with sugar, mustard, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until mixture is of consistency of thick cream.
Remove from fire and whip in 1/2 block of butter or 1/2 cup of sweet cream.
Pour over chilled cabbage while hot, mixing well. Chill before serving.
More seasoning can be added to suit taste.

title: tortoni
directions: Saute all ingredients together; top with cheddar cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Can be made in electric cooker. Serve with crisp salad and garlic bread.
Add water to make consistency of spaghetti, if needed.
Serves 30.

title: gourmet clam chowder
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in large frypan until the onions and celery are slightly translucent and potatoes are not brown.
Mix roux in separate pot.

title: beefed-up pot roast
directions: Cook beef in Dutch over over medium heat until brown, lower heat. Sprinkle both sides with salt and pepper,.Add water and heat to boiling. Lower heat, cover and simmer on range or 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours . Add vegetables. Cover and cook until tender, another hour. Transfer to platter. Gravy: Add enough water to broth to measure 2 cups.
Shake 1/2 cup cold water and 1/4 cup flour and stir into broth. Boil/stir one minute

title: cinnamon-pineapple buns
directions: Drain pineapple.

Mix together thoroughly the pineapple, 1/2 cup melted butter, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and pecans. Spoon into 12 muffin cups. Combine remaining ingredients and spoon over cinnamon-pineapple mixture.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Immediately turn upside down on rack or tray to remove buns.
Serve warm.
Makes 12.

title: lemon jelly roll
directions: Grease and line jelly roll pan.
Beat eggs until thick. Gradually beat in sugar.
Beat in water and vanilla.
Sift together and beat in all at once the flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Loosen edges and immediately turn cake upside down on a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Quickly and carefully pull off paper.
Spread with lemon filling and roll, beginning at short end.
Wrap in towel and cool.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese and pasta in a pot
directions: Cook ground beef in a little vegetable oil in a large, deep frying pan until brown, stirring often with a fork.
Drain off any excess fat.
Add onions, garlic, spaghetti sauce, stewed tomatoes and undrained mushrooms; mix well.
Simmer 20 minutes or until onions are soft.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Cream butter and oleo; add sugar and eggs, beating well after each.
Add other ingredients.
Bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Top while warm with 1/4 cup apricot nectar and enough confectioners sugar to make glaze.

title: donuts
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, milk and melted butter.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Turn onto floured board and roll 1/2-inch thick. Cook in hot fat.

title: dutch style beef cabbage
directions: Trim excess fat from meat and cut into 3/4 inch cubes. Combine flour, salt and pepper. Coat meat with flour mixture and brown all sides in skillet of hot oil. Drain and transfer to slow cooker. Put onions and mushrooms in same skillet. Combine water, vinegar and bouillon. Stir into skillet mixture, scraping brown bits from skillet. Pour all into cooker. Cover and cook on low heat for 8 hours. Serve over cooked cabbage. May also be served over rice, mashed potatoes or hot biscuits.

title: jiffy angel squares
directions: Cut cake in squares.
Toast coconut.
Melt margarine with milk.
Add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add more milk, if necessary.
Roll in coconut.
Cool.

title: deviled swiss steaks
directions: Mix mustard with flour and pound into steak.
Brown in Wesson oil on both sides.
Add salt, pepper, soup, onions, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Place in a small roaster or electric skillet.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil. Turn off burner and stir in peanut butter.
Pour ingredients over cereal and mix well.
In double boiler, mix both packages of chips.
Press cereal mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, then spread chip mixture on top. Set and cool. Cut like brownies.

title: nippy dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together and chill.
Serve with raw veggies.
Two tablespoons = 22 calories.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Beat eggs until they are foamy and stir in oil, sugar, squash and vanilla.
Add other ingredients.
Bake for one hour or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Make one large loaf or two small loaves.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine
all
ingredients.
Pour into well-greased, hot skillet.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together and freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine peaches, brown sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice and cinnamon.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole that has been sprayed with a nonfat cooking spray.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add biscuit mix and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Flatten with fork.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Do not overbake.
Cool.
Store tightly covered at room temperature.

title: cheese cake
directions: Pour all together in mixer and blend at high speed for 15 minutes.
Makes 7 (10-inch) cheese cakes.
Bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: green chili stew
directions: Saute beef or pork in grease (coat with flour, salt and pepper as desired).
Cook until well browned.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Cut off top of each green pepper; remove seeds.
Cover peppers in boiling salted water and cook for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Cook beef, onion and garlic in margarine, stirring to crumble meat. Add tomatoes; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs; stir to mix.
Stuff peppers with beef mixture and place in shallow pan.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: jewel salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine juice with lemon juice and cold water to measure 1 2/3 cups liquid.
Add to Jell-O.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in nuts, cranberry sauce and pineapple.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart mold and chill.
Serves 10 to 12, 164 calories per serving.

title: strawberry crunch
directions: Cut margarine into flour until it is evenly distributed. Add pecans and shape into the bottom of a 9 1/2 x 11-inch oblong glass baking dish. Bake for 30 minutes in a medium oven or until brown. Set aside and let cool.

title: cookies that bite back
directions: Set the butter out to soften ahead of time.
Beat the softened butter and brown sugar together until well blended.
Beat in the vanilla, egg yolks and lemon rind.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Soak raisins in the water and add with flour.
Add flavoring, cinnamon and salt.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour and baking soda alternately with raisins and water.
Mix in oatmeal and bake.

title: corn bread salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine vegetables; stir in dressing. Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Yields 8 servings.

title: low-fat crock-pot chicken and rice
directions: Mix in crock-pot the soup and rice.
Place chicken on top. Add diced celery.
Put lid on; cook on low for 4 hours, until chicken is done.

title: garlic bread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Peel and finely chop garlic; mix garlic with margarine or butter.
Cut bread crosswise into 1-inch slices. Spread margarine mixture over 1 side of each bread slice. Reassemble the loaf; wrap securely in heavy-duty aluminum foil. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until hot.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all together, then pour 1 bottle Italian dressing over. Marinate overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: mustard chicken
directions: Mix Tabasco and mustard together and spread over chicken, then coat with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: ham and cheese soup
directions: In a large sauce pan, saute onions, celery, and bell pepper in olive oil until tender.
Add ham and continue to saute to release some oils and meld the flavors.
Add stock, bay leaf, and basil.
Simmer to reduce slightly (20 to 30 minutes).
Add cream and return to a boil to thicken a bit.
Slowly add cheese, stirring constantly. Serve immediately.
Garnish with green onion.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.
Keeps several months.

title: dump it cake
directions: Dump all into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Do not grease pan or stir. Dribble butter over top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: don's dairy mart onion rings
directions: Mix in large bowl. Dip sliced onions. Drop in hot oil; cook and turn over. Remove when golden brown.

title: home style potatoes
directions: In large saucepan, bring broth to a boil.
Add cabbage; cover and simmer 5 to 8 minutes.
Measure liquid in saucepan.
Add milk and margarine; bring to a boil.
Stir in potatoes and corned beef; heat thoroughly.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine yeast and warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Add buttermilk and set aside.
Combine all remaining ingredients except shortening in a large bowl.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mix resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk mixture, stirring with a fork, until moist.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese and taco seasoning with mixer. Spread in flat pie plate.
Add chopped lettuce, covering completely.
Next, add layer of chopped tomatoes, finishing with layer of Cheddar cheese.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add sherbet and Cool Whip to hot jello.
Jello should be hot so sherbet and Cool Whip will melt. Stir in mandarin oranges.
Top with extra Cool Whip.

title: caramel mix
directions: Place cereal, peanuts, and pretzels in large bowl or pan.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Crust:
Mix pretzels, butter and brown sugar until well blended.
Spread on bottom of 9 x 13 inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring water, Crisco, margarine and cocoa to a boil in a saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Blend sugar, flour and salt, then pour in hot cocoa mix.

title: shrimp appetizers
directions: Melt oleo or butter,
add
the other listed ingredients and pour over 1 pound
of
shrimp (medium are best).
Marinate covered for several hours.
Bake,
uncovered,
at
350° for 20 minutes. Serve hot with toothpicks.

title: whole wheat pancakes
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl.
Mix together milk and egg substitute.
Stir in flour mixture.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place fruit in oblong 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dot with margarine. Make a mixture in order of 1/4 cup melted margarine milk, sugar, flour and baking powder.
Spread mixture over fruit.
Mix cornstarch and sugar; sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over entire pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until browned.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain and chop.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer ham and cheese over broccoli.
Beat remaining ingredients with hand mixer until smooth.
Slowly pour over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Microwave Directions:
In 2-quart casserole heat broccoli, uncovered, on High (full power) 6 minutes, or until almost tender. Stir in soup mix.
Blend with milk and flour.
Heat, stirring occasionally, 12 minutes or until soup is slightly thickened and broccoli is tender.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.

title: apple butter bread
directions: Combine eggs, margarine and apple butter; beat well.
Stir in pecans.
Add combined dry ingredients, stirring just until ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center of loaf comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: In a bowl, stir together yogurt, sour cream and vegetable soup mix. Squeeze excess liquid from spinach.
Finely chop the spinach. Stir spinach, water chestnuts, onion and ground red pepper into yogurt mixture. Cover and chill
for 2 to 24 hours before serving. Serve with assorted vegetables or crackers.

title: stars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine all ingredients except rolls.
Unroll dough; fold in half.
Roll into a 10-inch square.
Cut into 16 (2 1/2-inch) squares.
Make 1-inch cut diagonally from corner of each square toward the middle.
Place 1 heaping teaspoonful of filling in center.
Fold every other dough tip toward center.
Insert a wooden toothpick into center of each star to hold dough.
Bake on greased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: homemade ketchup or catsup
directions: Put
all
ingredients
together (except cornstarch) and boil for
1 hour, then put through sieve (strainer).
Replace on stove and
bring	to a boil, then add cornstarch (to water first) or as much to thicken as you like.
Bottle and seal.

title: scramble
directions: Pour pretzels, dry cereal and nuts into a large roaster. Heat butter, sauce and salt
in sauce pan over low heat.
Pour over dry mixture and mix well.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour. Stir occasionally.
Drain on paper towel until cool.
Store in tins.
Indefinite shelf life.

title: homemade chicken pot pie
directions: Combine ingredients together and pour over chicken mixture. Bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour.
Place tin foil on bottom of oven as this tends to run over while baking.
Serve with biscuits or bread as there is ample creamed gravy as in a pot pie.

title: marie's fruit juice sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan. Stir in pineapple and orange juice and bring to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add lemon juice. Serve hot or cold. Makes 1 1/2 cups of sauce. Serve over Pineapple Upside-Down Cake.

title: vanilla wafer pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add milk and vanilla.
Fold in vanilla wafers, nuts and coconut with a spoon.
Bake in tube pan 2 hours at 275°.

title: nana flynn's meat loaf
directions: Break bread slices in small pieces.
Add milk, just enough to moisten.
Combine hamburg, egg, poultry seasoning, sugar, salt and pepper; mix well.
Shape into loaf using loaf pan or casserole dish. Pour tomato soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Serve with baked potatoes.
Enjoy.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Melt butter and 1/2 cup cocoa.
Cool for a few minutes.
Cream eggs and sugar.
Add cocoa mixture.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts. Mix well with mixer.
Flour oblong pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Take out of oven, cover with marshmallows and put back in oven until marshmallows are soft.

title: great cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs, oil and milk together.
Make well in center of dry ingredients mixture.
Pour in liquid; mix.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: pecan cinnamon biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In small mixing bowl, whip cream until stiff.
In another bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add to whipped cream and blend with a rubber spatula until a firm dough forms.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface and knead for one minute.
Roll out dough into a 1/4-inch thick rectangle approximately 9 x 12-inches.
Using a pastry brush, spread the melted butter over the dough.
Sprinkle evenly with cinnamon and sugar.
Beginning with a long side, roll up like a jelly-roll; with a serrated knife, cut into 3/4-inch slices. Place close together in a greased 8-inch round cake pan.
Bake for 15 minutes or until tops of rolls are lightly browned.
While rolls bake, prepare topping.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Make sauce.
As it thickens, add cheese and beaten yolks.
Stir until thick and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in a casserole 1 hour at 350°.
Serve immediately.

title: minty lamb burgers
directions: Prepare hot coals for grilling.
Place the ground lamb in a bowl and mix well with onion, garlic and chopped mint, being sure not to overmix.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Gently form the mixture into 4 patties.

Grill the burgers over hot coals, 3-inches from heat, for about 4 minutes per side for rare meat or 5 minutes per side for medium-rare. Serve the lamb burgers immediately on buns topped with a tomato slice and a dollop of yogurt, if desired.

title: oven fried catfish nuggets
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Dip fish in margarine; roll in crumb mixture.
Place fish 1/2 inch apart on foil lined baking sheets.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Turn nuggets; bake 5 minutes more.
Serve at once.
Makes 7 appetizers.

title: hopscotchers
directions: Combine over hot water in double boiler the butterscotch morsels, corn syrup, water and shortening.
Heat until melted and smooth.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add noodles and mix well.
Cool slightly and fold in marshmallows or dates.
Drop by rounded tablespoons onto waxed paper lined cookie sheets.
Chill in refrigerator about
20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: In large bowl, dissolve gelatin completely in 3 cups boiling water; stir in 3 cups cold water.
Refrigerate; stir occasionally until mixture mounds slightly.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add juice or water.
Chill until partially thick.
Fold in rest of ingredients.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, peanuts, corn syrup and molasses in 2-quart microwave-proof mixing bowl.
Microwave at High 4 minutes.
Stir. Microwave at High an additional 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Microwave 1 minute longer and remove from oven.
Add baking soda.
Stir until well mixed.
Spread on aluminum foil covered cookie sheet to cool.
Break in pieces when firm.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: spaghetti sauce(north carolina-style)
directions: Soften onions, green pepper; brown ground beef.
Put with everything in crock-pot.
Cook on high for 2 to 3 hours.
Turn down to low setting.

title: chicken dressing supreme
directions: Combine bread, onions and seasonings; place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spread chicken over dressing.
Melt butter.
Blend in flour until smooth.
Add broth; stir well.
Add eggs; cook until thickened.
Pour sauce over chicken and dressing.
Sprinkle lightly with bread crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
15 to 20 servings.

title: soy sauce marinade
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use to marinate beef, pork or chicken before grilling or broiling.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Great for shish kebabs.

title: cheese rarebit
directions: Cut cheese into pieces.
Melt butter in top of double boiler. Add cheese.
As it melts gradually, add beer, stirring constantly with wooden spoon.
Add paprika and mustard.
Stir mixture until cheese is melted.
Serve on toast.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Drain.
Add next 6 ingredients. Mix well.
Cover with cracker crumbs and drizzle with butter. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Simmer scallops in boiling, salted water 3 to 4 minutes; drain.
Cook onion in 2 tablespoons of butter until tender.
Add soup, milk, curry powder, pepper and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add scallops to green beans and peas and put in casserole.
Pour soup mixture over.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese, bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons of butter.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: southern yellow corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour the batter into a greased 8 or 9-inch round pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream the sugar and oil for 2 minutes.
Beat eggs in thoroughly. Add flour and beat until blended.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Pour into well-greased and floured pans.
May want to line entire pan with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to instructions on box.
Mix pudding; set aside.
Crumble 1/2 of the cake in a punch bowl.
Layer 1 can pie filling, 1 can pineapple, 1/2 of the pudding and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Repeat the layers.
Top with coconut and cherries.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook yellow rice as directed on package.
Add balance of ingredients.
Grate Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Wash the potatoes and cook in boiling salted water to cover 30 minutes or until tender. Drain and cool completely. Peel and cube potatoes. Combine potatoes, eggs and celery in a large bowl. Toss gently.

title: daiquiri punch
directions: Mix
undiluted	limeade and water.
Mix with strong tea and add
rum.
(This is strong and add rum accordingly.) Makes 60 servings.

title: how to boil water
directions: Fill tea kettle two-thirds full of nice clean water right from the well.
Go the wood house; bring back one big armful of nice dry wood.
Build fire in cook stove.
Put kettle on stove and bring to bubbling (boiling) point.

title: zesty carrot bake
directions: Cook carrots until tender; place in 1 quart casserole.
Combine onions, mayonnaise, water, horseradish and pepper and pour over carrots.
Combine bread crumbs and butter and sprinkle on top. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 2 to 3 more minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain off fat.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix with Veg-All and tomato soup.
Place cheese slices on top of ingredients, then press out biscuits.
Put on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Fry hamburger in large skillet.
Drain, then mix in soups. Grate cheese.
Line bottom of cooking dish with Tater Tots, then put the hamburger mix over Tater Tots.
Then put the cheese on top. Put in oven for about 45 minutes.
Serve with hot French bread.

title: mex dip
directions: At least 1 hour before preparation, set cream cheese out.
Mix cream cheese, Mozzarella cheese and chili, really folding them. Add onions, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Oops, black olives. Garnish as you see fit.
Great with Doritos or Fritos.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mock brittle
directions: Note:
Need one jelly roll pan and heavy-duty foil.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine jello and hot water.
Chill until thick.
Add salt, mayonnaise, celery, apples and pecans; then fold in 2 1/2 cups heavy cream (whipped) and 1/2 cup grapes.
Mold in 1 quart.

title: "chicken licking good" pork chops
directions: Combine flour, salt, mustard and garlic. Dredge chops in mixture. Brown chops in oil and put in crock-pot. Pour soup over and cook 3 1/2 hours on high or 6 to 8 hours on low.

title: microwave chocolate pudding
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, cornstarch and salt in a medium-size glass bowl.
Gradually stir in milk.
Microwave on High (full power) for 5 minutes, stirring once halfway through cooking time. Microwave on High (full power) until mixture is cooked and thickened, about 1 to 2 minutes more.
Depends on wattage of the microwave.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour into individual serving dishes.
Press plastic wrap directly onto surface of pudding.
Chill.
Serves 4.

title: lima bean surprise casserole
directions: Put lima beans in heavy pot.
Bring to boil.
Sprinkle very scant amount of salt and pepper.
Boil about 2 minutes.
Remove from fire.
While limas are cooking, generously line bottom of large size casserole with dressing mix.
Put a layer of grated cheese, a layer of chopped onion and a layer of red chopped pepper on top of the dressing mix.
Save back some cheese and peppers. Put limas on top of the previous 4 layers (mix cheese, onions and peppers) while hot.
Now sprinkle some grated cheese and red peppers on top.
Now drizzle milk over entire contents of casserole.
Put in oven.
Set at 350° for 40 minutes.
No preheating necessary.
After 15 minutes, add chopped up margarine on top of contents of the casserole.
This adds additional seasoning and moisture.

title: broken window glass cake
directions: Dissolve orange, cherry and lime Jell-O separately using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each.
Pour into three 8-inch square pans and chill until firm.
Cut firm Jell-O into 1/2-inch cubes.
Mix pineapple juice and sugar; heat until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon Jell-O until dissolved.
Add remaining cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.

title: peanut butter sandwich
directions: Note:
Combine peanut butter with one of the above ingredients.

title: taco dip
directions: Add 1 package taco mix to hamburger.
Mix sour cream with mayonnaise, then add 1 package taco mix.
Layer according to ingredients list in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve with tortilla chips (lightly seasoned type).

title: crunchy lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl combine oats, flour, nuts, sugar, baking powder and butter; stir to form a crumbly mixture.
Set aside.
In medium bowl combine sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice.
Pat 1/2 the crumb mixture evenly on bottom of 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread sweetened condensed milk mixture on top and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool thoroughly before cutting. Loosely cover any leftovers.
Makes 9 servings.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Tear tortillas into pieces.
Cover the bottom of a casserole dish with tortilla pieces.
Begin layering chicken, cheese, tomatoes and their liquid, mushroom soup, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Sprinkle top with layer of cheese.
Add chicken broth just before serving.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: golden punch
directions: Each nice ear of corn wrapped separate in wax paper and cook in microwave for 2 minutes.
Let cool and put the wrapped ears in a baggie and freeze.
Take out of freezer the number of ears you want for a meal.
Put frozen ears in microwave one ear at a time for 4 minutes.
Very delicious in winter.

title: black forest torte
directions: Mix together the pecans, 1 1/2 cups flour and 1 1/2 sticks of oleo.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: peanut butter ripple ice cream
directions: Blend peanut butter and honey.
Put 1/2 of vanilla ice cream in freezer tray.
Cover with layer of peanut butter.
Add remaining ice cream.
With a spoon, stir so that peanut butter is mixed partially with ice cream.
Refreeze.

title: shrimp de jonghe
directions: Mix butter and garlic, parsley, paprika, cayenne and sherry. Add bread crumbs and toss.
Place shrimp in baking dish.
Spoon butter mixture over it.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until crumbs brown.

title: low calorie chocolate mousse
directions: Place water, gelatin, and chocolate drink in blender and blend at low speed.
Add ice cubes one at a time.
Pour into 16 ounce glass and refrigerate.
Ready to eat in about 1/2 hour.
75 calories per serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni until cooked.
Drain and add a little milk. Add 1 can of cream of celery soup.
Mix until fully mingled.
Add chicken, onion, tomato and garlic powder.
Mix again until fully mingled.
Add sharp Cheddar cheese and mix once more.
Keep on top of stove on warm until ready to serve and top with black pepper.

title: mexican shells
directions: Cook noodles, rinse and drain.
Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Return ground beef to frying pan and add picante sauce, water, tomato sauce, chilies, onions, and 1 cup cheese.
Cook until cheese melts; mix well.
Stuff the shells with the meat mixture and top with remaining cup of cheese.
Put in microwave until the cheese melts; serve.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into Bundt pan.
Bake approximately 50 minutes at 325°.
Glaze if desired.

title: ham-noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Add milk to soup.
Blend in sour cream, mustard, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix in ham and cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: flounder au gratin
directions: Combine bread crumbs and cheese in a shallow dish.
Brush all sides of fillets with mayonnaise.
Coat with crumb mixture. Arrange in a single layer in a shallow baking pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden and fish flakes easily. Makes 4 servings.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown garlic in olive oil; add paste and water.
Simmer 10 minutes; add tomatoes and spices.
Cook 4 hours.
Add onions and mushrooms about half time.
For a special touch, steam and brown fresh Italian sausage links and add to sauce immediately.

title: taco salad
directions: Add taco seasoning to ground beef and lettuce; mix.
Combine beans, cheese, onions, tomatoes, Doritos and French dressing. Just before serving, combine warm meat with bean mixture.
Crunch up Doritos and add and toss with dressing.

title: chili con carne(texas style - hot)
directions: Brown meat.
Sprinkle enough flour into pan to coat meat. Stir until meat is rebrowned and pan is slightly coated with rebrowned meat.
Add approximately 4 to 5 cups water.
Saute onions and green pepper in separate pan.
Add to meat.
Add garlic, cominos, bay leaf and chili powder.
Simmer 1 hour or longer.

title: jeff's hot wings
directions: Heat oil in large pot.
Melt margarine and add hot sauce in separate pot.
Season chicken wings.
Place wings a few at a time in hot oil.
Cook until they come to the top of the oil and add a couple of extra minutes to the cooking time after they reach top of oil.
Drain on paper towels and place in sauce mixture for a few minutes, turning to coat.
Take out put in dish to put in oven on 250° to stay warm until all wings are done.
Any extra sauce can be used as dipping sauce for French fries.

title: cinnamon apple topping for ice cream
directions: You will also need 6 hot, half pint canning jars with lids and bands.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Put in baking dish.
Add cheese and chips on top.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until slightly browned.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the sugar, milk and butter together.
Put on stove.
Bring to a boil and boil 1 minute.
Take off heat and add the peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix together the cocoa and oats and add to the mixture.
Stir well.
Take a spoon and drop spoonfuls onto wax paper to cool.
When cool, place cookies in airtight container.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Place sugars and syrup in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter, cornflakes and nuts; press firmly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and spread over top.
Cut into bars.

title: no bake bar cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; stir constantly while bringing this to a full, rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour mixture over first layer of graham crackers and top with another layer of the whole crackers.
Let cool, then cut into smaller blocks.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Break cookies in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer ice cream about 1/2-inch or until you use all the ice cream.
Then layer Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chocolate syrup over the top.
Then decorate with cherries.
Place in freezer until ready to serve.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Lay chicken breasts in oblong baking dish.
Mix sour cream, lemon juice, horseradish and salt together and put over chicken. Prepare day before; cover with foil and refrigerate.
When ready to use, roll each piece in cracker crumbs.	Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: never fail crisp dill pickles
directions: Place
dill
and
garlic
on
bottom and proceed to put cucumbers into quart jar.
Put in the salt, sugar and vinegar; fill
with
tap
water so that cucumbers are covered.
Put jar caps
on
tight.
Place the filled jars in a preheated oven at 200°
to
225° (depending on each individual oven) on a cookie sheet.
When almost all green is gone, remove from oven, cover with towel for a few minutes and then let cool.

title: manicotti
directions: Cook noodles by package directions.
Combine cheeses.
Stuff cheese mixture in cooked noodles.
Set aside.
Mix garlic, tomatoes, tomato paste, oregano, basil and lemon juice in blender. Add sausage and blend again.
Place sauce mixture on bottom of dish.
Lay stuffed noodles on top.
Pour remaining sauce over and between noodles and bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough out on pizza pan.
Follow baking instructions on package.
Let cool.
Cream together sugar and cream cheese and spread over cookie dough.
Drain all fruit in colander and spread over a thick layer of paper towels.
Fruit needs to dry as much as possible.
Chop all fruit and mix together in a bowl.
Spread fruit over cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip, cherries and nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: mom's cookies
directions: Set aside the walnuts, coconut flakes, raisins and semi-sweet morsels.
Beat the margarine, vegetable oil, light brown sugar, egg, cold water, salt, baking soda and vanilla extract together. Add flour.
Blend well.
Stir in nuts, flakes, morsels and raisins. Then add Quaker oats.
Mix well.
Slightly flatten dough out.
It won't spread that much when the cookies are baking.
Grease cookie sheets lightly with solid Crisco.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 13 minutes.
Don't overcook.
If they look undercooked, they're probably done.

title: kielbasa delights
directions: Heat in frypan and serve hot.

title: emily's low-fat cornbread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl, make well in center of mixture.
Combine buttermilk, oil, egg and egg whites; add to cornmeal mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Coat a 10-inch cast-iron skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Heat skillet at 450° for 4 to 5 minutes or until hot.
Remove skillet from oven, pour batter into hot skillet. Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove cornbread from skillet immediately.

title: cranberry squares
directions: Cranberry sauce:
Place 4 cups fresh or frozen cranberries in a 9x13 baking dish.
Sprinkle evenly with 2 cups sugar.
Cover and bake at 300 degrees for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Stir carefully, then stir in 1/3 c orange juice.

title: macaroni delight
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
Drain and add cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Add milk, broccoli and 2 cans chicken breasts.
Stir occasionally about 10 to 15 minutes until broccoli is soft.
Serves 4.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Mix pineapple and jello first, then fold in Cool Whip and cottage cheese. Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375° Peel, slice apples and place in apple dish. Sprinkle orange or lemon juice over apples. In seperate bowl mix flour, salt, brown sugar, cinnamon and butter. Spread dough over apples. Bake 40 min. Serve warm with ice cream or whip cream.

title: quick pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Salt and fry chops in oil; set aside.
Place rice in baking dish.
Add pepper, onion, soup and water.
Lay chops on top. Cover with foil; bake at 400° for 35 minutes, or until rice is flaky and tender.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the shortening, margarine, sugar and egg.
Stir in milk and vanilla flavoring.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill dough for several hours. Roll very thin (1/16-inch).
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet; sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Blend butter, sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs, beating well. Stir in corn, then milk.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Stir only once during baking.

title: easy oven lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add water, sauce and salt.
Bring to boil.

title: taco pie
directions: Line bottom of large pie plate with rolls.
Next, layer 1/2 of taco chips (crushed).
Next, layer browned hamburger mixed with taco seasoning, water and sour cream.
Top with Cheddar cheese and remaining chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: winter salad
directions: Combine tomatoes and 2 tablespoons salt.
Let stand overnight. Drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine turmeric, allspice, sugar, 2 tablespoons salt, mustard seed and vinegar.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook 30 minutes.
Seal.
Makes 5 pints.

title: hello dollies
directions: Line basin of serving bowl with sponge fingers, ladyfingers or pound cake slices. Do not use American cake mix-type cake as sponge must be a little dry. Cover sponge layer with strawberry, raspberry or blackberry jam preserves. Pour rum or sherry over the top of mixture. Mix strawberry or other jello. Let chill until thickened. Pour over sponge/jam mixture. Mix vanilla pudding and let cool.
When jello layer is set, add a layer of fruit. Cover with cooled custard. Shortly before serving, add whipped topping or whipped cream. Garnish as desired.

title: coconut thins
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Blend.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Make small balls and flatten out on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook mixture until thick.
Add vanilla.
Add lump of butter after mixture cooks.
If mixture begins to lump, then reduce heat and beat until smooth.
Cook slow until done or thickened.
Pour into cooked pie shell.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Soak fryer in buttermilk 1 hour before frying.
Mix flour (about 1 cup) with seasonings and roll cut up chicken in it.
In a heavy skillet, cook chicken in hot fat, covered, a few minutes, then remove lid and brown slowly.
Serves 4.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Crush chips in bottom of large casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour on top of chips.
Top with cheese. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Put
sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in boiler.
Boil for 1
1/2 to
minutes.
Add
vanilla, oats, peanut butter and nuts. Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: wheat soup(shourbat amh)
directions: Soak wheat overnight; place all the spices in a piece of cloth to form a sac.
Strain the wheat and place in a pot with the meat. Add the spice cloth, reduce heat and cook for 40 minutes.
Remove the meat and spices; puree the broth and then strain.
Add the meat, tomatoes, oil and salt to the soup.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Stir to blend.
Sift flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add to sugar, oil and egg mixture.
Blend.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Blend.
Pour into prepared Bundt pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
